DESCRIPTION:<br><b>FCC Volunteers Needed to Make and Deliver Bagged Lunches
  to Newark\, Saturday September </b>1<br><br>Bridges Outreach needs our hel
 p to provide lunches to underprivileged NJ communities this summer. Bridges
  Outreach is a volunteer organization that delivers thousands of lunches ev
 ery year to NY and NJ neighborhoods in need. FCC has volunteered to provide
  250 non-perishable brown bag lunches to communities in Newark on Saturday 
 Sept. 1. <br><br><u><b>There are multiple ways you can help us meet this go
 al</b></u><br><br><b>1. Donations: </b>We need specific food donations and 
 will be accepting donations until&nbsp\;&nbsp\; Sunday August 19. We need t
 he following items:<br><ul><li>Chicken or tuna salad packets with crackers 
 (not a can of tuna or chicken)</li><li>Fruit cups</li><li>Unsweetened apple
 sauce</li><li>Nutri-grain type fruit or cereal bars</li><li>Small bags of n
 uts\, trailmix\, goldfish\, or pretzels</li><li>Brown paper lunch bags</li>
 <li>Monetary donations are also acceptable</li></ul><b><br>2. Lunch Packers
 : </b>We need volunteers to help pack the lunches on Sunday August 26 in af
 ter church in the Guild Room.&nbsp\;&nbsp\; <br><br><b>3. Lunch Deliverers:
  </b>We need up to 15 volunteers to help deliver the lunches to communities
  in Newark on the morning of Saturday Sept. 1. The entire event will likely
  go from approximately 8:30 AM – 12:30 PM. <br><b>Please contact Faith in A
 ction Chair\, Jose Ortiz\, at 201-314-1342 or at <a href="mailto:Josemortiz
 1981@gmail.com" target="_blank">Josemortiz1981@gmail.com</a> to volunteer o
 r learn more about how you can help. </b>
LAST-MODIFIED:20180807T162510Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Volunteers needed to deliver bagged lunches in Newark (Bridges Outr
 each for the homeless run)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
