DESCRIPTION:Sunday Nov 19 from 9am-2pm in the FCC back Parking Lot!\n\nHelp
  a local family have a happy Thanksgiving by contributing to our food drive
  for the Community Food Bank of New Jersey.  CFB provides food for area sou
 p kitchens\, shelters and food pantries throughout northern NJ.  \n\nHere’s
  what they need:  \n(Most needed items:  Frozen Turkeys (see note below)\, 
 Canned Yams & Sweet Potatoes\, Gravy (packs and cans)\, Cranberry Sauce\, C
 anned Vegetables\, Stuffing Mixes\, Instant Mashed Potatoes\, Applesauce\, 
 Canned Fruits\, Beverages and Boxed Desserts (be sure to check the expirati
 on date.).  Donations should be dropped off in the church parking lot.  If 
 you will not be at church that Sunday\, please consider bringing in your do
 nation earlier – marked “Thanksgiving Food Drive” and leaving it in the Tow
 er Room.  If you can help with this event\, please contact Deb Duhamel at d
 ebbieduhamel@hotmail.com.\n\nFROZEN TURKEYS CAN ONLY BE BROUGHT ON NOVEMBER
  19 and will be collected in the back parking lot!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171107T182543Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Thanksgiving Turkey and Food Drive for the  Community Food Bank of 
 NJ - 9am-2pm
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
