DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><h3><span>Join us for a thought- provoking zo
 om discussion with author\, Rev. Brooks Brendt\,on&nbsp\;November 9 at 7pm<
 /span><span> <br></span></h3><p><span>&nbsp\;The evidence of climate change
  is all around us and as people of faith we have a calling to respond.&nbsp
 \; On November 9 we will join with UCC Minister for Environmental Justice\,
  Rev. Brooks Brendt\, to discuss his book\, <u>Cathedral on Fire</u>.&nbsp\
 ;&nbsp\;<br><br>Topics include: </span></p><ul><li><span>a commitment to ca
 re for God’s     creation as our first calling</span></li><li><span>a scrip
 tural basis in pursuing     justice for a planet and its people</span></li>
 <li><span>a moral foundation for     understanding the climate crisis as an
  inequality crisis</span></li><li><span>a powerful\, sacred language for   
   articulating what fundamentally motivates people to act</span></li><li><s
 pan>a hope-giving history with the     faith leaders who launched the envir
 onmental justice movement</span></li><li><span>a rich tradition of theology
  in     times of crisis</span></li><li><span>a countercultural ethic of    
  generational justice found in the Bible</span></li><li><span>a recognition
  of youth as the     climate prophets of today</span></li></ul><p><b><span>
 FCC has purchased 50 copies of the book to be given for free to folks inter
 ested in participating in the discussion.&nbsp\;Books are available in the 
 Narthex at church during Sunday worship or in the church office during the 
 week.&nbsp\;</span></b><span><br><br><b><span>If you'd like to order your o
 wn copy of the book\, </span></b><a href="https://firstcongmontclair.us6.li
 st-manage.com/track/click?u=62bf2ca744bdb8b46fa1a7788&id=3f66e4c175&e=d2d6a
 c503b"><b><span>click here.</span></b></a></span></p><p><span><a href="http
 s://firstcongmontclair.us6.list-manage.com/track/click?u=62bf2ca744bdb8b46f
 a1a7788&id=4043ca0fc6&e=d2d6ac503b"><span>CLICK HERE FOR ZOOM LINK</span></
 a><br><br><a href="https://firstcongmontclair.us6.list-manage.com/track/cli
 ck?u=62bf2ca744bdb8b46fa1a7788&id=1ce794ca7f&e=d2d6ac503b"><span>Meeting ID
 : 836 2117 2014<br>Passcode: 451129</span></a></span></p><p><span>&nbsp\;</
 span><b><span>We look forward to sharing this&nbsp\;enlightening\, challeng
 ing and empowering conversation!&nbsp\;</span></b></p><u></u></html-blob>
LAST-MODIFIED:20221025T150808Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:How should our church respond to the climate crisis? 
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
