UID:6693mrtvm6nuegqh10ucecklki@google.com
CREATED:20180410T191719Z
DESCRIPTION:<br><p><b><span>The Lost Scriptures of Early Christianity\, 7-8
 :30 in the FCC library<br></span></b></p><p></p><span>In the last 170 years
 \, over a hundred early Christians texts have emerged from the sands of Egy
 pt\, middle-eastern markets\,and the back shelves of scholars’ libraries. F
 or the first time\, scholars and congregations have been able to translate 
 and read texts like the&nbsp\;<i><span>Gospel of Thomas</span></i>&nbsp\;an
 d the<i><span>&nbsp\;Gospel of Mary</span></i>\,which have previously eithe
 r been lost or dismissed.<br><br>There is so much to discover! In&nbsp\;<i>
 <span>The Gospel of Thomas</span></i>&nbsp\;we find more sage-like sayings 
 of Jesus and in&nbsp\;<i><span>The Acts of Paul and Thecla</span></i>&nbsp\
 ;we are introduced to a fierce female Apostle named Thecla— and these are o
 nly a couple of many texts to explore.<br><br>With such diversity of materi
 al\, these scriptures are water for the spiritually thirsty and enticing cl
 ues for anyone wondering about Christianity before it became the official r
 eligion of the Roman Empire. Come join us on this journey of discovery!<br>
 &nbsp\;<br>To help us delve into these scriptures\,<b><span>we will be read
 ing Elaine Pagels’</span></b><i><b><span>The Gnostic Gospels</span></b></i>
 <b><span>. Affordable copies are available on Amazon</span></b>.&nbsp\;This
  study will be led by Associate Pastor John Rogers\, who has produced short
  films on early Christian writings and presented on this material at confer
 ences across the country\, and Robin Bratton-Bias\, who has journeyed with 
 these texts for years. <br></span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20180419T164823Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Discover the Lost Scriptures of Early Christianity! April 18\, 25 &
  May 2
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
