CREATED:20170213T165755Z
DESCRIPTION:Kindred Spirits for Racial Justice - - “Saturday Session” May 2
 0\, from 9am-12pm \n\nOur conversations on white privilege and racial injus
 tice continue on May 20  This is the  fourth  session and we will be gather
 ing together for the first time as an interracial group.  Our moderator is 
 Emily Jones McGowan. \n\n__________________________________________________
 ______________________\n\nKSRJ is a special initiative of First Congregatio
 nal Church whose mission is to promote dialogue\, learning and deepen relat
 ionships between our diverse community.  Throughout the year we will be off
 ering various experiences and programs to help us challenge systems of raci
 al injustice\, oppression and prejudice in society and in the church.\n\nIn
  addition to special events\, we will be engaging in regular monthly conver
 sations on race on the following Saturday mornings: February 25\, March 25\
 , April 15\, May 20 and June 24.\n\nFor more information\, please see Rev. 
 Ann or John Rogers\, or email Emily Jones McGowan at ejonesmcgowan@gmail.co
 m 
LAST-MODIFIED:20170508T172847Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Kindred Spirits for Racial Justice "Saturday Sessions"
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
