BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:First Congregational Church Montclair
X-SOURCE-URL:https://fccmontclair.org/upcoming-events-at-fcc/
DTSTART:20200423T230000Z
DTEND:20200424T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260401T043557Z
UID:1h3c1k3417uv2ufhd87rb5giea@google.com
CREATED:20200420T160228Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><strong>Thursday\, April 23 7pm via Zoom Webinar through Mon
 tclair "Bounce" &nbsp\;</strong> <br></p><p>Join Rabbi Marc Katz\, of Templ
 e Ner Tamid in Bloomfield\, Reverend Ann Ralosky\, of First Congregational 
 Church in Montclair and Pastor Leslie Houseworth-Fields of St. Mark’s Unite
 d Methodist Church in Montclair for an interfaith discussion on loneliness.
  Clergy will touch on topics including defining loneliness — a very individ
 ual state —&nbsp\; recognizing loneliness in their congregations and ways t
 o help. Today’s Covid crisis only exacerbates a prevalence of loneliness in
  our society now being better understood as a health as well as a spiritual
  and psychological concern. Yet\, faith and religion offer unique perspecti
 ves on tackling isolation and alienation. Join these three faith leaders in
  an exploration on how to find comfort\, alone and together\, in this chall
 enging time.</p><p></p><p>Please click the link below to join the webinar:<
 /p><p><a href="https://zoom.us/j/99291214556"><span>https://zoom.us/j/99291
 214556</span></a></p><p>Details\, registration viewing and participation in
 formation are available at <a href="https://montclairbounce.org/"><span>mon
 tclairbounce.org</span></a>.&nbsp\; The website also features practical res
 ources on crisis needs and mental health support\, as well as on individual
  and family activities that are both playful and meaningful.<br>&nbsp\;<br>
 MONTCLAIR Bounce reflects mental health research on ways we can boost our m
 oods and bolster our resilience. The Festival is a project of <a href="http
 s://toniskitchen.org/"><span>Toni’s Kitchen</span></a>. &nbsp\; Toni’s Kitc
 hen is playing a central role in addressing food insecurity resulting from 
 Covid-19. To support these efforts\, please go to <a href="https://toniskit
 chen.org/"><span>toniskitchen.org</span></a>.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20200420T160228Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Loneliness in the Time of COVID: an Interfaith Conversation
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:First Congregational Church Montclair
X-SOURCE-URL:https://fccmontclair.org/upcoming-events-at-fcc/
DTSTART:20180518T230000Z
DTEND:20180519T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260401T043557Z
UID:1asi37ep96a618gqh0bsd8ect5@google.com
CREATED:20180501T211546Z
DESCRIPTION:<br><p><span>May's book club selection\, <i>Moonglow</i> by Mic
 hael Chabon\, has been called "a wondrous book that celebrates the power of
  family bonds and the&nbsp\;slipperiness of memory . . . A thoroughly encha
 nting story about the circuitous&nbsp\;path that a life follows\, the accid
 ents that redirect it\, and the secrets that can be felt but never seen" (<
 i>Washington Post</i>).&nbsp\;</span> <br></p><p><span>Blurring the lines b
 etween memoir and fiction\, the novel unfolds as the death bed confession o
 f a man the narrator refers to only as "my grandfather." &nbsp\;From the Je
 wish slums of pre-war South Philadelphia\, to the invasion of Germany\,&nbs
 p\;from a Florida retirement village to New York's Wallkill prison\,from th
 e heyday of the space program to the twilight of the "American Century\," t
 he novel revisits an entire era through a single life and collapses a lifet
 ime into a single week.&nbsp\;</span></p><p></p><p><span>FCC Member Mike Ma
 gdalenski is facilitating this group and will be hosting at his home.&nbsp\
 ; We'd like to make it both a literary and socia levening\, so we invite co
 ntributions of light refreshments and beverages as well.&nbsp\; We'll gathe
 r at&nbsp\;<span>7:00</span>&nbsp\;with some social time and begin&nbsp\;<s
 pan>book</span>&nbsp\;discussion at 7:30<span>pm</span>.&nbsp\;</span></p><
 p><span><br>Please contact Mike to RSVP&nbsp\;<u>by Tuesday\, May 15th</u>:
  </span><span><a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https%3A%2F%2Ffirstcong
 montclair.us6.list-manage.com%2Ftrack%2Fclick%3Fu%3D62bf2ca744bdb8b46fa1a77
 88%26id%3De1f7c99029%26e%3D382909cbb3&amp\;sa=D&amp\;usd=2&amp\;usg=AFQjCNE
 DvbfE_weNrr--Udbd4a8yWVs_Lw" target="_blank"><span>michael.magdalenski@gmai
 l.com</span></a></span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20180501T213812Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Next FCC Book Club conversation and refreshments
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
