CREATED:20160607T142624Z
DESCRIPTION:Help Serve Local Homeless Families Through IHN\, June 21\, 23 &
  25\n(at Union Congregational Church)\n\nThe Interfaith Hospitality Network
  (IHN) helps temporarily homeless families in Essex County get back on thei
 r feet. Families stay in local churches and synagogues and have meals\, com
 panionship\, and overnight supervision provided by volunteers from the  con
 gregations as they rebuild their lives. For the past couple of years we hav
 e partnered with Union Congregational Church as they host IHN families in t
 heir church building (176 Cooper Avenue\, Upper Montclair).\n\nThis June we
  are recruiting for volunteers to staff the various shifts through the onli
 ne  sign-up tool. Just go to www.tinyurl.com/IHNjune to see what shifts are
  available\, make your selection and hit "submit."\n\nFCC reserves the Tues
 day\, Thursday\, and Saturday morning slots. You can help with contributing
  a meal\, helping with cleanup from 5:30 to 7:30pm\, children's activities 
 6:30 to 8:30pm and overnight supervision. Contact our IHN Coordinator\, Sar
 ah Feliciano\, at sfeliciano1@gmail.com if you have any questions\, or Jack
  Cuffari at jack@cuffari.com .
LAST-MODIFIED:20160607T145229Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Help serve homeless families through IHN\, June 21\, 23 & 25
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
