UID:cvegdveat0tfdvft1lop8m8dj8@google.com
CREATED:20161011T212458Z
DESCRIPTION:The New Jim Crow ....from Awareness to Action\n\nSomewhere betw
 een the silent protests on the football field and the violence in Ferguson\
 , Baltimore and Dallas\, many people who care about the issues of racism an
 d mass incarceration are voicing their opinions.  Since Michelle Alexander 
 wrote her book\, The New Jim Crow\, over 4 years ago\, conversations about 
 mass incarceration have taken place on a national level.\n\nThe third event
  in the “Still Speaking” Lecture Series will add to the dialogue with this 
 program. It takes place at Union Cong\, 176 Cooper Ave. Montclair\, NJ. Doo
 rs will open at 7:00pm for light refreshments. \n\nThe presenters are two N
 ew Jersey residents\, State Senator Raymond Lesniak and Frank Bolden.  Both
  are very knowledgeable about the issues of racism and mass incarceration.\
 n
LAST-MODIFIED:20161011T212458Z
LOCATION:Union Congregational Church\, 176 Cooper Avenue\, Montclair\, NJ\,
  07043
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Still Speaking Lecture Series (at Union Cong Church)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
