UID:hrubpa22pobhg1697fj47qu8v0@google.com
CREATED:20160531T214040Z
DESCRIPTION:“Be still\, & know that I am God” - A Workshop on the Spiritual
  Practice of Eldering\, Saturday\, June 18\, 9am-2pm\n\nThe Spiritual Pract
 ice of “Eldering” has\, at times\, been described as “holding in prayer”\, 
 “holding in the Light of Christ”\, “spiritual accompaniment”\, “Spiritual c
 ompanionship”\, “Deep\, active listening”\, or “walking between words & sil
 ence”.  At its foundation “Eldering” is grounded in the belief that through
  an inward turning & deep\, silent prayer we may connect with the Divine Pr
 esence\, bringing it forth & holding others in the Light & Love of the Chri
 st. \n\nEldering has been an important part of traditional Quaker practice\
 ; elders are usually present at business meetings\, meetings for healing\, 
 meetings for discernment of critical issues affecting both individuals and 
 the congregation. And\, just as importantly\, this practice has been used b
 y individuals to simply deepen their own spiritual practice.  \n\nAnn Pomer
 oy will be leading the workshop\; Ann is a member of New Paltz Monthly Meet
 ing\, an experienced Elder\, & has introduced many people to the practice o
 f Eldering. \n\nThis workshop is being offered at no cost to participants o
 n Saturday\, June 18\, 2016 starting at 9:00AM to 2:00 PM. Please bring a b
 ag lunch.\n\nIf you should have any questions concerning Eldering or the Wo
 rkshop contact Derek Polzer at pineknotred@yahoo.com  
LAST-MODIFIED:20160531T214040Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:A Workshop on the Spiritual Practice of Eldering
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
