CREATED:20181012T213054Z
DESCRIPTION:In the last 170 years\, over a hundred early Christians texts h
 ave emerged from the sands of Egypt\, middle-eastern markets\, and the back
  shelves of scholars’ libraries. For the first time\, scholars and congrega
 tions have been able to translate and read texts like the Gospel of Thomas 
 and the Gospel of Mary\, which have previously either been lost or dismisse
 d.\n\nWith such diversity of material\, these scriptures are water for the 
 spiritually thirsty and enticing clues for anyone wondering about Christian
 ity before it became the official religion of the Roman Empire. Come join u
 s on this journey of discovery! 
LAST-MODIFIED:20181012T213054Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Continue Our Discovery of Lost Scriptures! October 17th & 24th\, 7:
 30 pm -Guild Room
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
