DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20210908T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20210908T130000
RRULE:FREQ=WEEKLY;WKST=SU;UNTIL=20211103T035959Z
DTSTAMP:20260401T043557Z
UID:ob0n87or6r3jmdsrdicf35np8r_R20210908T150000@google.com
CREATED:20210714T163746Z
DESCRIPTION:<span>Weekly: Wednesdays 11am-1pm in the Sanctuary</span><span>
  (beginning September 8)</span><br><span>AND <u>&nbsp\;</u></span><br><span
 ><u>FIRST Saturday </u>of each month: 11am-1pm (beginning November 6)</span
 ><br><span>&nbsp\;</span><i> </i><p></p><p><span>Take your soul for a walk 
 on the labyrinth.&nbsp\; We are pleased to offer labyrinth walks each Wedne
 sday in the mid-day as a chance to connect with your soul in our beautiful 
 sanctuary.&nbsp\;<br><br><b>Social distancing will be observed with one wal
 ker at a time on the labyrinth and specially designated pews for prayer and
  meditation. We look forward to welcoming you back.</b></span> <br></p><p><
 span>The labyrinth is an ancient spiritual tool \, a mode of “walking praye
 r” that invites us to go deeper in our walk with God.&nbsp\; Our labyrinth\
 , modeled on one in Chartes Cathedral in France\, sits as the center of our
  Sanctuary\, a constant metaphor for our spiritual lives.&nbsp\; Just like 
 the labyrinth\, our lives are not linear\, but filled with twists and turns
 .&nbsp\; Sometimes we make great progress\, and other times we feel we are 
 going backwards.&nbsp\; But if we trust in the path we will find ourselves 
 in the center -- the heart of God.</span> <br></p><p><span>All are welcome 
 to take their souls out for a healing walk... no experience necessary!&nbsp
 \;</span> <a href="https://baristanet.com/2014/03/labyrinth-walk-meditation
 -satisfies-soul/"><span>Check out this lovely write up on Baristanet</span>
 </a> <span>from the Spring 2014.</span> <br></p><p><a href="https://www.you
 tube.com/watch?time_continue=2&v=D453ajtWb74&feature=emb_logo"><span>Watch 
 this video</span></a> <span>to find out more about walking the labyrinth. I
 f you’ve never done so come out one Wednesday evening and give it a try. It
  is a wonderful way to nourish your soul and spend some quiet time in praye
 r or meditation.</span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20211104T214624Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Weekly Labyrinth Walks\, Wednesdays 11am-1pm AND FIRST Saturday of 
 each month (same time)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
