CREATED:20220127T225821Z
DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><u></u><p><span><i>&nbsp\;</i><u><b>Fo
 ur Wednesday Evening Sessions in February 7:30pm to 9 pm:</b></u> </span></
 p><p><b><span><span><u>New</u> Zoom Link for February 9th session: </span><
 /span></b><a href="https://us02web.zoom.us/j/82193599950?pwd=TVNxUTNFS1dwb1
 luTWl3N0E1LzdyZz09#success" id="ow413" __is_owner="true"><b><span><u><span>
 Click Here</span></u></span></b></a><br><b><span>Password: <strong><span>88
 9407</span></strong>&nbsp\; </span></b><span><i>&nbsp\;</i></span></p><p><s
 pan><i>Our first three sessions will take place over Zoom. For our last cla
 ss\, we will gather in the FCC Guild Room and also provide a virtual option
 .</i></span></p><span>February 2nd - on Zoom (led by Rev. Dr. Taussig)<br>&
 nbsp\;February 9th - on Zoom (led by Rev. Dr. Taussig)<br>February 16th - o
 n Zoom (led by Rev. Dr. Spencer-Miller)<br>February 23rd -<b> </b>in-person
  and virtual (led by Rev. John)</span><p><span><b>We encourage you to pick 
 up a copy of <i>After Jesus\, Before Christianity:</i></b></span><b><i> </i
 ></b><u><b><a href="https://www.harpercollins.com/products/after-jesus-befo
 re-christianity-erin-vearncombebrandon-scotthal-taussig?variant=33097760636
 962"><span>Please click here</span></a></b></u><span>. Although reading the
  text is recommended\, it is not required. </span></p><p><span><i>If you'd 
 like any assistance paying for the book\,&nbsp\; please let us know. FCC re
 ceived a generous anonymous donation from a member to help cover the cost o
 f books for folks who need it.</i></span></p><p><br><span><u>Course Write-U
 p: </u></span></p><p><span>What do we really know about how Christianity to
 ok shape? Do the rituals\, practices\, and beliefs common today look anythi
 ng like those of the earliest Christians? How did the earliest followers of
  Jesus navigate the changing world around them\, build greater spiritual fo
 rtitude\, and create a movement that has deeply impacted the world?<br>&nbs
 p\;<br>Highlighting the many archeological and manuscript discoveries over 
 the past twenty years\, After Jesus\, Before Christianity offers new insigh
 ts that provide a paradigm-shifting picture.<br>&nbsp\;<br>Each Wednesday i
 n February\, our FCC community will explore the diversity\, creativity\, an
 d spirituality of the earliest followers of Jesus. Three scholars and minis
 ters will help lead us on this journey<b>.</b>The first is <b>Rev. Dr. Hal 
 Taussig\,</b> former Professor of New Testament at Union Theological Semina
 ry and one of the authors of After Jesus\, Before Christianity. One session
  will be led by our own <b>Rev. Dr. Althea Spencer Miller</b>\, Assistant P
 rofessor of New Testament at Drew Theological Seminary. And\, finally\, hel
 ping to guide the conversation each week\, will be <b>Rev. John Rogers</b>\
 , FCC’s Lead Pastor of Spiritual Formation and Community Development.</span
 ></p><p><br><span><b>If you have any questions please email Rev. John at&nb
 sp\; </b></span><a href="mailto:john.rogers28@gmail.com"><span>john.rogers2
 8@gmail.com</span></a><span>.</span></p><p><span>We hope you join us for th
 is paradigm-shifting and spiritually enriching journey into the life and pr
 actices of the early church!</span></p><u></u><u></u><u></u></html-blob>
LAST-MODIFIED:20220208T213441Z
