DESCRIPTION:Every year\, Muslims around the globe observe the holy month of
  Ramadan.\,  a time for reflection\, devotion to God\, and self-control. Du
 ring the month of Ramadan\, Muslims show their devotion by fasting\, or abs
 taining from food during the day. Each evening at sunset they break the fas
 t with a special meal called “iftar.”  It is a time of great hospitality an
 d celebration. \n\nThis year our friends of Peace Islands will be sharing a
 n “iftar” supper with us here at FCC!   We’ll learn about the tradition\, s
 hare in delicious Turkish food and deepen our friendship.  An email sign-up
  will be sent out soon.  Questions?  See Rev. Ann.
LAST-MODIFIED:20160531T213520Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Celebrate Ramadan with our Muslim friends from  Peace Islands Insti
 tute (at FCC)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
