UID:sqbs40svcf6fjopqbjjmbj1s4k@google.com
CREATED:20160914T162549Z
DESCRIPTION:SEPTEMBER 28 MESSY CHURCH\n(Will be led by our Youth Group!)\n\
 nThis summer\, the Youth Group had the opportunity to visit Heifer Farm\, l
 ocated in Rutland\, MA.  Through caring for the animals and participating i
 n simulations\, they learned about Heifer’s efforts to end hunger and pover
 ty and how to live more sustainable lives.\n\nIn this upcoming Messy Church
 \, they will share a traditional Ghanaian dish they made on the trip (child
 ren’s options are available)\, show a slideshow capturing their experience\
 , teach about Heifer’s message\, and run a game called “Survive\,” which si
 mulates the need and struggle for food\, money and business acumen in Globa
 l South nations.  For those who do not wish to play the game\, there will b
 e a craft station run by Youth Group members. The Youth Group is so excited
  to share their experience\n\n(To offset meal costs\, we are requesting a s
 uggested donation of $5 per person\, max of $20 per family.)\n\n___________
 ____________________\n\nMessy Church is an informal and unstructured (“mess
 y”) evening each month that brings our community together mid-week for a si
 mple dinner\, an opportunity to work together to create a stronger communit
 y within and out-side our church walls\, or simply just be.\nWe will provid
 e dinner\, a brief and informal worship experience\, and either an activity
  or an opportunity to serve our community. You come and go as you like\, pa
 rticipating in whatever way you see fit. This is a great way to offer frien
 dship and share in God’s love in a fun\, informal way. So take a break from
  the mid-week stress\, and recharge yourself with us!\n\n(To offset meal co
 sts\, we are requesting a suggested donation of $5 per person\, max of $20 
 per family.)
LAST-MODIFIED:20160914T163406Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Messy Church returns!  6-8pm in the Guild Room.
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
