RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20191222T103000
CREATED:20110321T135654Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><span>A SPECIAL MUSICAL CHRISTMAS GIFT ! Sunday Worship\, De
 cember 22\, 10:30am</span> <br></p><p><span>During our fourth Sunday of Adv
 ent&nbsp\; we will have very special music provided by our exceptional choi
 r and&nbsp\; special guest instrumentalists The combined forces will presen
 t a bright\, magnificent work by the composer John Rutter\, entitled </span
 ><span>Gloria. </span><span>&nbsp\;&nbsp\;The text is one of the most tradi
 tional expressions of praise\, often heard at Christmas time\, beginning wi
 th </span><span>Glory to God in the highest\, and on earth peace to people 
 of good will.</span></p><p><span>Rutter’s setting of the text is divided in
 to three movements: exalted\, devotional and jubilant by turns.&nbsp\; The 
 accompaniment is for brass ensemble with timpani\, percussion and organ — a
  combination\, which issued softly and introspectively in the middle moveme
 nt and in the outer movements\, makes quite a joyful noise unto the Lord!</
 span></p><p><span>For the morning’s “sermon in song”\, Rev. John Rogers wil
 l be interweaving the </span><span>Gloria </span><span>text with that of th
 e Gospel of Matthew’s story of Joseph’s dream which is the gospel reading f
 or the day.&nbsp\; When looking at the two highlighted texts together\, new
  insights\, and perhaps even a new perspective on each\, will be achieved\,
  enhancing our celebration of the season.</span></p><p><i><span>This specia
 l morning of music is made possible by a generous gift from the Monsees Fou
 ndation.&nbsp\; </span></i></p><p>&nbsp\;</p><p>&nbsp\;</p><p>&nbsp\;</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20200503T045201Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Sunday Worship Service\, Special Christmas Music!
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
