CREATED:20190521T202250Z
DESCRIPTION:<br>MONTCLAIR BOUNCE! - A festival of Optimism and Resilience!&
 nbsp\; A playful\, town-wide exploration of ways to brighten our days and s
 trengthen our spirits.<br><br>This class is for Women 18 &amp\; up\, please
  bring a yoga mat &amp\; bath towel. There is no cost to attend this event 
 but <b>you must register by contacting facilitator\, Donna Dimino\, </b>at 
 <a href="mailto:knowbodyawareness@yahoo.com" target="_blank">knowbodyawaren
 ess@yahoo.com</a>&nbsp\; .&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;
 &nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp
 \;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nb
 sp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\; <br>Space is limited to the first 15 women who re
 gister\, so if your plans change kindly let Donna know. <br><br>Qoya is bas
 ed on the idea through movement\; we remember our essence is wise\, wild an
 d free.Wise - Calling on the wisdom of yoga<br>Wild - Evoking our creativit
 y and authentic expression through dance<br>Free - Expanding our capacity t
 o actually feel good in our body<br><br>Through movement\, we remember thos
 e things that can never be put into words.<br><br>In Qoya movement\, there 
 is no way you can do it wrong and the way you know you are doing it right i
 s that it feels good to you\, it feels true. Qoya is designed to help you r
 emember the physical sensation of truth in your body and reclaim your inner
  knowing\, intuition and instincts so that you let that feeling be north on
  your compass &amp\; let your body guide you on your soul's journey.<br><br
 ><u><b>About Donna</b></u><br>Donna Dimino became a Certified Qoya teacher 
 in 2017\, but has been facilitating classes\, workshops and private session
  work since 2004 when she founded ‘Living’ Body Awareness Programs.. Using 
 an intuitive sense\, Donna works with listening to the language of the body
  to look more deeply as to what is needed for each experience. She believes
  that our bodies can act as a map to guide us back to ourselves allowing us
  to make choices in alignment with who we truly are &amp\; what we truly wa
 nt to create in our lives and in our world.<br><br>Donna’s training and stu
 dy in Dance\, Body Alignment\, Tai Chi\, Qi Gong\, Yoga\, Energy Work\, Spi
 rituality\, Mysticism\, Sound Healing\, Empowerment Coaching\, Theatre\, Es
 sential Oils\, Body Centered Meditation &amp\; her greatest teacher\, Natur
 e. She has shared her work with people ages 12 thru 95\, facilitating custo
 mized programs for College Nursing &amp\; Employee Assistance Programs\, Th
 e NY Foundling\, Expectant Mothers\, Dentists\, Social Workers\, Business o
 wners\, Lawyers\, Wellness Programs for Teachers\, Caregivers\, The Prison 
 Population\, High School Students\, Senior Communities\, Massage Therapists
 \, Staff Wellness Days\, Retreats and Conferences. <br>&nbsp\;
LAST-MODIFIED:20190521T210702Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:"Montclair Bounce Week" event: Qoya Movement Class for Women - led 
 by our own Donna Dimino!
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
