CREATED:20190903T175958Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><span>The Acts of the Apostles</span> <br></p><p><span>Start
 ing on&nbsp\; November 4th\, our Slow&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\; Motion Adult Bib
 le Study will start digging into the Acts of the Apostles. Written by the a
 uthor(s) of the Gospel of Luke\, the Acts of the Apostles is&nbsp\;a dynami
 c book that pays attention to leadership and conflict issues\, the use of w
 ealth and possessions\, the role of women in the church\, the relationship 
 between the church and the state and Christians and civil authorities\, and
  the challenge of persecution. <br></span></p><p><span>Join us for a fascin
 ating journey into this wonderful work. Feel free to come and jump right in
 . Bring your favorite translation / paraphrase of the Bible\, and join us!<
 /span><br></p><br><i>Rev. Jack Cuffari is a member of FCC\, as well as our 
 Spiritual Director in Residence. He currently serves as Interim Pastor at t
 he First Congregational United Church of Christ in Haworth\, NJ. </i>
