CREATED:20180305T200826Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>We will celebrate<span>&nbsp\;</span>Jesus’ last supper with
  his friends in a special worship service with foot washing and Holy<span>&
 nbsp\; </span>Communion in the<span> </span>Sanctuary.</p><p align="center"
 >&nbsp\;<b><span>What is foot washing (and why?)</span></b><span> <br></spa
 n></p><p><span>When Jesus invited his friends to join him for the Passover 
 meal (which became his last supper)\, he began the night by doing something
  very unexpected: he washed their feet.<span>&nbsp\; </span>This was an act
  of profound humility and service.<span>&nbsp\; </span>That one act said mo
 re than any sermon. On Maundy Thursday (Holy Thursday) we model that kind o
 f servanthood by washing one another’s feet. <br></span></p><p><b><span>The
  ritual is entirely voluntary</span></b><span>.<span>&nbsp\; </span>All are
  welcome\, but only if you feel moved should<span>&nbsp\;</span>you partici
 pate.<span>&nbsp\; </span>There will be four stations with a chair\, a basi
 n\, a pitcher and towels up front in the Sanctuary. Folks will form two lin
 es down the center aisle (like Communion) — remove shoes and socks before y
 ou get in line!<span>&nbsp\;</span>Instructions will be given during the se
 rvice to explain the procedure.<span>&nbsp\; </span>You will have a chance 
 to both have your feet washed and wash another’s feet.<span>&nbsp\; </span>
 Water in the basin is changed frequently and there are fresh towels for eac
 h person. <br></span></p><p><span>This experience can be moving\, disconcer
 ting and humbling all at once — and it’s supposed to be!<span>&nbsp\; </spa
 n>Showing service and compassion in this way is out of many of our comfort 
 zones.<span>&nbsp\; </span>But Holy Week invites us to find the blessing in
  the unexpected as we grow closer to God.<span>&nbsp\; </span></span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20180305T201306Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Maundy Thursday Service of  foot washing and Holy  Communion\, 8pm
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
