CREATED:20161205T182313Z
DESCRIPTION:Longest Night Service\, 8pm on December 21 \n\nChristmas is a t
 ime of joy and celebration.  Yet for many of us the holiday season brings a
  sense of sadness and grief as well.  Separation from loved ones through di
 stance or death\, personal illness\, loneliness\, or financial stress can m
 ake this “season of light” a time of darkness.\n\nOn Wednesday\, December 2
 1\, we will offer a special service to acknowledge the difficult emotions o
 f the season and offer a place for blessing and reconciliation.  There will
  be a contemplative service of readings and music\, a time to pray individu
 ally with our pastors\, receive an anointing with oil\, and an opportunity 
 to walk the labyrinth.  All are welcome to find comfort and hope.\n
