UID:6hdbsjb8cu2cm9oh1eblhcflh4@google.com
CREATED:20150427T161250Z
DESCRIPTION:With our congregation growing\, how do we maintain the wonderfu
 l hospitality that welcomed so many of us to FCC? How do we move from “gues
 t” to “host”? Did your “shepherd” make you feel a part of the church? How c
 an we be more welcoming ushers or coffee hosts?\nAs part of our sabbatical 
 grant\, we are hosting a consultant from the former Alban Institute to help
  us explore this issue. The Rev. John Wimberly was Senior Minister for 30 y
 ears at Western Presbyterian Church in Washington DC. Under his leadership 
 the church grew dramatically in numbers and diversity. \nRev. Wimberly’s sp
 ecial expertise is in incorporating hospitality into congregational life an
 d he has helped dozens of churches just like ours. We have lots of question
 s and we hope to hear great answers!\nAt this workshop we are especially ho
 ping to hear from folks who have joined FCC in the past 2 years: what was y
 our experience of being welcomed to FCC? What worked and what didn’t when y
 ou joined? Please RSVP by calling the church office.  Lunch will be served.
LAST-MODIFIED:20150508T143226Z
LOCATION:First Congregational Church\, So.Fullerton Avenue\, Montclair\, NJ
 \, 07042
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Retreat event with John Wimberly (12-5pm) - PLEASE RSVP!  (Lunch wi
 ll be served)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:First Congregational Church Montclair
X-SOURCE-URL:https://fccmontclair.org/upcoming-events-at-fcc/
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20200513T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20200513T200000
DTSTAMP:20260401T043557Z
UID:7sr8vjp9d8pe9q4fjkatnvtjcm@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20200513T190000
CREATED:20200503T051412Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>What does it mean to be a "progressive" Christian?&nbsp\; Ho
 w do we take the Bible "seriously but not literally?"&nbsp\; What does it m
 ean&nbsp\;to live our faith in this era of change and uncertainty?&nbsp\;Ma
 ny folks who find our church are drawn to our open\, inclusive\, and heart 
 felt experience of Christianity\, but are unfamiliar with the theology behi
 nd it.&nbsp\; For three Wednesday evenings in May\, Rev. Ann and Rev. John 
 will host an online discussion to engage us in the deepest questions of fol
 lowing Jesus in the 21st century.&nbsp\; We will be using a book by one of 
 our most beloved spiritual teachers\, the late Marcus Borg\, entitled The H
 eart of Christianity.&nbsp\;<br><br>Each week we will engage in conversatio
 n about our understanding of scripture\, how we encounter Jesus' teachings 
 on justice\, salvation and rebirth\, and how we embrace the blessings of al
 l religious traditions while honoring Christianity as our core faith.&nbsp\
 ;</p><p>If you'd like to participate\, please RSVP to Rev. Ann at <a href="
 mailto:acralosky@msn.com"><span>acralosky@msn.com</span></a>.<br>ORDER THE 
 BOOK: You will need to order the book and it is available on most online bo
 okstores.&nbsp\; <a href="https://firstcongmontclair.us6.list-manage.com/tr
 ack/click?u=62bf2ca744bdb8b46fa1a7788&id=e1ba6a41c3&e=d2d6ac503b"><span>Her
 e is a link to buy an inexpensive used copy</span></a>. <br></p><p><a href=
 "https://us02web.zoom.us/j/89864428536?pwd=c3FaMlZ3akpTNVBxQXJWNXhWQTJVQT09
 " id="ow648" __is_owner="true"><u><b><span>CLICK HERE</span></b></u></a> to
  join us on Zoom at 7pm and enter the password: <b>586012</b>&nbsp\;<i> (We
 'll be reading the first two chapters for the first session.)&nbsp\; <br></
 i></p><p><i></i><u>DOWNLOAD ZOOM:</u> We will be using Zoom technology for 
 this class\, so be sure you have downloaded Zoom.&nbsp\; If you need help w
 ith this\, <a href="https://firstcongmontclair.us6.list-manage.com/track/cl
 ick?u=62bf2ca744bdb8b46fa1a7788&id=fc1d12314a&e=d2d6ac503b"><span>here is a
  video to get you started.</span></a></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20200512T205859Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Adult Study: An Exploration Into The Heart of Christianity\, Wednes
 days May 13\, 20\, 27 at 7pm
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
