UID:37c52dijpboropurfg703vua8c@google.com
CREATED:20230405T141046Z
DESCRIPTION:<b><span>Join us for an animated discussion about ideas in Jame
 s Bridle’s book\, </span></b><i><b><u><span>Ways of Being\,</span></u></b><
 /i><b><span> 7 pm on Wednesday\, May10 at FCC Montclair. </span></b><b><spa
 n> <br></span></b><p><b><u><span>Ways of Being</span></u></b><span> expands
  humans’ frame of reference regarding life - to include ALL life on the pla
 net - plants\,animals\, and technology.  Through a survey of these non-huma
 n lifeforms we begin to see that humans are not omniscient. The intelligenc
 e of plants\, animals and microorganisms (including viruses) has been chang
 ing and evolving over 700million years (and more for the microorganisms).  
 Bridle is out to change our human-centric view and begin the process of liv
 ing with the world\, rather than trying to dominate it.  The non-human worl
 d is strange to us\, yet there is much to learn from it.</span></p><p><span
 >Bridle includes technology in its relationship to all life on this planet 
 - through material.  What ideas are our technological society based on? How
  would you change the parameters for AI? <i><span>For now </span></i>techno
 logy is in our hands and we still have capability to repair\, restore and r
 e-introduce its entanglement with the world. </span></p><p><span>For more i
 nformation and commentary\, check out Bridle’s website  <a href="https://fi
 rstcongmontclair.us6.list-manage.com/track/click?u=62bf2ca744bdb8b46fa1a778
 8&id=87ee7d7a72&e=d2d6ac503b"><span>https://jamesbridle.com/books/ways-of-b
 eing</span></a>.</span><span><br><br></span><b><span>The book discussion wi
 ll be led by Joanne Kornoelje on May 10\, 7 pm\, at First Congregational Ch
 urch in Montclair.</span></b><span> Reading the book prior to the session i
 s not necessary\, but <i><span>is recommended</span></i>.  You can order it
  from the library (</span><span><a href="https://firstcongmontclair.us6.lis
 t-manage.com/track/click?u=62bf2ca744bdb8b46fa1a7788&id=08d7a1ed8a&e=d2d6ac
 503b"><span>https://montclairlibrary.org/</span></a></span><span>)\, or pur
 chase it from your friendly local bookseller  (</span><span><a href="https:
 //firstcongmontclair.us6.list-manage.com/track/click?u=62bf2ca744bdb8b46fa1
 a7788&id=280ffb7d0e&e=d2d6ac503b"><span>https://www.watchungbooksellers.com
 /</span></a></span><span>)</span></p><span>Come with an open mind and a wil
 lingness to ask\, listen and consider. <br>Hope to see you there!</span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230509T204420Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Book Discussion "Ways of Being\," 7 pm in the FCC Sanctuary
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
