CREATED:20160111T172226Z
DESCRIPTION:SpiritQuest: Exploring Our Theological Worlds\n\nWednesday Eves
  Faith Exploration Class @ 7:30pm\nJanuary 13-February 17 at FCC\n \nHow we
  come to experience God is the result of our theological worldview -- that 
 constellation of beliefs\, assumptions\, and realities that shape our spiri
 tual selves.  The impact of that worldview is huge\, but rarely do we explo
 re its origins or effect on our faith. Based on the work of  W. Paul Jones\
 , this series will engage us in the spiritual quest which calls to the   in
 ner rhythm of our souls. Is our journey more that of the Warrior or of the 
 Refugee? It might be we feel ourselves to be an Alien in life or possibly a
 n Outcast\, even from ourselves. Still our quest may be more as a Fugitive 
 caught in the duplicity of human existence.\n \nIn this five week experienc
 e we will explore the conundrum which sets us on our quest\, the possible r
 esolution which leads to “success” of the quest\, and resources to aid us o
 n our journey. We will begin with a survey to help identify which quest eac
 h of us is on. During our time we will      encounter Shakespeare\, Broadwa
 y Musicals\, and Pop Culture as well as more traditional faith guides for o
 ur quest.\n \nThe workshop will be held IN THE FCC LIBRARY on Wednesdays\, 
 \nJanuary 13 - February 17 (DARK FOR ASH WEDNESDAY\, FEB. 10). \n\nThe Rev.
  David K. Popham will be our facilitator. David is a member of First Congre
 gational Church as well as an Associate Conference Minister with the Centra
 l Atlantic Conference.\n \nFor more information you can talk with Rev. Ann 
 or David (973-558-0620)\, and check out information at http://theologicalwo
 rlds.weebly.com.\n 
LAST-MODIFIED:20160111T172226Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Wednesday Eves Faith Exploration Class @ 7:30pm (5 Wednesdays)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
