DESCRIPTION:<br>Join our FCC family as we walk to ensure LGBTQ rights!  Thi
 s year our church will be the site of the annual GSE Equality walk!  We'll 
 begin right after worship on the front lawn\, enjoy music\, refreshments an
 d some inspirational speakers and then take to the streets of Montclair.<br
 ><br>Equality Walk is Garden State Equality’s largest annual community fund
 raiser. Last year\, there were hundreds of individuals in attendance and th
 ousands of dollars was raised. This year\, to under score the fact that the
 y are a statewide organization with an unwavering commitment to all of NJ\,
  they will be hosting an Equality Walk Weekend and holding a total of three
  separate walks\, representing the three geographical regions of our great 
 state: north\, central\, and south. <br><br><b>FCC is the location for the 
 Northern NJ Walk!</b><br><br>Funds raised at Equality Walk 2018 will suppor
 t the innovative work GSE is doing in the areas of policy\, education\, and
  health. Every day\, their team is busy advocating for the LGBT community i
 n our state and offering programs that can serve as models for other states
 \, agencies\, and organizations. <br><br><b>A sign up table will be availab
 le during coffee hours.&nbsp\;</b> Our FCC coordinators are Michele Velez\,
  Armee Grace Campos\, Carlo Bodiongan and Lauren Goodwyn.&nbsp\;
LAST-MODIFIED:20180907T160049Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Garden State Equality March - after worship
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
