DESCRIPTION:WHAT??  We’re planning to have an intentionally messy church at
  FCC??  Yes!  \n“Messy Church” is an informal and unstructured (“messy”) ev
 ening of dinner/play/worship/fellowship that brings the church community to
 gether mid-week.  On the fourth Wednesday of each month\, from 5:45-8:30pm 
 (beginning in the Guild Room)\, we plan to provide an evening at church whe
 re FCC’s family and friends can come for fellowship\, fun\, a simple dinner
 \, and opportunities to sit together and talk\, or study\, or play games or
  sports\, or be creative\, or work\, or simply just be\, as they like\, eit
 her alone or with others.  We will provide dinner and several study/discuss
 ion group/creative offerings\, as well as a very brief and informal worship
  experience.  Participants come and go as they like\, participating in what
 ever way they see fit – but knowing that we’ll be there one Wednesday every
  month to offer friendship and share in God’s love in an unstructured\, fun
 \, informal\, family-oriented way.  Child care for age 3 and younger will b
 e provided.  
LAST-MODIFIED:20151014T153352Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Messy Church! 5:45-8:00pm (every 4th Wednesday of the month)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
