DESCRIPTION:On Thursday\, April 13 we will be joining with folks from Bnai 
 Keshet and the Baitul Wahid Mosque for a day of work and fellowship at a Ha
 bitat work site in Paterson\, NJ.  In past years we have worked on insulati
 on\, siding\, general carpentry\, painting and landscaping.  All ages (Habi
 tat requires volunteers to be at least 16 years of age) and skill levels ar
 e welcome.  We will meet at B'nai Keshet (99 S Fullerton) at 7:45am to carp
 ool to the worksite and will be returning mid-afternoon.  \n\nFor our congr
 egation it is Maundy Thursday and a wonderful chance to begin the Easter Ob
 servance with our interfaith brothers and sisters.  If you are interested i
 n joining us for a day of work and fun\, please contact Dick Thomas at rtho
 mas14@comcast.net  as we would like to have a rough count for planning purp
 oses.
