UID:05v0ds8u3nmvlupag1cj3lqloa_R20210310T160000@google.com
CREATED:20200828T215625Z
DESCRIPTION:<span>Weekly: Wednesdays 11am-1pm in the Sanctuary</span><span>
 &nbsp\;</span><br><span>AND <u>&nbsp\;</u></span><br><span><u>FIRST Saturda
 y </u>of each month: 11am-1pm</span><i> </i><p><b><span>(There will be no l
 abyrinth walk during the&nbsp\; month of August)</span></b><br></p><p><span
 >Take your soul for a walk on the labyrinth.&nbsp\; We are pleased to offer
  labyrinth walks each Wednesday in the mid-day as a chance to connect with 
 your soul in our beautiful sanctuary.&nbsp\;<br><br><b>Social distancing wi
 ll be observed with one walker at a time on the labyrinth and specially des
 ignated pews for prayer and meditation. We look forward to welcoming you ba
 ck.</b></span> <br></p><p><span>The labyrinth is an ancient spiritual tool 
 \, a mode of “walking prayer” that invites us to go deeper in our walk with
  God.&nbsp\; Our labyrinth\, modeled on one in Chartes Cathedral in France\
 , sits as the center of our Sanctuary\, a constant metaphor for our spiritu
 al lives.&nbsp\; Just like the labyrinth\, our lives are not linear\, but f
 illed with twists and turns.&nbsp\; Sometimes we make great progress\, and 
 other times we feel we are going backwards.&nbsp\; But if we trust in the p
 ath we will find ourselves in the center -- the heart of God.</span> <br></
 p><p><span>All are welcome to take their souls out for a healing walk... no
  experience necessary!&nbsp\;</span> <a href="https://baristanet.com/2014/0
 3/labyrinth-walk-meditation-satisfies-soul/"><span>Check out this lovely wr
 ite up on Baristanet</span></a> <span>from the Spring 2014.</span> <br></p>
 <p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=2&v=D453ajtWb74&fea
 ture=emb_logo"><span>Watch this video</span></a> <span>to find out more abo
 ut walking the labyrinth. If you’ve never done so come out one Wednesday ev
 ening and give it a try. It is a wonderful way to nourish your soul and spe
 nd some quiet time in prayer or meditation.</span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20210714T162918Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Weekly Labyrinth Walks\, Wednesdays 11am-1pm & and FIRST Saturday o
 f each month (same time)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
