UID:7uihl9aoe26214138qj5t5lor5@google.com
CREATED:20200807T165728Z
DESCRIPTION:<br><strong><span>Join us (via Zoom) Thursday\, August 27th at 
 7:00pm for our next FCC&nbsp\;Book&nbsp\;Club&nbsp\;conversation</span></st
 rong><br><strong>Our next book club selection is "The Vanishing Half" by Br
 it Bennett.</strong>The Vignes twin sisters will always be identical. But a
 fter growing up together in a small\, southern black community and running 
 away at age sixteen\, it's not just the shape of their daily lives that is 
 different as adults\, it's everything: their families\, their communities\,
  their racial identities. Ten years later\, one sister lives with her black
  daughter in the same southern town she once tried to escape. The other sec
 retly passes for white\, and her white husband knows nothing of her past. S
 till\, even separated by so many miles and just as many lies\, the fates of
  the twins remain intertwined. What will happen to the next generation\, wh
 en their own daughters' storylines intersect?<br><p><strong>Michael Magdale
 nski\, is stepping down as facilitator and August 27th will mark Julie Matz
 -Rees’s debut in his stead. &nbsp\; </strong>Mike founded the Book Club bac
 k in November of 2017 and it is hard to imagine FCC without it! Whether gat
 hering around his living room\, or in respective ZOOM boxes\, Mike brought 
 titles to readers they might not have found on their own\, and led rich and
  thoughtful discussions that often ran over our meeting time.&nbsp\; Mike h
 as agreed to fill in as facilitator if needed so this is hardly goodbye!&nb
 sp\;<br><br>Instructions will be sent out in advance to those who RSVP as t
 o how to easily download Zoom.<span><strong>Please contact Julie to RSVP by
  Monday\, August 23rd: </strong></span><span><strong><a href="mailto:juliem
 arie.matz@gmail.com" id="ow717" __is_owner="true">juliemarie.matz@gmail.com
 </a></strong></span><br></p><p><br></p><br>&nbsp\;
LAST-MODIFIED:20200807T165728Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Book Club Zoom  - August 27\, 7pm
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
