UID:5u7sjb8sftht4lji3kb9j472s8@google.com
CREATED:20220127T225821Z
DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><p><span><i>&nbsp\;</i><u><b>Four Wedn
 esday Evening Sessions in February 7:30pm to 9 pm:</b></u> </span></p><u></
 u><u></u><p><b><span><span>Zoom Link: </span></span></b><a href="https://us
 02web.zoom.us/j/82179097321?pwd=YTVINFE5ZE9wYjQ1UDVubldIeDR5UT09#success"><
 b><span><u><span>Click Here</span></u></span></b></a><br><b><span>Password:
  292263<br>Meeting ID:&nbsp\;821 7909 7321</span></b><br></p><u></u><u></u>
 <p><span><i>Our first three sessions will take place over Zoom. For our las
 t class\, we will gather in the FCC Guild Room and also provide a virtual o
 ption.</i></span></p><span>February 2nd - on Zoom (led by Rev. Dr. Taussig)
 <br>&nbsp\;February 9th - on Zoom (led by Rev. Dr. Taussig)<br>February 16t
 h - on Zoom (led by Rev. Dr. Spencer-Miller)<br>February 23rd -<b> </b>in-p
 erson and virtual (led by Rev. John)</span><p><span><b>We encourage you to 
 pick up a copy of <i>After Jesus\, Before Christianity:</i></b></span><b><i
 > </i></b><u><b><a href="https://www.harpercollins.com/products/after-jesus
 -before-christianity-erin-vearncombebrandon-scotthal-taussig?variant=330977
 60636962"><span>Please click here</span></a></b></u><span>. Although readin
 g the text is recommended\, it is not required. </span></p><p><span><i>If y
 ou'd like any assistance paying for the book\,&nbsp\; please let us know. F
 CC received a generous anonymous donation from a member to help cover the c
 ost of books for folks who need it.</i></span></p><p><br><span><u>Course Wr
 ite-Up: </u></span></p><p><span>What do we really know about how Christiani
 ty took shape? Do the rituals\, practices\, and beliefs common today look a
 nything like those of the earliest Christians? How did the earliest followe
 rs of Jesus navigate the changing world around them\, build greater spiritu
 al fortitude\, and create a movement that has deeply impacted the world?<br
 >&nbsp\;<br>Highlighting the many archeological and manuscript discoveries 
 over the past twenty years\, After Jesus\, Before Christianity offers new i
 nsights that provide a paradigm-shifting picture.<br>&nbsp\;<br>Each Wednes
 day in February\, our FCC community will explore the diversity\, creativity
 \, and spirituality of the earliest followers of Jesus. Three scholars and 
 ministers will help lead us on this journey<b>.</b>The first is <b>Rev. Dr.
  Hal Taussig\,</b> former Professor of New Testament at Union Theological S
 eminary and one of the authors of After Jesus\, Before Christianity. One se
 ssion will be led by our own <b>Rev. Dr. Althea Spencer Miller</b>\, Assist
 ant Professor of New Testament at Drew Theological Seminary. And\, finally\
 , helping to guide the conversation each week\, will be <b>Rev. John Rogers
 </b>\, FCC’s Lead Pastor of Spiritual Formation and Community Development.<
 /span></p><p><br><span><b>If you have any questions please email Rev. John 
 at&nbsp\; </b></span><a href="mailto:john.rogers28@gmail.com"><span>john.ro
 gers28@gmail.com</span></a><span>.</span></p><p><span>We hope you join us f
 or this paradigm-shifting and spiritually enriching journey into the life a
 nd practices of the early church!</span></p><u></u><u></u></html-blob>
LAST-MODIFIED:20220208T213546Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:After Jesus\, Before Christianity A New Study Of Our Spiritual Root
 s: 4 Wednesdays Evenings  Starting 2/2 at 7:30 pm
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
