DESCRIPTION:Christmas is a time of joy and celebration. Yet for many of us 
 the holiday season brings a sense of sadness and grief as well. Separation 
 from loved ones through distance or death\, personal illness\, loneliness\,
  or financial stress can make this “season of light” a time of darkness. On
  Sunday\, December 21\, we will offer a special service to acknowledge the 
 difficult emotions of the season and offer a place for blessing and reconci
 liation.  There will be a contemplative service of readings and music\, a t
 ime to pray individually with our pastors\, receive an anointing with oil\,
  and an opportunity to walk the labyrinth. All are welcome to find comfort 
 and hope.
LAST-MODIFIED:20141203T172504Z
