UID:2oc1ocno77sbsb8meogom43gdj@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20200122T180000
CREATED:20190620T202538Z
DESCRIPTION:<br><b>THERE WILL BE NO LABYRINTH WALK ON JANUARY 22\, 2020!</b
 ><br><br><br>Take your soul for a walk on the labyrinth\, Wed Eves 6pm-8pm 
 (closed on holidays).<br>The spiritual practice of labyrinth walking is an 
 ancient\, yet ever new\, experience of prayer and meditation.  As we enter 
 the sacred path we attempt to open ourselves to God’s presence through the 
 simple act of mindful walking.  <br>&nbsp\;<br>As we follow the twists and 
 turns of the path\, we see that we are not on a maze — with wrong turns and
  dead ends — but on an unbroken path to the center\, the symbolic heart of 
 God.  There we rest in deeper stillness as we take a moment to center ourse
 lves.  Then\, as you are ready to return to the world\, you follow the same
  path back out — refreshed and renewed to listen more deeply for God in you
 r daily life.  The labyrinth is different for different people\, and at dif
 ferent times.  But one thing remains the same: you have taken a step closer
  to God.  (See <a href="https://fccmontclair.org/walk-the-labyrinth/">"Wors
 hip/Walk the Labyrinth"</a> tab on our website for more info and a video on
  walking the labyrinth.)<br>&nbsp\;<br>At First Congregational Church we op
 en the labyrinth to the wider community so that all may experience it.  It 
 is open each Wednesday evening from 6pm-8pm from September - June.  You may
  also request to walk the labyrinth at other times by calling the church of
 fice to see if it is free (973-744-4856).
LAST-MODIFIED:20200121T165420Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:CLOSED TONIGHT ONLY! Labyrinth Walk\, 6-8pm 
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
