DTSTAMP:20260401T043557Z
UID:5u7sjb8sftht4lji3kb9j472s8_R20220217T003000@google.com
CREATED:20220127T225821Z
DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><u></u><p><span><i>&nbsp\;</i><u><b>Fo
 ur Wednesday Evening Sessions in February 7:30pm to 9 pm:</b></u> </span></
 p><u></u><u></u><p><i><b><span><span>Zoom Link will be provided soon.</span
 ></span></b></i><br></p><u></u><u></u><p><span><i>Our first three sessions 
 will take place over Zoom. For our last class\, we will gather in the FCC G
 uild Room and also provide a virtual option.</i></span></p><span>February 2
 nd - on Zoom (led by Rev. Dr. Taussig)<br>&nbsp\;February 9th - on Zoom (le
 d by Rev. Dr. Taussig)<br>February 16th - on Zoom (led by Rev. Dr. Spencer-
 Miller)<br>February 23rd -<b> </b>in-person and virtual (led by Rev. John)<
 /span><p><span><b>We encourage you to pick up a copy of <i>After Jesus\, Be
 fore Christianity:</i></b></span><b><i> </i></b><u><b><a href="https://www.
 harpercollins.com/products/after-jesus-before-christianity-erin-vearncombeb
 randon-scotthal-taussig?variant=33097760636962"><span>Please click here</sp
 an></a></b></u><span>. Although reading the text is recommended\, it is not
  required. </span></p><p><span><i>If you'd like any assistance paying for t
 he book\,&nbsp\; please let us know. FCC received a generous anonymous dona
 tion from a member to help cover the cost of books for folks who need it.</
 i></span></p><p><br><span><u>Course Write-Up: </u></span></p><p><span>What 
 do we really know about how Christianity took shape? Do the rituals\, pract
 ices\, and beliefs common today look anything like those of the earliest Ch
 ristians? How did the earliest followers of Jesus navigate the changing wor
 ld around them\, build greater spiritual fortitude\, and create a movement 
 that has deeply impacted the world?<br>&nbsp\;<br>Highlighting the many arc
 heological and manuscript discoveries over the past twenty years\, After Je
 sus\, Before Christianity offers new insights that provide a paradigm-shift
 ing picture.<br>&nbsp\;<br>Each Wednesday in February\, our FCC community w
 ill explore the diversity\, creativity\, and spirituality of the earliest f
 ollowers of Jesus. Three scholars and ministers will help lead us on this j
 ourney<b>.</b>The first is <b>Rev. Dr. Hal Taussig\,</b> former Professor o
 f New Testament at Union Theological Seminary and one of the authors of Aft
 er Jesus\, Before Christianity. One session will be led by our own <b>Rev. 
 Dr. Althea Spencer Miller</b>\, Assistant Professor of New Testament at Dre
 w Theological Seminary. And\, finally\, helping to guide the conversation e
 ach week\, will be <b>Rev. John Rogers</b>\, FCC’s Lead Pastor of Spiritual
  Formation and Community Development.</span></p><p><br><span><b>If you have
  any questions please email Rev. John at&nbsp\; </b></span><a href="mailto:
 john.rogers28@gmail.com"><span>john.rogers28@gmail.com</span></a><span>.</s
 pan></p><p><span>We hope you join us for this paradigm-shifting and spiritu
 ally enriching journey into the life and practices of the early church!</sp
 an></p><u></u><u></u><u></u></html-blob>
LAST-MODIFIED:20220208T213546Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:After Jesus\, Before Christianity A New Study Of Our Spiritual Root
 s: 4 Wednesdays Evenings  Starting 2/2 at 7:30 pm
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
