DESCRIPTION:<span>Join the FCC Green Team and the Youth Group for a special
  experience with these magnificent birds. To carpool\, meet at FCC at 9:45.
   To sign up and get more information\, please email  Elizabeth Honer (</sp
 an><a href="mailto:grrlrighter@gmail.com"><span>grrlrighter@gmail.com</span
 ></a><span>).</span><p><span>The Raptor Trust\, located in Basking Ridge\, 
 NJ\, on 14 gorgeous acres\, was established in 1968 as a haven for all kind
 s of injured birds of prey\, who for years had been hunted with impunity. T
 o learn more about the Raptor Trust you can </span><a href="https://therapt
 ortrust.org/"><span><b>CLICK HERE.</b></span></a><span> <b>Our tour is sche
 duled for 11am. </b><br>For those driving themselves\, the address is 1390 
 White Bridge Rd\, Basking Ridge\, NJ 07920. </span><a href="https://therapt
 ortrust.org/visit/directions/"><span><b>CLICK HERE</b></span></a><span> for
  directions.</span></p><p><span>After the tour\, we can do a little free-fo
 rm exploring together\, and then Derek Polzer is going to lead a Poetry in 
 Nature workshop\, likely around 12:30 or so. We'll leave around 2:00 and ge
 t back to FCC by 3:00 at the latest (for those carpooling).</span></p><p><s
 pan><i>There is no cost for this event -- our admission will be underwritte
 n by the Lilly Foundation Sabbatical grant.  </i> </span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230713T155606Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Get Close to the Wonder of Nature at the Raptor Trust\, July 22!  (
 Sign up by July 20 - limited to 15 people)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
