UID:438587elkjr5fo61f25p3c39ss@google.com
CREATED:20230123T170617Z
DESCRIPTION:<h1><span><a href="https://firstcongmontclair.us6.list-manage.c
 om/track/click?u=62bf2ca744bdb8b46fa1a7788&id=ed837ec6c2&e=d2d6ac503b"><spa
 n></span></a></span></h1><p><span>Join Rev. Dr. JJ Flag in a zoom conversat
 ion to look at this question from the perspective of disability justice and
  disability theology. Rev. Flag is the Associate Minister of Pastoral Care 
 and Justice at Myers Park Baptist Church in Charlotte\, NC. Having been bor
 n with a disability\, advocating for those with disabilities is an integral
  part of living out his call. As a member of the UCC’s Disabilities Ministr
 ies Board of Directors\, JJ hopes to bring about lasting change for persons
  with disabilities within the denomination and beyond. He will lead us in a
  discussion of disability justice and theology. We will learn about some fr
 ameworks for understanding disability in society and the church\, wrestle w
 ith what stories scripture tells about disability\, and ask how we as churc
 hes can work towards becoming more accessible. I hope you will join us for 
 this valuable conversation.</span></p><p><a href="https://us02web.zoom.us/j
 /3319435596#success"><span> <span><b><span>Click Here for Zoom Link</span><
 /b></span></span></a></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span> </span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230123T171104Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY: “Disability Justice and Disability Theology” with Rev. JJ Flagg - 
 7pm on Zoom
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
