DESCRIPTION:Take your soul for a walk on the labyrinth.&nbsp\; <span>We are
  pleased to offer labyrinth walks each Wednesday in mid-day as a chance to 
 connect with your soul in our beautiful sanctuary.&nbsp\;<br><b><br>Social 
 distancing will be observed with one walker at a time on the labyrinth and 
 specially designated pews for prayer and meditation. </b>We look forward to
  welcoming you back. </span><br><br>The spiritual practice of labyrinth wal
 king is an ancient\, yet ever new\, experience of prayer and meditation.  A
 s we enter the sacred path we attempt to open ourselves to God’s presence t
 hrough the simple act of mindful walking.  <br>&nbsp\;<br>As we follow the 
 twists and turns of the path\, we see that we are not on a maze — with wron
 g turns and dead ends — but on an unbroken path to the center\, the symboli
 c heart of God.  There we rest in deeper stillness as we take a moment to c
 enter ourselves.  Then\, as you are ready to return to the world\, you foll
 ow the same path back out — refreshed and renewed to listen more deeply for
  God in your daily life.  The labyrinth is different for different people\,
  and at different times.  But one thing remains the same: you have taken a 
 step closer to God.  (See <a href="https://fccmontclair.org/walk-the-labyri
 nth/">"Worship/Walk the Labyrinth"</a> tab on our website for more info and
  a video on walking the labyrinth.)<br>&nbsp\;<br>At First Congregational C
 hurch we open the labyrinth to the wider community so that all may experien
 ce it.
LAST-MODIFIED:20200828T214950Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Re-Opens with new time: Weekly Labyrinth Walks\, Wednesdays 11am-1p
 m in the Sanctuary
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
