DESCRIPTION:<br><b>Tonight's Labyrinth Walk is cancelled.</b> (we will resu
 me next week Wednesday 6-8pm.)<br><br><br>Take your soul for a walk on the 
 labyrinth\, Wed Eves 6pm-8pm (closed on holidays).<br>The spiritual practic
 e of labyrinth walking is an ancient\, yet ever new\, experience of prayer 
 and meditation.  As we enter the sacred path we attempt to open ourselves t
 o God’s presence through the simple act of mindful walking.  <br>&nbsp\;<br
 >As we follow the twists and turns of the path\, we see that we are not on 
 a maze — with wrong turns and dead ends — but on an unbroken path to the ce
 nter\, the symbolic heart of God.  There we rest in deeper stillness as we 
 take a moment to center ourselves.  Then\, as you are ready to return to th
 e world\, you follow the same path back out — refreshed and renewed to list
 en more deeply for God in your daily life.  The labyrinth is different for 
 different people\, and at different times.  But one thing remains the same:
  you have taken a step closer to God.  (See <a href="https://fccmontclair.o
 rg/walk-the-labyrinth/">"Worship/Walk the Labyrinth"</a> tab on our website
  for more info and a video on walking the labyrinth.)<br>&nbsp\;<br>At Firs
 t Congregational Church we open the labyrinth to the wider community so tha
 t all may experience it.  It is open each Wednesday evening from 6pm-8pm fr
 om September - June.  You may also request to walk the labyrinth at other t
 imes by calling the church office to see if it is free (973-744-4856).
