CREATED:20210714T163746Z
DESCRIPTION:<span>Weekly: Wednesdays 11am-1pm in the Sanctuary</span><span>
  </span><span></span><i> </i><p></p><p><span>Take your soul for a walk on t
 he labyrinth.&nbsp\; We are pleased to offer labyrinth walks each Wednesday
  in the mid-day as a chance to connect with your soul in our beautiful sanc
 tuary.&nbsp\;<br><br><b>Social distancing will be observed with one walker 
 at a time on the labyrinth and specially designated pews for prayer and med
 itation. We look forward to welcoming you back.</b></span> <br></p><p><span
 >The labyrinth is an ancient spiritual tool \, a mode of “walking prayer” t
 hat invites us to go deeper in our walk with God.&nbsp\; Our labyrinth\, mo
 deled on one in Chartes Cathedral in France\, sits as the center of our San
 ctuary\, a constant metaphor for our spiritual lives.&nbsp\; Just like the 
 labyrinth\, our lives are not linear\, but filled with twists and turns.&nb
 sp\; Sometimes we make great progress\, and other times we feel we are goin
 g backwards.&nbsp\; But if we trust in the path we will find ourselves in t
 he center -- the heart of God.</span> <br></p><p><span>All are welcome to t
 ake their souls out for a healing walk... no experience necessary!&nbsp\;</
 span> <a href="https://baristanet.com/2014/03/labyrinth-walk-meditation-sat
 isfies-soul/"><span>Check out this lovely write up on Baristanet</span></a>
  <span>from the Spring 2014.</span> <br></p><p><a href="https://www.youtube
 .com/watch?time_continue=2&v=D453ajtWb74&feature=emb_logo"><span>Watch this
  video</span></a> <span>to find out more about walking the labyrinth. If yo
 u’ve never done so come out one Wednesday evening and give it a try. It is 
 a wonderful way to nourish your soul and spend some quiet time in prayer or
  meditation.</span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20211104T214624Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Weekly Labyrinth Walks\, Wednesdays 11am-1pm
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
