BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:First Congregational Church Montclair
X-SOURCE-URL:https://fccmontclair.org/upcoming-events-at-fcc/
DTSTART:20191019T210000Z
DTEND:20191019T223000Z
DTSTAMP:20260401T043557Z
UID:6e7c3c59mqa2d0per4ddd5nf2d@google.com
CREATED:20190916T174720Z
DESCRIPTION:<br><br><i>Underground Church travels back to our earliest Chri
 stian roots. We seek to recapture the excitement and community of Jesus' ea
 rly followers through worship that is simple yet profound\, communal yet pe
 rsonal\, comforting yet inspiring. All are welcome to this monthly worship!
 </i><br><br>This Saturday\, October 19:&nbsp\;&nbsp\; <b>The Persistence of
  the Heart</b><br>&nbsp\;<br>In Luke Chapter 18\, Jesus shares with his dis
 ciples the tale of a persistent widow.&nbsp\; Despite being turned away mul
 tiple times by a hard-hearted judge who cares neither for other people nor 
 for God\, this courageous woman demands justice against an adversary.&nbsp\
 ; Finally\, against all odds\, the judge hears her and gives her the satisf
 action she seeks. It is an encounter that calls us to examine our own persi
 stence in the face of adversity.&nbsp\; In a world that can seem harsh and 
 uncaring\, how do we keep our hearts open with Jesus' message of warmth\, l
 ove and compassion?<br>&nbsp\;<br>&nbsp\;&nbsp\; As always\, Jesus describe
 s an encounter that is overflowing with possibilities.&nbsp\; Who are we in
  this encounter?&nbsp\; Are we the widow\, bravely and repeatedly confronti
 ng an uncaring person?&nbsp\; Or are we sometimes the judge\, stubbornly re
 fusing to see what God shows us so clearly?&nbsp\; Ultimately\, how do we b
 ring these two powerful characters into union\,&nbsp\; closing the distance
  between prayer and response\, becoming the very force for good in the worl
 d that we are praying for?<br><br>Join us this Saturday evening as we explo
 re&nbsp\; the Parable of the Persistent Widow and witness an encounter betw
 een a force that persistently calls for "yes" in the face of "no."&nbsp\; <
 br><br>Underground church travels back to our earliest Christian roots.&nbs
 p\; We seek to recapture the excitement and community of Jesus' early follo
 wers through worship that is simple yet profound\, communal yet personal\, 
 comforting yet inspiring.&nbsp\; We live the questions much as Jesus' frien
 ds did as they sought ways to transform the world through the simple acts o
 f a shared and loving community. <br>&nbsp\;<br>We invite you to gather wit
 h us this Saturday\, October 19th\, on the Labyrinth in FCC's sanctuary to 
 go deeper into the beauty of community.&nbsp\; Worship will be informal. We
  will engage through the reading of sacred texts\, share a simple and bless
 ed light communion meal\, and join in music that celebrates community.&nbsp
 \; <br><br>Join us as we explore this powerful story.&nbsp\; All are welcom
 e!
LAST-MODIFIED:20191017T165405Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Underground Church\, 5pm on the labyrinth in the FCC Sanctuary
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
