CREATED:20220517T212256Z
DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><br>    <html-blob><html-blob><p><b><span>CPR (Adult
  &amp\; Pediatric) Certification Class at FCC! Wednesday May 18\, 7pm in th
 e Guild Room</span></b><br><html-blob><html-blob></html-blob></html-blob></
 p></html-blob></html-blob></html-blob><html-blob><p><span>FCC now owns an A
 utomated External Defibrillator (AED). This device is used to help those ex
 periencing sudden cardiac arrest. It's a sophisticated\, yet easy-to-use\, 
 medical device that can analyze the heart's rhythm and\, if necessary\, del
 iver an electrical shock\, or defibrillation\, to help the heart re-establi
 sh an effective rhythm.<br><br>You can learn CPR and how to use an AED in o
 ne evening at First Congregational Church.<br>&nbsp\;<u>Cost:</u><br>$50/pe
 rson and is open to all ages.&nbsp\;<br>Payment will be collected on the ni
 ght of the training <i>(paid directly to vendor by cash/check/credit card).
  </i></span><br></p><p><i><b><span>And yes\, you can show up for the class 
 if you didn't get a chance to register.</span></b></i></p></html-blob>
LAST-MODIFIED:20220517T212328Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:CPR & AED Training in the Guild Room\, 7pm
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
