DESCRIPTION:The Interfaith Hospitality Network (IHN) helps temporarily home
 less families in Essex County get back on their feet.  Families stay in loc
 al churches and synagogues and have meals\, companionship\, and overnight s
 upervision provided by volunteers from the congregations as they rebuild th
 eir lives.  \n\nFor the past few years we have partnered with Union Congreg
 ational Church as they host IHN families in their church building (176 Coop
 er Avenue\, Upper Montclair).   \n\nThis November we are again recruiting f
 or volunteers to staff the various shifts!  \n\nFirst Congregational will b
 e volunteering to help on  November 7\, 9 & 11 this year. You can sign up o
 nline by going to www.tinyurl.com/nov2IHN where you can sign up for opportu
 nities to help with contributing a meal\, clean-up 5:30 to 7:30\, children'
 s activities 6:30 to 8:30 and overnight supervision (if you sign-up for the
  overnight shift please bring a pillow and a blanket.)    \n\nAs volunteers
  we provide food\, conversation\, and for the children\, games or help with
  homework. \n\nwww.tinyurl.com/nov2IHN \n
LAST-MODIFIED:20171010T161853Z
LOCATION:Union Congregational Church\, 176 Cooper Avenue\, Montclair\, NJ
SEQUENCE:2
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Help Serve Local Homeless Families Through IHN November 7\, 9 & 11 
 (at Union Cong)
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
