CREATED:20220224T174735Z
DESCRIPTION:<span>The Journey of Lent Begins with Ash Wednesday\, March 2 a
 t 7:30pm in the Sanctuary&nbsp\;</span><p><strong><em><span>"From dust you 
 came and to dust you shall return..."</span></em></strong><br></p><p><span>
 The season of Lent is a time for going deeper into our faith journey and co
 ming to terms with our struggles and our yearning for God. It is a time of 
 reflection that prepares us for the&nbsp\;passion of Holy Week and the glor
 y of Easter Sunday.<br>&nbsp\;<br>We begin with a special Ash Wednesday ser
 vice. Through song and prayers and times of silence we will share the ritua
 l of the imposition of ashes\, a symbol of our mortality and brokenness\, a
 s well as experience the hope and unity of Holy Communion.<br>&nbsp\;<br>Th
 is is a deeply meaningful way to begin the season.&nbsp\; If you are new to
  our tradition and have never been to an Ash Wednesday service\, we encoura
 ge you to share it with us.<br>&nbsp\;<br>We will be <a href="https://www.f
 acebook.com/FCCMontclair/" id="ow1277" __is_owner="true">live-streaming</a>
  the service over Facebook. For the safety of in-person attendance&nbsp\; C
 OVID-safe protocols will be observed.</span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20220224T175001Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Ash Wednesday\, 7:30pm in the sanctuary
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
