CREATED:20160810T150012Z
DESCRIPTION:PLEASE CALL CHURCH TO FIND OUT ABOUT TONIGHT - MIGHT BE CANCELL
 ED DUE TO WEATHER!\n\n\nTake your soul for a walk on the labyrinth\, Wed Ev
 es 6pm-8pm (closed on holidays).\n\nThe spiritual practice of labyrinth wal
 king is an ancient\, yet ever new\, experience of prayer and meditation.  A
 s we enter the sacred path we attempt to open ourselves to God’s presence t
 hrough the simple act of mindful walking.  \n \nAs we follow the twists and
  turns of the path\, we see that we are not on a maze — with wrong turns an
 d dead ends — but on an unbroken path to the center\, the symbolic heart of
  God.  There we rest in deeper stillness as we take a moment to center ours
 elves.  Then\, as you are ready to return to the world\, you follow the sam
 e path back out — refreshed and renewed to listen more deeply for God in yo
 ur daily life.  The labyrinth is different for different people\, and at di
 fferent times.  But one thing remains the same: you have taken a step close
 r to God.  (See "Going Deeper" page for more info and a video on walking th
 e labyrinth.)\n \nAt First Congregational Church we open the labyrinth to t
 he wider community so that all may experience it.  It is open each Wednesda
 y evening from 6pm-8pm.  You may also request to walk the labyrinth at othe
 r times by calling the church office to see if it is free (973-744-4856).
LAST-MODIFIED:20170809T151930Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Labyrinth Walks 6-8pm (POSSIBLY CANCELLED TONIGHT DUE TO WEATHER)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
