DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><b><span></span></b><span><span>We are beyond
  thrilled that FCC will have our own booth at Montclair's 1st Annual Pride 
 Festival (location TBA)\, where we will be able to represent our church com
 munity's Open and Affirming LGBTQIA+ Inclusion. <span>To learn more\, </spa
 n><a href="https://firstcongmontclair.us6.list-manage.com/track/click?u=62b
 f2ca744bdb8b46fa1a7788&id=eead634314&e=d2d6ac503b"><b><span>CLICK HERE.</sp
 an></b></a></span></span><br><span><span></span></span><u></u><u></u><p><sp
 an><span>As we approach&nbsp\;the event\, we want to touch base about a few
  matters and ask for your help.&nbsp\;</span></span></p><p><span><span><br>
 <b><u><span>Volunteers</span></u></b><u>:</u> Pride is on Saturday\, June 1
 1th from 11 am - 6 pm. We are asking for volunteers to help represent FCC a
 nd introduce who we are. We have broken it down into four 2-hour shifts and
  we are hoping to have at least four volunteers per shift.<br><b><span>Use 
 the following linkto sign up: <a href="https://firstcongmontclair.us6.list-
 manage.com/track/click?u=62bf2ca744bdb8b46fa1a7788&id=534e31382b&e=d2d6ac50
 3b"><span>https://forms.gle/H2aNTeUc27a2Xgkv9</span></a></span></b><br>&nbs
 p\;<br><b><u><span>Slide Show</span></u></b><u>:</u>We are collecting photo
 s to feature in a slideshow! We are looking for as many images as possible 
 that reflect&nbsp\;and tell our story as an Open and Affirming Church. If y
 ou have any photos to share\, please send them to Daniel Belnavis (<a href=
 "mailto:djbelnavis@gmail.com"><span>djbelnavis@gmail.com</span></a>). If yo
 ur photos exceed the size limit for email\, please upload them to Google Dr
 ive and send the link to Daniel. </span></span></p><u></u></html-blob>
