CREATED:20110321T135654Z
DESCRIPTION:Still Speaking” Interfaith Event\, Sunday\, May 1\, 2016 at FCC
 \n“Finding Hope Beyond Religious Violence”\n\nIn a time of fear\, divisive 
 language and angry politics\, coming together across religious lines is mor
 e important than ever.  We know that God has something to say to us in this
  moment.   On Sunday\, May 1\, 2016 Montclair will be the site of an interf
 aith conversation on how people of faith can respond in this climate of fea
 r.  The event\, held at First Congregational Church of Montclair\, will inc
 lude shared worship\, an interfaith panel discussion\, and a lunch open to 
 the public.   The panel is part of the "Abraham's Table" series by the Peac
 e Islands Institute\, an Islamic organization whose mission is to foster op
 en dialogue and friendship between the Muslim\, Jewish and Christian commun
 ities.  This event is part of the “Still Speaking” series sponsored by Unio
 n Congregational Church and First Congregational Church. Mark your calendar
 s and join this important conversation! \n\n10:30am Interfaith Worship serv
 ice at FCC \n\n11:45am “Abraham’s Table” panel discussion on \n“Finding Hop
 e Beyond Religious Violence”\nPanelists: Dr. Nuray Yurt\, Rabbi Ariann Weit
 zman and Rev. David Shaw\n\n1:15pm Lunch on our front lawn provided by the 
 Peace Islands Institute (please RSVP for lunch if possible)\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20230105T101302Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Sunday Worship Service (Special “Still Speaking” Interfaith Service
 !)  
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
