DESCRIPTION:<span>UndergroundChurch travels back to our earliest Christian 
 roots.&nbsp\; We seek to recapturethe excitement and community of Jesus's e
 arly followers through worship that issimple yet profound\, <span align="ri
 ght" width="165" height="94"></span>communal yet personal\,comforting yet i
 nspiring.&nbsp\; We live the questions much as Jesus' friendsdid as they so
 ught ways to transform the world through the simple acts of ashared and lov
 ing community.&nbsp\;Worship is informal\, but we engage throughthe reading
  of a sacred text\, create space to share what is on our hearts\, andshare 
 a simple and blessed communion meal of soup\, salad\, and bread\, ending ou
 revening with song and "Spiritual Take-Out."&nbsp\;We will meet at thehome 
 of Julie Matz-Rees—<u> <b>to RSVP and get address please email her</b> at</
 u> <a href="mailto:juliemarie.matz@gmail.com" target="_blank"><span>juliema
 rie.matz@gmail.com</span></a></span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20180110T151427Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Underground Church (please contact Julie Matz for address)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
