CREATED:20200221T202045Z
DESCRIPTION:<br>    <br><p>The season of Lent is a time for going deeper in
 to our faith journey and coming to terms with our struggles and our yearnin
 g for God. We begin with a special Ash Wednesday service. Through song and 
 prayers and times of silence we will share the ritual of the imposition of 
 ashes\, a symbol of our mortality and sinfulness\, as well as experience th
 e hope and unity of Holy Communion.</p><p>This is a deeply meaningful way t
 o begin the season. &nbsp\;If you are new to our tradition and have never b
 een to an Ash Wednesday service\, we encourage you to share it with us. (Ou
 r regular Wednesday Labyrinth walk will end at 7:30pm to prepare for our wo
 rship service.)</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20200221T202045Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Ash Wednesday Service\, 8pm
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
