UID:2885upg9atqr7ndps9dr933guh@google.com
CREATED:20200124T160036Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><span>On February 19\, Rev. Ann Ralosky will lead a scriptur
 e study to engage issues of LGBTQ justice and the biblical tradition at FCC
  in the Sanctuary at 7:30pm. &nbsp\; ALL ARE WELCOME!</span></p><p><span></
 span></p><p>This special evening of sacred study and conversation is part o
 f a spring series called: <strong>2020 Interfaith and Ecumenical Series of 
 Sacred Studies: Breaking the Hate</strong></p><p>It is sponsored by Union B
 aptist church and invites clergy from area congregations to share a scriptu
 re study engaging issues of injustice which stem from a culture of white su
 premacy.&nbsp\; In this study we will engage in conversations around the te
 xts that are so often used to condemn LGBTQ persons and relationships and s
 ee them through the lens of historical context and Jesus’ call to just comm
 unity. <br></p><p>&nbsp\;</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20200218T163818Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Rev. Ann leading town wide Bible Study (in FCC Sanctuary)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
