DESCRIPTION:John & Ann Ralosky and Nancy & Luis Pi-Sunyer invite you to the
 ir homes for the 5th Annual First Congregational Church Christmas Open Hous
 e!  (Contact office for location and to RSVP).  \n\nJoin us for an afternoo
 n in Montclair's oldest continuous home (built in 1723!) for a time of trea
 ts both sweet and savory\, mulled wine\, egg nog and a generous helping of 
 holiday cheer!  Once a year our two families take down the dividing wall in
  this historic house and combine our two homes together\, welcoming all our
  friends from FCC. We'll provide ham\, turkey\, beverages and sweets\, but 
 we'd love for you to add to the feast!  If you are able\, please bring an a
 ppetizer\, side dish or dessert.  If you can just bring yourself\, that's g
 ift enough\, too!  Please RSVP to Rena Majeed at FCC (admin@fccmtc.com or 9
 73-744-4856) so we know you are coming!  Looking forward to seeing you ther
 e!
