CREATED:20180322T205806Z
DESCRIPTION:<br><p><span>April 2\, 5 &amp\; 7<b> (</b></span><b><u><span>At
  Union Congregational Church</span></u><span>) </span></b></p><p></p><p><sp
 an>The Interfaith Hospitality Network (IHN) helps temporarily homeless fami
 lies in Essex County get back on their feet. Families stay in local churche
 s and synagogues and have meals\, companionship\, and overnight supervision
  provided by volunteers from the congregations as they rebuild their lives.
  </span></p><p></p><p><span>For the past several years we have partnered wi
 th Union Congregational Church as they host IHN families <u><b>in their chu
 rch building </b></u></span><span><u><b>(176 Cooper Avenue\, Upper Montclai
 r).</b></u>This </span><span>April </span><span>we are again recruiting for
  volunteers to staff the various shifts! </span></p><p></p><p><span>See bel
 ow for the link where you can sign up for </span><span>opportunities to hel
 p with : </span></p><ul><li><span>c</span><span>ontributing a meal </span><
 /li><li><span></span><span>clean-up 5:30 to 7:30pm </span></li><li><span></
 span><span>children's activities 6:30 to 8:30pm </span></li><li><span></spa
 n><span>and overnight supervision (if you sign up for the overnight shift p
 lease bring a pillow and a blanket.) </span></li></ul><p></p><p><span><span
 ><a href="http://www.signupgenius.com/go/4090545abab2ba02-november"><b>Clic
 k here to sign up!!</b></a></span></span></p><p><span>As volunteers we prov
 ide food\, conversation\, and for the children\, games or help with homewor
 k.</span><span>Contact our IHN Coordinator\, Sarah Grigg\, at </span><a hre
 f="mailto:sfeliciano1@gmail.com"><span>sfeliciano1@gmail.com</span></a><spa
 n> if you have any questions. </span></p><p></p><p><span><br></span></p><p>
 <span> </span><span><br></span></p><p></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20180322T205806Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Help Serve Local Homeless Families Through IHN  April 2\, 5 & 7
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
