RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20190616T103000
CREATED:20110321T135654Z
DESCRIPTION:<br>Please join us today for a special <b>Juneteenth Celebratio
 n worship service!</b> <br><br>Juneteenth is the oldest known celebration c
 ommemorating the end of slavery.  Dating back to 1865\, it was on June 19 t
 hat the Union soldiers landed in Galveston\, TX with the news that the Civi
 l war had ended and all enslaved people were free.  This was a full 2 years
  after the Emancipation Proclamation made slavery illegal.  Since that time
 \, African American communities have proclaimed Juneteenth as their Indepen
 dence Day.<br>This year\, FCC will join in the celebration!  Join us for a 
 wonderful worship service of music\, stories and sacred ritual to acknowled
 ge this important day in our nation's history.
LAST-MODIFIED:20200503T045201Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Sunday Worship Service
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:First Congregational Church Montclair
X-SOURCE-URL:https://fccmontclair.org/upcoming-events-at-fcc/
DTSTART:20231222T003000Z
DTEND:20231222T013000Z
DTSTAMP:20260401T043557Z
UID:35puq20ed507ni7tm3nku1v3ml@google.com
CREATED:20231206T155029Z
DESCRIPTION:<span><b></b>Join us for a contemplative and healing service to
  acknowledge the shadow side of the season present within the light.</span>
 <br><span> </span><br><b><u>Sometimes the Christmas season is not so merry<
 /u></b><br> <br> If you are needing comfort this season join us for The Lon
 gest Night:<br><b><u>7:00pm</u></b> Solstice Singing Bowl Sound Meditation<
 br><b><u>7:30pm</u></b> Longest Night Service   <br> <br>Christmas is a tim
 e of joy and celebration. Yet for many of us the holiday season brings more
  complicated emotions. Separation from loved ones through distance or death
 \, personal illness\, difficult memories\, loneliness\, or financial stress
  can make this "season of light" a time of darkness. <br><br>On Thursday\, 
 December 21\, the longest night of the year\, we will offer a special worsh
 ip experience to acknowledge the difficult emotions of the season and offer
  a place for blessing and comfort.  <b>We will begin at 7pm with a Sound Me
 ditation on singing bowls and then at 7:30 we will begin our contemplative 
 service</b> of readings and music\, a time to pray individually with our pa
 stors\, receive an anointing with oil\, and an opportunity to walk the laby
 rinth.<br> <br><b><i>You are not alone. Join us for moment of comfort and h
 ope. All are welcome.</i></b>
LAST-MODIFIED:20231208T231950Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Longest Night Service\, 7:30pm in the Sanctuary
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
