UID:2pga9pj88l22vjhedqlv6fckff@google.com
CREATED:20200807T161452Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><b>Waiting for a sign from God</b><br><br><br>If we are look
 ing for a sign from God\, we couldn't do much better than what Moses experi
 enced...a flaming bush that doesn't burn itself up\, an angel speaking to h
 im from the midst of the conflagration\, and the voice of God calling him b
 y name.&nbsp\; That message would be hard to miss\, and even harder to igno
 re. <br><br><br>The signs we see today may be more subtle\, but are no less
  compelling.&nbsp\; We who believe that God is still speaking know that She
  is there with us everyday\, making Her voice heard through the friend in n
 eed of healing\, the lonely person in need of a companion\, and a world cry
 ing out in a thousand ways for justice.<br><br><br>How do we make sure we h
 ear God's voice and see His signs?&nbsp\; How do we make sure our minds and
  hearts are open to God's messages everywhere\, making sure that we hear no
 t only the shouts\, but the whispers\, and see not only the firey bush\, bu
 t the face of God in our simplest encounters?<br><br><br>Join us this Satur
 day as we read Exodus 3:1-15 and explore Moses' encounter with the burning 
 bush and the voice of God as he is called to lead his people to safety.&nbs
 p\; It was a tall order to be sure\, but God promised to be with him.&nbsp\
 ; Just as God will be with us when She calls\, lighting the fire of compass
 ion in each one of us.<br><br><br>Once again\, the Spirit leads Underground
  Church to go beyond our social distance boundaries and find a way to care 
 for each other through the wonders of technology.<br><br>This Saturday\, we
  will meet virtually through the online program Zoom. Please click this lin
 k to join the meeting: <a href="https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84845199677" id="
 ow330" __is_owner="true"><b>https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84845199677</b></a>. 
 Together\, we will talk\, sing\, and create sacred space that transcends th
 e walls of our homes.&nbsp\; Like Jesus' early followers\, we will gather t
 ogether to ease our fears and loneliness by creating a community of love an
 d trust. All are welcome!</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20200828T213159Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Underground Church\, 5pm via Zoom Teleconferencing
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
