CREATED:20171207T201756Z
DESCRIPTION:<span><span><span><b><span>Waiting\, Wandering\, Welcoming</spa
 n></b></span><br><br>During this Advent season\, how do we experience the w
 ait?&nbsp\; Are wewandering through our days\, feeling pressure and stress?
 &nbsp\; Or are we livingin that space\, preparing ourselves to meet the God
  who has been with us allalong?&nbsp\; Join us at Underground Church this S
 aturday evening as we delveinto Isaiah Chapter 40 and "prepare the way of t
 he Lord\," recognizingthis sacred time of experiencing God in the waiting\,
  welcoming God and eachother in an evening of community\, communion\, and s
 ong.</span></span><span><br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span>Undergroundchurch travel
 s back to our earliest Christian roots.&nbsp\; We seek to recapturethe exci
 tement and community of Jesus's early followers through worship that issimp
 le yet profound\, communal yet personal\, comforting yet inspiring.&nbsp\; 
 Welive the questions much as Jesus's friends did as they sought ways to tra
 nsformthe world through the simple acts of a shared and loving community.</
 span></span><br><span><span>&nbsp\;</span></span><i><br><span><span>Weinvit
 e you to gather with us this Saturday\, December 9th from 5PM to 6:30PM</sp
 an></span><span><span>&nbsp\;</span></span></i></span><span><i><span>at the
  home of Deband Julie Matz-Rees\,</span></i></span><span><i><span>&nbsp\;<a
  href="https://firstcongmontclair.us6.list-manage.com/track/click?u=62bf2ca
 744bdb8b46fa1a7788&amp\;id=7ce6779694&amp\;e=d2d6ac503b"><span>268 Park Str
 eet\, Upper Montclair</span></a></span></i></span><span><span>\,&nbsp\;to g
 o deeperinto the beauty of community.&nbsp\; Worship will be informal. We w
 ill engagethrough the reading of sacred texts\, share a simple and blessed 
 communion mealof soup and bread\, and end our evening with "Spiritual Take-
 Out"&nbsp\;to make this Advent a blessed time of drawing closer to the God 
 who holds us inHer care.</span></span><span><br>&nbsp\;<br></span><b><span>
 <i><span>Please RSVP to Julie at</span></i></span></b><span><b>&nbsp\;</b><
 span><span><a href="mailto:juliemarie.matz@gmail.com" target="_blank"><span
 >juliemarie.matz@gmail.com</span></a>&nbsp\;andjoin us in the&nbsp\;transfo
 rmative power of opening hearts to the Holy Spirit andto each other. &nbsp\
 ;</span></span><br>&nbsp\;<br><span><i><u><span>Need a ride?</span></u></i>
 </span><span><span>&nbsp\; "The Underground Church TransportationService" w
 ill meet you in the FCC parking lot and drive you to our meetingplace\, and
  drive you back after our gathering!&nbsp\; Just be in the parking lotbehin
 d the church at 4:15PM and a member of the Underground Church family willbe
  there to greet you.</span></span></span>
