RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20191127T180000
CREATED:20190620T202538Z
DESCRIPTION:Take your soul for a walk on the labyrinth\, Wed Eves 6pm-8pm (
 closed on holidays).<br><br>The spiritual practice of labyrinth walking is 
 an ancient\, yet ever new\, experience of prayer and meditation.  As we ent
 er the sacred path we attempt to open ourselves to God’s presence through t
 he simple act of mindful walking.  <br>&nbsp\;<br>As we follow the twists a
 nd turns of the path\, we see that we are not on a maze — with wrong turns 
 and dead ends — but on an unbroken path to the center\, the symbolic heart 
 of God.  There we rest in deeper stillness as we take a moment to center ou
 rselves.  Then\, as you are ready to return to the world\, you follow the s
 ame path back out — refreshed and renewed to listen more deeply for God in 
 your daily life.  The labyrinth is different for different people\, and at 
 different times.  But one thing remains the same: you have taken a step clo
 ser to God.  (See <a href="https://fccmontclair.org/walk-the-labyrinth/" ta
 rget="_blank">"Worship/Walk the Labyrinth"</a> tab on our website for more 
 info and a video on walking the labyrinth.)<br>&nbsp\;<br>At First Congrega
 tional Church we open the labyrinth to the wider community so that all may 
 experience it.  It is open each Wednesday evening from 6pm-8pm from Septemb
 er - June.  You may also request to walk the labyrinth at other times by ca
 lling the church office to see if it is free (973-744-4856).
LAST-MODIFIED:20190930T193421Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:CLOSED TODAY: Weekly Labyrinth Walks\, 6-8pm Wednesdays in the Sanc
 tuary (closed on holidays)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:First Congregational Church Montclair
X-SOURCE-URL:https://fccmontclair.org/upcoming-events-at-fcc/
DTSTART:20190508T230000Z
DTEND:20190509T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260401T043557Z
UID:1ed5htehei0ti4t0t424drhpra@google.com
CREATED:20190503T193403Z
DESCRIPTION:<br><b>Please contact Mike to <u>RSVP by Sunday May 5th</u>: </
 b><a href="mailto:michael.magdalenski@gmail.com">michael.magdalenski@gmail.
 com</a><br><br><br>May's book club selection\, <i><b>The House of Broken An
 gels</b></i> <b>by Luis Alberto Urrea</b>\, has been called a "clamoring\, 
 joyful pan-generational family saga with an enormous\, bounding heart . . .
  a book about celebration that is itself a celebration" (Newsday/Washington
  Post)<br>In his final days\, beloved patriarch Miguel Angel de La Cruz\, a
 ffectionately called Big Angel\, has summoned his entire clan for one last 
 legendary birthday party. But as the party approaches\, his mother\, nearly
  one hundred\, dies\, transforming the weekend into a farewell doubleheader
 . Among the guests is Big Angel's half brother\, known as Little Angel\, wh
 o must reckon with his identity and the differences between his siblings' l
 ives and his own.<br>&nbsp\;<br>Across two bittersweet but riotous days in 
 their San Diego neighborhood\, the revelers mingle among the palm trees and
  cacti\, celebrating the lives of Big Angel and his mother\, and recounting
  the many myths that have passed into family lore\, the acts both ordinary 
 and heroic that brought the family to a fraught and sublime country and all
 owed them to flourish in the land they have come to call home.<br>&nbsp\;<b
 r>Teeming with warmth and humor\, authentic at every turn\, The House of Br
 oken Angels is Luis Alberto Urrea at his best\, and cements his reputation 
 as a storyteller of the first rank. (synopsis adapted from goodreads.com)<b
 r><br><br><u><b>FCC Member Mike Magdalenski is facilitating this group at h
 is home</b>.</u>&nbsp\; We like to make it both a literary and social eveni
 ng\, so <b>we invite pot luck contributions or light refreshments and bever
 ages as well.&nbsp\;</b> We'll gather at 7:00 with some social time and beg
 in book discussion at 7:30pm. <br><br><br><b>Please contact Mike to <u>RSVP
  by Sunday May 5th</u></b><u>:</u> <a href="mailto:michael.magdalenski@gmai
 l.com">michael.magdalenski@gmail.com</a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20190503T193403Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Next FCC Book Club  Meeting\, May 8\, 7pm (email Mike for location)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
