 ery Thursday at 7:00pm for approximately an hour on Zoom <i>(please note ne
 w time.)<br></i></span></p><p><span>Our method is to take our time and dig 
 deeply into Scripture\, bringing in cultural\, historical\,theological\, an
 d linguistic backgrounds and resources. We utilize Queries(questions posed 
 for consideration and opening\, not to garner answers) and cross-referencin
 g. (There are occasional dives down theological or linguistic rabbit holes.
 ) Participants are encouraged to have their favorite translation of the Bib
 le with them. </span></p><p><span><u><b>Click </b></u></span><a href="https
 ://us02web.zoom.us/j/87486762412?pwd=N0Z2eVlCNzJPbVM3VmdzZW1GYzZHUT09#succe
 ss"><u><b><span>HERE</span></b></u></a><a href="https://us02web.zoom.us/j/8
 7486762412?pwd=N0Z2eVlCNzJPbVM3VmdzZW1GYzZHUT09#success"><u><b> </b></u></a
 ><span><u><b>to join!  </b></u><b>Meeting ID: 874 8676 2412<br>Passcode: 98
 5645   </b>Phone only? Dial 646 558 8656  <br></span></p><p><span></span></
 p><p><b>Questions? Contact Rev. Jack Cuffari at <a href="mailto:jack@cuffar
 i.com">jack@cuffari.com</a>.</b><br></p><u></u><u></u>
