CREATED:20190306T183944Z
DESCRIPTION:Please join us on March 10th\, after worship\, when FCC welcome
 s sculptor Rev. Charles McCollough\, the artist who created the beautiful b
 eatitudes sculptures in our sanctuary.&nbsp\; During this special presentat
 ion he’ll discuss his inspiration for the beatitudes series of sculpture an
 d how they represent the complex relationship between Jesus and the values 
 of empire.<br><br>Come and listen as Rev. McCollough talks about the inters
 ection of socio-political\, theological and interpersonal themes. <b>He wil
 l also be offering his latest book\, called\, Picture This\,</b> which expl
 ores his experience as an artist with dyslexia and how he learned to use pi
 ctures to help him communicate.&nbsp\; <b>This will also be the special day
  that we will unveil a new\, powerful sculpture that Rev. McCollough is len
 ding to FCC\,&nbsp\;</b> that depicts the crucifixion carved from a single 
 elm tree. Save the date on your calendars\, and mark the connection card in
  your bulletin to let us know you’ll be attending.
LAST-MODIFIED:20190306T184415Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Conversation with the Sculptor  March 10 at FCC\, following worship
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
