UID:2oc1ocno77sbsb8meogom43gdj_R20200422T220000@google.com
CREATED:20190620T202538Z
DESCRIPTION:<br><b>IN ORDER TO CURB THE SPREAD OF THE COVID-19 VIRUS ALL CO
 MMUNAL PROGRAMS IS CANCELLED DURING THIS TIME</b><br><br>Take your soul for
  a walk on the labyrinth\, Wed Eves 6pm-8pm (closed on holidays).<br>The sp
 iritual practice of labyrinth walking is an ancient\, yet ever new\, experi
 ence of prayer and meditation.  As we enter the sacred path we attempt to o
 pen ourselves to God’s presence through the simple act of mindful walking. 
  <br>&nbsp\;<br>As we follow the twists and turns of the path\, we see that
  we are not on a maze — with wrong turns and dead ends — but on an unbroken
  path to the center\, the symbolic heart of God.  There we rest in deeper s
 tillness as we take a moment to center ourselves.  Then\, as you are ready 
 to return to the world\, you follow the same path back out — refreshed and 
 renewed to listen more deeply for God in your daily life.  The labyrinth is
  different for different people\, and at different times.  But one thing re
 mains the same: you have taken a step closer to God.  (See <a href="https:/
 /fccmontclair.org/walk-the-labyrinth/">"Worship/Walk the Labyrinth"</a> tab
  on our website for more info and a video on walking the labyrinth.)<br>&nb
 sp\;<br>At First Congregational Church we open the labyrinth to the wider c
 ommunity so that all may experience it.  It is open each Wednesday evening 
 from 6pm-8pm from September - June.  You may also request to walk the labyr
 inth at other times by calling the church office to see if it is free (973-
 744-4856).
LAST-MODIFIED:20200420T155734Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:ON HIATUS: Weekly Labyrinth Walks\, 6-8pm Wednesdays in the Sanctua
 ry (closed on holidays)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
