UID:no4e1dl85vnqvk2niidf2bmloo@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20161228T180000
CREATED:20160810T150012Z
DESCRIPTION:Take your soul for a walk on the labyrinth\, Wed Eves 6pm-8pm (
 closed on holidays).\n\nThe spiritual practice of labyrinth walking is an a
 ncient\, yet ever new\, experience of prayer and meditation.  As we enter t
 he sacred path we attempt to open ourselves to God’s presence through the s
 imple act of mindful walking.  \n \nAs we follow the twists and turns of th
 e path\, we see that we are not on a maze — with wrong turns and dead ends 
 — but on an unbroken path to the center\, the symbolic heart of God.  There
  we rest in deeper stillness as we take a moment to center ourselves.  Then
 \, as you are ready to return to the world\, you follow the same path back 
 out — refreshed and renewed to listen more deeply for God in your daily lif
 e.  The labyrinth is different for different people\, and at different time
 s.  But one thing remains the same: you have taken a step closer to God.  (
 See "Going Deeper" page for more info and a video on walking the labyrinth.
 )\n \nAt First Congregational Church we open the labyrinth to the wider com
 munity so that all may experience it.  It is open each Wednesday evening fr
 om 6pm-8pm.  You may also request to walk the labyrinth at other times by c
 alling the church office to see if it is free (973-744-4856).
LAST-MODIFIED:20170809T151930Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:No Labyrinth Walk today! (Will resume next week)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
