CREATED:20171107T183345Z
DESCRIPTION:This year\, FCC's Giving Tree is once again focusing on two won
 derful charities: Eva’s Village and Bridges Outreach. These two charitable 
 non-profits do wonderful work\, and have been carefully vetted to assure th
 at gifts and donations are going directly to clients\, and programs.  Quest
 ions? Contact Janifer Marsh at jbreezy778@gmail.com\n\nEVA'S VILLAGE COLLEC
 TION: We’ll be collecting (unwrapped)  gifts on Sundays November 26 and Dec
 ember 3rd for Eva's Village: \nProvide a  homeless parent with the chance t
 o shop for their child this Christmas at Eva's Village. Eva’s Village is a 
 shelter for mothers and children in Paterson. This Christmas FCC will contr
 ibute to their "Christmas Store."  Please shop for a gift for a child (age 
 infant through 17—Please note: Gifts for teens are especially needed! ) you
  may bring in as many as you like. The gifts remain UNWRAPPED. Eva's villag
 e sets up a "store" that enables parents to pick out a gift for their child
 ren.  It is wrapped and delivered on Christmas Eve by Eva's Village.\n\nHel
 p BRIDGES OUTREACH FOR THE HOMELESS keep people in fresh socks and underwea
 r! (Details about dates of Bridges Outreach collection coming soon!)\nThis 
 year we will once again be helping Bridges Outreach for the homeless provid
 e new\, clean\, packaged underwear and socks for their clients -- one of th
 eir most consistent need. \n\nA box will be set up later in November in the
  Guild Room by the Giving Tree to put your donations in. You can drop your 
 gifts off before worship or during coffee hours.\n\n\n\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20171107T183345Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:The Giving Tree Christmas gifts collection
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
