UID:02gr5ne7jgtc9dp4chvs458mf8@google.com
CREATED:20180328T145630Z
DESCRIPTION:<br><p><span>April's book club selection\, <i>Little Fires Ever
 ywhere</i>\, has been hailed as "an utterly engrossing\, often heartbreakin
 g\, deeply empathetic experience"which will "give you pause and help you th
 ink differently about humanity and this country’s current state of affairs"
  (<i>New York Times\; San Francisco Chronicle</i>). <b>&nbsp\;</b></span> <
 br></p><p><span>In the idyllic suburb of Shaker Heights\, Ohio\, a guiding 
 principle is playing by the rules\, and no one embodies this spirit more th
 an Elena Richardson.&nbsp\; But when Mia Warren - an enigmatic artist and s
 ingle mother - and her daughter Pearl rent a home from the successful Richa
 rdsons\, all four Richardson children are drawn to the mother-daughter pair
  whose mysterious past and disregard for the status quo threaten to upend t
 he carefully ordered community. &nbsp\;</span></p><p>&nbsp\;<span>When old 
 friends of the Richardsons attempt to adopt a Chinese-American baby\, a cus
 tody battle erupts that dramatically divides the town -- and puts Mia and E
 lena on opposing sides.&nbsp\; Suspicious of Mia and her motives\, Elena is
  determined to probe Mia's past.&nbsp\; But her obsession will come at unex
 pected and devastating costs. &nbsp\;</span></p><p><i><span>Little Fires Ev
 erywhere</span></i><span>&nbsp\;explores the weight of secrets\,the nature 
 of art and identity\, and the ferocious pull of motherhood – and the danger
  of believing that following the rules can avert disaster.&nbsp\;(Synopsis 
 adapted from <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=http%3A%2F%2Fgoodreads.c
 om&amp\;sa=D&amp\;usd=2&amp\;usg=AFQjCNHsqxcsUCbzkv2HfyKJKfp_5mAT1A" target
 ="_blank">goodreads.com</a>).&nbsp\;</span></p><p><b>&nbsp\;</b><span><b>FC
 C Member Mike Magdalenski is facilitating this group and willbe hosting at 
 his home.</b>&nbsp\; We'd like to make it both a literary and social evenin
 g\, so we invite contributions of light refreshments and beverages as well.
 &nbsp\; We'll gather at&nbsp\;<span>7:00</span>&nbsp\;with some social time
  and begin&nbsp\;<span>book</span>&nbsp\;discussion at 7:30<span>pm</span>.
 &nbsp\;<br><br><b>Please contact Mike to RSVP&nbsp\;<u>by Tuesday\, April 2
 4th</u>:</b> </span><a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https%3A%2F%2Ffir
 stcongmontclair.us6.list-manage.com%2Ftrack%2Fclick%3Fu%3D62bf2ca744bdb8b46
 fa1a7788%26id%3De1f7c99029%26e%3D382909cbb3&amp\;sa=D&amp\;usd=2&amp\;usg=A
 FQjCNEDvbfE_weNrr--Udbd4a8yWVs_Lw" target="_blank"><span>michael.magdalensk
 i@gmail.com</span></a></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20180416T173544Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:FCC Book Club conversation and refreshments (email for location)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:First Congregational Church Montclair
