DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20231122T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20231122T130000
DTSTAMP:20260401T043557Z
UID:0qm2j5fm5eed7d3pm2jae3vqfj@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20231122T110000
CREATED:20230512T174108Z
DESCRIPTION:<u>PLEASE NOTE:</u> <span>Due to the Thanksgiving holiday we wi
 ll not havea labyrinth walk on Wednesday Nov 22. The labyrinth will be open
  again on Nov29 from 11am-1pm.<br></span><br><span> </span><br><span>______
 __________________________________ </span><br><span> </span><br><span>Weekl
 y: Wednesdays 11am-1pm in the Sanctuary</span><span> </span><span></span><i
 > </i><p></p><p><span>Take your soul for a walk on the labyrinth.  We are p
 leased to offer labyrinth walks each Wednesday in the mid-day as a chance t
 o connect with your soul in our beautiful sanctuary. <br><br>The labyrinth 
 is an ancient spiritual tool \, a mode of “walking prayer” that invites us 
 to go deeper in our walk with God.  Our labyrinth\, modeled on one in Chart
 es Cathedral in France\, sits as the center of our Sanctuary\, a constant m
 etaphor for our spiritual lives.  Just like the labyrinth\, our lives are n
 ot linear\, but filled with twists and turns.  Sometimes we make great prog
 ress\, and other times we feel we are going backwards.  But if we trust in 
 the path we will find ourselves in the center -- the heart of God.</span> <
 br></p><p><span>All are welcome to take their souls out for a healing walk.
 .. no experience necessary! </span> <a href="https://baristanet.com/2014/03
 /labyrinth-walk-meditation-satisfies-soul/"><span>Check out this lovely wri
 te up on Baristanet</span></a> <span>from the Spring 2014.</span> <br></p><
 p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=2&v=D453ajtWb74&feat
 ure=emb_logo"><span>Watch this video</span></a> <span>to find out more abou
 t walking the labyrinth. If you’ve never done so come out one Wednesday eve
 ning and give it a try. It is a wonderful way to nourish your soul and spen
 d some quiet time in prayer or meditation.</span></p><u></u>
LAST-MODIFIED:20231120T164134Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:No Labyrinth Walk this Wednesday (due to Thanksgiving)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
