CREATED:20221122T190923Z
DESCRIPTION:<i><b><span>Sometimes the Christmas season is not always merry.
 </span></b></i><html-blob>&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\; </html-blob><html-blob><p><
 span>Christmas is a time of joy and celebration. Yet for many of us the hol
 iday season brings a sense of sadness&nbsp\;as well. Separation from loved 
 ones through distance or death\, personal illness\, difficult memories\, lo
 neliness\, or financial stress can make this "season of light" a time of da
 rkness.</span> <br></p><p><span>At 7:30pm on Wednesday\, December 21\, the 
 longest night of the year\, we will offer a special worship service to ackn
 owledge the difficult emotions of the season and offer a place for blessing
  and comfort. There will be a contemplative service of readings and music\,
  a time to pray individually with our pastors\, receive an anointing with o
 il\, and an opportunity to walk the labyrinth.<br><br><i><b>You are not alo
 ne. Join us to find a moment of comfort and hope.&nbsp\; All are welcome.</
 b></i><span><i><span><span></span><span></span></span></i></span></span></p
 ></html-blob>
LAST-MODIFIED:20221214T233743Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:The Longest Night Service\, Wednesday\, December 21\, 7:30pm
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
