UID:q9p8gcmt5nj2narudbbr1jd11g@google.com
CREATED:20160531T213858Z
DESCRIPTION:Book Discussion: Wednesday\, June 29\, 7:30pm at Union Congrega
 tional Church - 176 Cooper Avenue\, Montclair\, NJ\n\nBook:  "Not in God’s 
 Name: Confronting Religious Violence" by Rabbi Jonathan Sacks \n\nJoin us f
 or a fascinating discussion on the roots of religious violence between the 
 three Abrahamic faiths.  By looking anew at the book of Genesis\, with it’s
  foundational stories of Judaism\, Christianity and Islam\, Rabbi Sacks off
 ers a radical rereading of many of the Bible’s seminal stories about siblin
 g rivalry: Cain and Abel\, Isaac and Ishmael\, Jacob and Esau\, Joseph and 
 his brothers\, Racheal and Leah.\n\nWe’ll join with our brothers and sister
 s at Union Congregation as we explore how better to understand religious ex
 tremism and glimpse some solutions.  Questions?  See Rev. Ann.  Books can b
 e ordered online or found in most bookstores. \n
LAST-MODIFIED:20160531T213858Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Book Discussion (at Union Congregational Church - 176 Cooper Ave.\,
  Montclair))
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
