CREATED:20230201T182931Z
DESCRIPTION:<span>Elder law is an emerging practice area that is largely fu
 eled by the aging baby boomer population and their children.Misleading as i
 t may be\, elder law seeks to address the complex intersection between esta
 te planning\, government benefits planning and long-term care planning by a
 ddressing issues affecting <i>both the old and young alike</i>.<br><br>Donn
 y Dennison\, a member of FCC and local elder law attorney will lead an inte
 ractive discussion about elder law and what individuals should consider bot
 h for themselves and their loved ones as we age. Topics will include the im
 portance of establishing an estate plan\, spotting issues that may be resol
 ved through the use of counsel\, and how to prepare ourselves and our famil
 ies for the inevitable through the use of trusts and planned lifetime givin
 g. <b>The event will also be livestreamed.</b></span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230201T183000Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:A Conversation on Elder Law for All Generations\, 12 noon (in the s
 anctuary following worship)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
