DESCRIPTION:<b>FCC Volunteers Needed to Make and Deliver Bagged Lunches to 
 Newark\, Saturday September 1</b><br><br>Bridges Outreach needs our help to
  provide lunches to underprivileged NJ communities this summer. Bridges Out
 reach is a volunteer organization that delivers thousands of lunches every 
 year to NY and NJ neighborhoods in need. FCC has volunteered to provide 250
  non-perishable brown bag lunches to communities in Newark on Saturday Sept
 . 1. <br><br><u><b>There are multiple ways you can help us meet this goal</
 b></u><br><br><b>1. Donations</b>: We need specific food donations and <b>w
 ill be accepting donations until&nbsp\;&nbsp\; Sunday August 19.</b> We nee
 d the following items:<br><ul><li>Chicken or tuna salad packets with cracke
 rs (not a can of tuna or chicken)</li><li>Fruit cups</li><li>Unsweetened ap
 plesauce</li><li>Nutri-grain type fruit or cereal bars</li><li>Small bags o
 f nuts\, trailmix\, goldfish\, or pretzels</li><li>Brown paper lunch bags</
 li><li>Monetary donations are also acceptable</li></ul><br><b>2. Lunch Pack
 ers:</b> <b>We need volunteers to help pack the lunches on Sunday August 26
  in after church in the Guild Room.&nbsp\;&nbsp\; </b><br><br><b>3. Lunch D
 eliverers: </b>We need up to 15 volunteers to help deliver the lunches to c
 ommunities in Newark on the morning of Saturday Sept. 1. The entire event w
 ill likely go from approximately 8:30 AM – 12:30 PM. <br><br><b>Please cont
 act Faith in Action Chair\, Jose Ortiz\, at 201-314-1342 or at <a href="mai
 lto:Josemortiz1981@gmail.com" target="_blank">Josemortiz1981@gmail.com</a> 
 to volunteer or learn more about how you can help. </b>
LAST-MODIFIED:20180807T162443Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Lunch packers needed for Bridges run brown bag lunches - after wors
 hip in the Guild Room
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
