DESCRIPTION:Take your soul for a walk on the labyrinth\, Wed Eves 6pm-8pm (
 closed for month of August and holidays).\n\nThe spiritual practice of laby
 rinth walking is an ancient\, yet ever new\, experience of prayer and medit
 ation.  As we enter the sacred path we attempt to open ourselves to God’s p
 resence through the simple act of mindful walking.  \n \nAs we follow the t
 wists and turns of the path\, we see that we are not on a maze — with wrong
  turns and dead ends — but on an unbroken path to the center\, the symbolic
  heart of God.  There we rest in deeper stillness as we take a moment to ce
 nter ourselves.  Then\, as you are ready to return to the world\, you follo
 w the same path back out — refreshed and renewed to listen more deeply for 
 God in your daily life.  The labyrinth is different for different people\, 
 and at different times.  But one thing remains the same: you have taken a s
 tep closer to God.  (See "Going Deeper" page for more info and a video on w
 alking the labyrinth.)\n \nAt First Congregational Church we open the labyr
 inth to the wider community so that all may experience it.  It is open each
  Wednesday evening from 6pm-8pm.  You may also request to walk the labyrint
 h at other times by calling the church office to see if it is free (973-744
 -4856).\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20160607T150338Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Labyrinth Walks 6-8pm Wednesdays (closed for holidays & month of Au
 gust)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:First Congregational Church Montclair
X-SOURCE-URL:https://fccmontclair.org/upcoming-events-at-fcc/
