DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20191225T200000
DTSTAMP:20260401T043557Z
UID:2oc1ocno77sbsb8meogom43gdj@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20191225T180000
CREATED:20190620T202538Z
DESCRIPTION:Take your soul for a walk on the labyrinth\, Wed Eves 6pm-8pm (
 closed on holidays).<br><br>The spiritual practice of labyrinth walking is 
 an ancient\, yet ever new\, experience of prayer and meditation.  As we ent
 er the sacred path we attempt to open ourselves to God’s presence through t
 he simple act of mindful walking.  <br>&nbsp\;<br>As we follow the twists a
 nd turns of the path\, we see that we are not on a maze — with wrong turns 
 and dead ends — but on an unbroken path to the center\, the symbolic heart 
 of God.  There we rest in deeper stillness as we take a moment to center ou
 rselves.  Then\, as you are ready to return to the world\, you follow the s
 ame path back out — refreshed and renewed to listen more deeply for God in 
 your daily life.  The labyrinth is different for different people\, and at 
 different times.  But one thing remains the same: you have taken a step clo
 ser to God.  (See <a href="https://fccmontclair.org/walk-the-labyrinth/" ta
 rget="_blank">"Worship/Walk the Labyrinth"</a> tab on our website for more 
 info and a video on walking the labyrinth.)<br>&nbsp\;<br>At First Congrega
 tional Church we open the labyrinth to the wider community so that all may 
 experience it.  It is open each Wednesday evening from 6pm-8pm from Septemb
 er - June.  You may also request to walk the labyrinth at other times by ca
 lling the church office to see if it is free (973-744-4856).
