CREATED:20150209T164839Z
DESCRIPTION:The season of Lent is a time for going deeper into our faith jo
 urney and coming to terms with our struggles and our yearning for God.  It 
 is a time of reflection that prepares us for the drama of Holy Week and the
  glory of Easter Sunday.  We begin with a special service to invite us into
  the depth of the season.  Through song and prayers and times of silence we
  will share the ritual of the imposition of ashes\, a symbol of our mortali
 ty and sinfulness\, as well as experience the hope and unity of Holy Commun
 ion.  Our regular Wednesday Labyrinth walk will end at 8pm and we will begi
 n our worship service then.  If you are new to our tradition and have never
  been to and Ash Wednesday service\, we encourage you to share it with us. 
  
LAST-MODIFIED:20150209T164839Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Ash Wednesday Service\, 8pm
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:First Congregational Church Montclair
X-SOURCE-URL:https://fccmontclair.org/upcoming-events-at-fcc/
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20200902T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20200902T130000
RRULE:FREQ=WEEKLY;WKST=SU;UNTIL=20210310T045959Z
DTSTAMP:20260401T043557Z
UID:0u6sd7c0hphen05e0eev91fnjd@google.com
CREATED:20210714T163746Z
DESCRIPTION:<span>Weekly: Wednesdays 11am-1pm in the Sanctuary</span><span>
  </span><br><span>AND <u> </u></span><br><span><u>FIRST Saturday </u>of eac
 h month: 11am-1pm</span><i> </i><p><b><span>(There will be no labyrinth wal
 k during the  month of August)</span></b><br></p><p><span>Take your soul fo
 r a walk on the labyrinth.  We are pleased to offer labyrinth walks each We
 dnesday in the mid-day as a chance to connect with your soul in our beautif
 ul sanctuary. <br><br><b>Social distancing will be observed with one walker
  at a time on the labyrinth and specially designated pews for prayer and me
 ditation. We look forward to welcoming you back.</b></span> <br></p><p><spa
 n>The labyrinth is an ancient spiritual tool \, a mode of “walking prayer” 
 that invites us to go deeper in our walk with God.  Our labyrinth\, modeled
  on one in Chartes Cathedral in France\, sits as the center of our Sanctuar
 y\, a constant metaphor for our spiritual lives.  Just like the labyrinth\,
  our lives are not linear\, but filled with twists and turns.  Sometimes we
  make great progress\, and other times we feel we are going backwards.  But
  if we trust in the path we will find ourselves in the center -- the heart 
 of God.</span> <br></p><p><span>All are welcome to take their souls out for
  a healing walk... no experience necessary! </span> <a href="https://barist
 anet.com/2014/03/labyrinth-walk-meditation-satisfies-soul/" target="_blank"
 ><span>Check out this lovely write up on Baristanet</span></a> <span>from t
 he Spring 2014.</span> <br></p><p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?ti
 me_continue=2&v=D453ajtWb74&feature=emb_logo" target="_blank"><span>Watch t
 his video</span></a> <span>to find out more about walking the labyrinth. If
  you’ve never done so come out one Wednesday evening and give it a try. It 
 is a wonderful way to nourish your soul and spend some quiet time in prayer
  or meditation.</span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20210714T164109Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Weekly Labyrinth Walks\, Wednesdays 11am-1pm & and FIRST Saturday o
 f each month (same time)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
