CREATED:20190306T200926Z
DESCRIPTION:<br><br>During our Saturday evening gatherings\, the Undergroun
 d Church travels back to our earliest Christian roots.&nbsp\; We seek to re
 capture the excitement and community of Jesus' early followers through wors
 hip that is simple yet profound\, communal yet personal\, comforting yet in
 spiring.&nbsp\; We live the questions much as Jesus' friends did as they so
 ught ways to transform the world through the simple acts of a shared and lo
 ving community.<br><br><b>We will gather at the home of Deb and Julie Matz-
 Rees - -&nbsp\; please RSVP to Julie</b> at <a href="mailto:juliemarie.matz
 @gmail.com" id="ow837" __is_owner="true">juliemarie.matz@gmail.com</a> and 
 join us in the transformative power of opening hearts to the Holy Spirit an
 d to each other.<br><br><br><u><b>Need a ride?</b></u>&nbsp\; "The Undergro
 und Church&nbsp\; Express" will meet you in the FCC parking lot and drive y
 ou to our meeting place\, and drive you back after our gathering!&nbsp\; Ju
 st be in the parking lot behind the church at 4:15PM and a member of the Un
 derground Church family will be there to greet you.
LAST-MODIFIED:20190306T200927Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Underground Church March 16\, 5pm  (please RSVP for location)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
