DESCRIPTION:<p><span><em>“To meditate is to discover new possibilities\, to
  awaken the capacities each of us has to live more wisely\, more lovingly\,
  more compassionately\, and more fully.”</em><br>- Jack Kornfield\, <em>Med
 itation for Beginners</em></span></p><p><span><u><strong>Dates:</strong></u
 > <b>March 5\, 12\, 19\, and 26</b> (Each Saturday in March)</span></p><p><
 span><u><strong>Time:</strong></u>&nbsp\; 12 noon to 1 p.m.</span></p><p><s
 pan><u><strong>Where</strong></u>: The Guild Room</span></p><p><span><u><st
 rong>What you’ll learn:</strong></u> What mindfulness is (and isn’t) • Mind
 fulness of the breath • Mindfulness of the body • Mindfulness of thinking •
  How to bring mindfulness beyond meditation into daily life</span></p><p><s
 pan><u><strong>Teacher:</strong></u> Sondra Wolfer\, FCC member and student
  meditation teacher. (Training with the Greater Good Science Center at the 
 University of California\, Berkeley.) </span></p><p><em><span>This class ho
 nors the Buddhist &amp\; Asian roots of mindfulness but these teachings and
  practices are secular and open to all.&nbsp\;</span></em></p>
