UID:6hhbd0lpurbbklhu2k2k6fsve5@google.com
CREATED:20200408T165802Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Our next book club selection is the short novel\, <strong>Th
 e Summer Book\, by Tove Jansson</strong>\, which was recommended in The New
  York Times last week in an article about "books that bring comfort": An el
 derly artist and her six-year-old granddaughter while away a summer togethe
 r on a tiny island in the gulf of Finland. Gradually\, the two learn to adj
 ust to each other's fears\, whims and yearnings for independence\, and a fi
 erce yet understated love emerges - one that encompasses not only the summe
 r inhabitants but the island itself\, with its mossy rocks\, windswept firs
  and unpredictable seas.</p><p>Full of brusque humour and wisdom\, The Summ
 er Book is a profoundly life-affirming story. Tove Jansson captured much of
  her own experience and spirit in the book\, which was her favourite of the
  novels she wrote for adults. This new edition sees the return of a Europea
 n literary gem - fresh\, authentic and deeply humane.</p><p>For convenience
  and given the closure of libraries\, there's a full pdf available online.&
 nbsp\; Google "Summer Book Tove Jansson pdf".&nbsp\; The first match has a 
 string of numbers that begins with 67...&nbsp\; Hit "The Summer Book" below
  it\, and it automatically launches the PDF.&nbsp\; You can also call Watch
 ung Books\, in Montclair\, between 10am-2pm\, give them your credit card in
 fo and they will then leave (any book) in a bag outside their backdoor for 
 pickup between the same hours. &nbsp\;<br>&nbsp\;<br>FCC Member Mike Magdal
 enski is facilitating this group.&nbsp\; Instructions will be sent out in a
 dvance as to how to easily download Zoom. <u><strong>Please contact Mike to
  RSVP by Monday\, April 13th:</strong></u> <a href="mailto:michael.magdalen
 ski@gmail.com"><span>michael.magdalenski@gmail.com</span></a></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20200408T165802Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:FCC Book Club Conversation\, 7pm Via Zoom (RSVP by 4/13)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
