DESCRIPTION:\nThe season of Lent is a time for going deeper into our faith 
 journey and coming to terms with our struggles and our yearning for God. It
  is a time of reflection that prepares us for the passion of Holy Week and 
 the glory of Easter Sunday.\n\nWe begin with a special Ash Wednesday servic
 e. Through song and prayers and times of silence we will share the ritual o
 f the imposition of ashes\, a symbol of our mortality and sinfulness\, as w
 ell as experience the hope and unity of Holy Communion.\n\nOur regular Wedn
 esday Labyrinth walk will end at 8pm and we will begin our worship service 
 then.\n\n\nThis is a deeply meaningful way to begin the season.  If you are
  new to our tradition and have never been to an Ash Wednesday service\, we 
 encourage you to share it with us.
LAST-MODIFIED:20190306T183558Z
LOCATION:40 S Fullerton Ave\, Montclair\, NJ 07042\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Ash Wednesday Service\, 8pm in the Sanctuary
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
