CREATED:20190306T184752Z
DESCRIPTION:Please join us on March 10th\, when FCC welcomes sculptor Rev. 
 Charles McCollough\, the artist who created the beautiful beatitudes sculpt
 ures in our sanctuary.&nbsp\; During this special presentation immediately 
 after worship\, he’ll discuss his inspiration for the beatitudes series of 
 sculptures\, and how they represent the complex relationship between Jesus 
 and the values of empire.<br><br>Come and listen as Rev. McCollough talks a
 bout the intersection of socio-political\, theological and interpersonal th
 emes. <b>He will also be offering his latest book\, called\, Picture This\,
  </b>which explores his experience as an artist with dyslexia and how he le
 arned to use pictures to help him communicate.&nbsp\; <b>This will also be 
 the special day that we will unveil a new\, powerful sculpture that Rev. Mc
 Collough is lending to FCC</b>\,&nbsp\; that depicts the crucifixion carved
  from a single elm tree. Save the date on your calendars\, and mark the con
 nection card in your bulletin to let us know you’ll be attending.
LAST-MODIFIED:20190306T184752Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Conversation with the Sculptor  March 10 at FCC\, following worship
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
