UID:0r3qbtiik8r85q4kohp9naqu62@google.com
CREATED:20190125T222543Z
DESCRIPTION:As is our tradition we will feed both our bodies and souls with
  a soul food meal\, a brief time of worship and then an amazing night of po
 etry.&nbsp\; <b>Poets and lovers of poetry are equally welcome to present. 
 Bring a copy of a favorite poem by a Black poet or select one to read from 
 the poems that will be on hand.&nbsp\;</b> <b>We also welcome original poem
 s related to our Black History month theme.</b> If you don't want to get on
  stage no worries we need an adoring audience as well!<br>&nbsp\;<br>Last y
 ear we had a full house for this amazing night of celebration through poetr
 y and we hope you can join us!&nbsp\; Please RSVP (and if you are bringing 
 a food contribution) by going to: <a href="http://www.tinyurl.com/poetrymes
 sychurch">www.tinyurl.com/poetrymessychurch </a><br><br>Donations and food 
 contributions welcome\, but not necessary. All are welcome!<br>Please conta
 ct Kathleen Korgen at korgenk@gmail.com if you have any questions <br><br><
 br><u><b>Messy Church FAQs:</b></u><br><br>What is&nbsp\;Messy&nbsp\;Church
 ?&nbsp\;Messy&nbsp\;church&nbsp\;is a time to join together with FCC friend
 s for a meal\, a brief time of prayer and singing\, and socializing. <br>&n
 bsp\;<br>What can I expect?&nbsp\;This is a low key event so there will be 
 time for plenty of socializing\, dinner\, brief group singing and prayer (w
 ords to songs provided or taught)\, and an activity.&nbsp\;&nbsp\; <br>&nbs
 p\;<br>Who can come to&nbsp\;Messy&nbsp\;Church?:&nbsp\;Everyone is welcome
  at&nbsp\;Messy&nbsp\;Church! Friends and members of FCC\, friends of frien
 ds\, young and old\, outgoing or shy\; you get the idea. This is an easy ev
 ent to invite friends to who maybe are curious about FCC but aren't ready t
 o attend a Sunday service. All are welcome!<br>&nbsp\;<br>Do I have to RSVP
  to attend?&nbsp\;RSVPing does help us know how much food to order but in t
 he event that you can join us last minute and you haven't been able to RSVP
 \, you are still welcome!<br>&nbsp\;<br>What can I bring?:&nbsp\;We will pr
 ovide the main course (fried chicken this month). By clicking onto the Sign
  Up Genius link above you can sign up to bring a salad\, dessert or other s
 ide dish. Homemade and store bought sides are equally welcome. If bringing 
 a side is not something you can do - no worries\, join us either way.
LAST-MODIFIED:20190125T222543Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Messy Church - 2nd annual Black History Month in poetry celebration
 !
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:First Congregational Church Montclair
