CREATED:20161011T211850Z
DESCRIPTION:Messy Church\, October 26! - - 6-8 pm in the Guild Room. \nPlea
 se go to www.tinyurl.com/messychurchOct26 for signup sheet and to RSVP.\n\n
 As we gear up to do the challenging work of addressing privilege and racism
  in our society\, we'd like to start by having some fun that also allows us
  to get to know more about each other. \n\nOctober's Messy Church will be s
 ponsored by the Privilege Task Force. We will come together to share a meal
  and prayer and then have a round robin\, musical chairs-type event meant t
 o foster deeper connection by sharing some basic information with each othe
 r (like where we grew up\, what we do for fun\, how we ended up at FCC\, et
 c.) This is a way that we can all get to know each other a little better as
  we prepare to do work in January that promises to stretch our minds and he
 arts. We hope to see you there!\n\n(To offset meal costs\, we are requestin
 g a suggested donation of $5 per person\, max of $20 per family.) \n\nWHAT 
 IS MESSY CHURCH?\n\nMessy Church is an informal and unstructured (“messy”) 
 evening each month that brings our community together mid-week for a simple
  dinner\, an opportunity to work together to create a stronger community wi
 thin and outside our church walls\, or simply just be.\n\nWe will provide d
 inner\, a brief and informal worship experience\, and either an activity or
  an opportunity to serve our community.  You come and go as you like\, part
 icipating in whatever way you see fit.  This is a great way to offer friend
 ship and share in God’s love in a fun\, informal way.\n \n So take a break 
 from the mid-week stress\, and recharge yourself with us!\n  \n \n
LAST-MODIFIED:20161017T211422Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Messy Church
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
