CREATED:20160125T203924Z
DESCRIPTION:Ash Wednesday Service \nFebruary 10th at 8pm\n\nThe season of L
 ent is a time for going deeper into our faith journey and coming to terms w
 ith our struggles and our yearning for God. It is a time of reflection that
  prepares us for the passion of Holy Week and the glory of Easter Sunday. W
 e begin with a special Ash Wednesday service. Through song and prayers and 
 times of silence we will share the ritual of the imposition of ashes\, a sy
 mbol of our mortality and sinfulness\, as well as experience the hope and u
 nity of Holy Communion. Our regular Wednesday Labyrinth walk will end at 8p
 m and we will begin our worship service then. This is a deeply meaningful w
 ay to begin the season.  If you are new to our tradition and have never bee
 n to and Ash Wednesday service\, we encourage you to share it with us. 
LAST-MODIFIED:20160125T203924Z
LOCATION:First Congregational Church\, 40 South Fullerton Avenue\, Montclai
 r\, NJ\, 07042
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Ash Wednesday Service\, 8pm
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
