DESCRIPTION:<b>The location will be 12 Park Street in Bloomfield (click sig
 nup link below for details). </b><br><br><br>The Interfaith Hospitality Net
 work (IHN) helps temporarily homeless families in Essex County get back on 
 their feet.&nbsp\; Families stay in local churches and synagogues and have 
 meals\, companionship\, and overnight supervision provided by volunteers fr
 om the congregations as they rebuild their lives.&nbsp\; This March the loc
 ation will be 12 Park Street in Bloomfield (a house owned by Park United Me
 thodist Church.)&nbsp\;&nbsp\; <br><br><br>We are recruiting for volunteers
  to staff the various shifts through the online sign-up tool.&nbsp\; Just c
 lick on the link below\, see what shifts are available\, make your selectio
 n and hit "submit."<br><br><br>If you have any questions\, please contact o
 ur FCC IHN Coordinator\, Sarah Grigg\, at (862)238-2784 or <a href="mailto:
 sfeliciano1@gmail.com" id="ow1209" __is_owner="true">sfeliciano1@gmail.com<
 /a>. Many shifts are available -- if you've been waiting\, now's your time!
 <br><br><a href="https://www.signupgenius.com/go/4090545abab2ba02-ihnmarch"
  id="ow1213" __is_owner="true">CLICK HERE TO SIGN UP!</a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20190306T202159Z
LOCATION:12 Park St\, Bloomfield\, NJ 07003
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Help FCC serve local homeless families through IHN\, March 26\, 28 
 & 30th
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
