UID:jlg23rdh4u1dp8is9a0egh6r7b@google.com
CREATED:20220615T175410Z
DESCRIPTION:<b><html-blob><span>The labyrinth will be closed for the summer
 . Please do visit starting September 7!</span></html-blob></b><br><b><html-
 blob><span>&nbsp\;</span></html-blob></b><br><html-blob><span><br></span></
 html-blob><br><html-blob><span><u><b>Reopening September:&nbsp\;</b></u>&nb
 sp\;</span></html-blob><br><html-blob><span>Weekly: Wednesdays 11am-1pm in 
 the Sanctuary</span><span> </span><span></span><i> </i><p></p><p><span>Take
  your soul for a walk on the labyrinth.&nbsp\; We are pleased to offer laby
 rinth walks each Wednesday in the mid-day as a chance to connect with your 
 soul in our beautiful sanctuary.&nbsp\;<br><br><b>We will be observing curr
 ent recommended Covid precautions. We look forward to welcoming you back.</
 b></span> <br></p><p><span>The labyrinth is an ancient spiritual tool \, a 
 mode of “walking prayer” that invites us to go deeper in our walk with God.
 &nbsp\; Our labyrinth\, modeled on one in Chartes Cathedral in France\, sit
 s as the center of our Sanctuary\, a constant metaphor for our spiritual li
 ves.&nbsp\; Just like the labyrinth\, our lives are not linear\, but filled
  with twists and turns.&nbsp\; Sometimes we make great progress\, and other
  times we feel we are going backwards.&nbsp\; But if we trust in the path w
 e will find ourselves in the center -- the heart of God.</span> <br></p><p>
 <span>All are welcome to take their souls out for a healing walk... no expe
 rience necessary!&nbsp\;</span> <a href="https://baristanet.com/2014/03/lab
 yrinth-walk-meditation-satisfies-soul/"><span>Check out this lovely write u
 p on Baristanet</span></a> <span>from the Spring 2014.</span> <br></p><p><a
  href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=2&v=D453ajtWb74&feature=
 emb_logo"><span>Watch this video</span></a> <span>to find out more about wa
 lking the labyrinth. If you’ve never done so come out one Wednesday evening
  and give it a try. It is a wonderful way to nourish your soul and spend so
 me quiet time in prayer or meditation.</span></p></html-blob>
LAST-MODIFIED:20220615T175904Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Labyrinth closed July & August
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
