CREATED:20160201T160043Z
DESCRIPTION:Wed Eves\, February 3—March 16\, 7:30pm at Union Baptist Church
 \, \n12-14 Midland Avenue\, Montclair\n\nHosted by Union Baptist church\, t
 his bible study invites a variety  of Montclair faith communities  — black\
 , white\, Jewish\, Christian and Muslim — to come together to explore the i
 ntersection between racial justice and scriptures.  Rev. Ann will be leadin
 g the study on February 24 on the role of prophetic imagination.  Let’s bui
 ld bridges together! ALL ARE WELCOME!\n\nFebruary 3\nThe Role and Function 
 of the Bible in the Founding of America\nRev. Cambpell Singleton\, III\, Un
 ion Baptist Church\n\nFebruary 10\nThe History of Race in America and the P
 sychological Effect of Racism\nBonnie Berman Cushing\, LCSW\, \nNorth Jerse
 y Chapter of the AntiRacist Alliance\n\nFebruary 17\nRace\, Guns\, and Sacr
 ed Texts in America\nRabbi Elliott Tepperman\, Bnai Keshet Synagogue\n\nFeb
 ruary 24\nThe Role of Prophetic Imagination in Societal Tranformation\nREV.
  ANN RALOSKY\, First Congregational Church\n\nMarch 2\nIdeological Power an
 d Race Relations\nRev. Dr. Paul Leggett\, Grace Presbyterian Church\n\nMarc
 h 9\nViolence in Sacred Texts and Society\nMr. Fariddudin Frederick Johnson
 \, Intersections International\n\nMarch 16\nBiblical Justice\, Wholeness an
 d Leadership\nRev. Dr. Bernadette Glover Williams\, St. Paul Baptist Church
 \n
LAST-MODIFIED:20160201T160433Z
LOCATION:Union Baptist Church\, 12-14 Midland Avenue\, Montclair\, NJ
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:2016 Interfaith Bible Study On Race\, Justice and Liberation AT UNI
 ON BAPTIST CHURCH
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
