DESCRIPTION:The Interfaith Hospitality Network (IHN) helps temporarily home
 less families in Essex County get back on their feet.&nbsp\; Families stay 
 in local churches and synagogues and have meals\, companionship\, and overn
 ight supervision provided by volunteers from the congregations as they rebu
 ild their lives.&nbsp\; <b>This November the location will be 12 Park Stree
 t in Bloomfield (a house owned by Park United Methodist Church.)</b>&nbsp\;
  <br><br>We are recruiting for volunteers to staff the various shifts!&nbsp
 \; First Congregational will be volunteering to help on November 20 and 24 
 this year. <br><br><a href="https://www.signupgenius.com/go/4090545abab2ba0
 2-ihnnovember">You can CLICK HERE to sign up</a> for opportunities to help 
 with contributing a meal\, clean up\, children's activities or overnight su
 pervision (if you sign-up for the overnight shift please bring a pillow and
  a blanket.—air mattresses will be provided.)&nbsp\;&nbsp\; <br><br><br>As 
 volunteers we provide food\, conversation\, and for the children\, games or
  help with homework.&nbsp\; <br><br>Contact our IHN Coordinator\, Sarah Fel
 iciano\, at <a href="mailto:sfeliciano1@gmail.com">sfeliciano1@gmail.com</a
 >\,&nbsp\; if you have any questions.
LAST-MODIFIED:20181106T205852Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Help Serve  Local Homeless Families Through IHN—Nov 20 &24 ....at 1
 2 Park Street in Bloomfield
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
