  at 7:00pm for our next FCC&nbsp\;Book&nbsp\;Club&nbsp\;conversation and re
 freshments.</b><br><b>“The Overstory\,”</b>&nbsp\;by National Book Award wi
 nner Richard Powers (his twelfth novel\,) is a book for all readers who des
 pair of humanity’s self-imposed separation from the rest of creation and wh
 o hope for the transformative\, regenerating possibility of a homecoming. I
 f the trees of this earth could speak\, what would they tell us?&nbsp\;"Lis
 ten. There’s something you need to hear." (synopsis from Goodreads.com) <br
 ><br><b>FCC Member Mike Magdalenski is facilitating this group at his home.
 </b>&nbsp\; We'd like to make it both a literary and social evening\, so we
  invite pot luck contributions or light refreshments and beverages as well.
 &nbsp\; We'll gather at&nbsp\;7:00&nbsp\;with some social time and begin&nb
 sp\;book&nbsp\;discussion at 7:30pm. <br><br><b>Please contact Mike to RSVP
 &nbsp\;by Sunday\, February 17th: </b><br><a href="mailto:michael.magdalens
 ki@gmail.com" target="_blank">michael.magdalenski@gmail.com</a>
