CREATED:20200828T215625Z
DESCRIPTION:Take your soul for a walk on the labyrinth.  <span>We are pleas
 ed to offer labyrinth walks each Wednesday in mid-day as a chance to connec
 t with your soul in our beautiful sanctuary. <br><b><br>Social distancing w
 ill be observed with one walker at a time on the labyrinth and specially de
 signated pews for prayer and meditation. </b>We look forward to welcoming y
 ou back. </span><br><br>The spiritual practice of labyrinth walking is an a
 ncient\, yet ever new\, experience of prayer and meditation.  As we enter t
 he sacred path we attempt to open ourselves to God’s presence through the s
 imple act of mindful walking.  <br> <br>As we follow the twists and turns o
 f the path\, we see that we are not on a maze — with wrong turns and dead e
 nds — but on an unbroken path to the center\, the symbolic heart of God.  T
 here we rest in deeper stillness as we take a moment to center ourselves.  
 Then\, as you are ready to return to the world\, you follow the same path b
 ack out — refreshed and renewed to listen more deeply for God in your daily
  life.  The labyrinth is different for different people\, and at different 
 times.  But one thing remains the same: you have taken a step closer to God
 .  (See <a href="https://fccmontclair.org/walk-the-labyrinth/" target="_bla
 nk">&quot\;Worship/Walk the Labyrinth&quot\;</a> tab on our website for mor
 e info and a video on walking the labyrinth.)<br> <br>At First Congregation
 al Church we open the labyrinth to the wider community so that all may expe
 rience it.
LAST-MODIFIED:20210714T162432Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Re-Opens with new time: Weekly Labyrinth Walks\, Wednesdays 11am-1p
 m in the Sanctuary
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
