DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20230226T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20230226T160000
RRULE:FREQ=WEEKLY;WKST=SU;UNTIL=20230403T035959Z;BYDAY=SU
DTSTAMP:20260401T043557Z
UID:5a5ald3qdrhpg1alrs385bi425@google.com
CREATED:20230217T212540Z
DESCRIPTION:<table> <tbody><tr>  <td><table>   <tbody><tr>    <td>    <tabl
 e>     <tbody><tr>      <td>      <table>       <tbody><tr>        <td><br>
 </td><td><p><b>Lent is a time for letting go and dropping the distractions 
 that keep us from experiencing God.</b><span><b> </b><br></span></p><p>We o
 ften seek to strengthen our spiritual discipline during the Lenten season b
 ut are caught in the fast current of modern life and are kept away from exp
 eriencing the present moment. Mindfulness Mediation is a practice that can 
 often remedy the ongoing neurosis we create by living in today's world and 
 add a level of focus and discipline to our Christian spiritual practice. Mi
 ndfulness can be defined as “bringing our attention to the present moment b
 y observing our thoughts without bias”. </p><p><b>During this Lenten season
  Samuel Ralosky will be offering a six-week course on the foundations of Mi
 ndfulness Meditation practice</b> as taught by the Kagyu Lineage of Tibetan
  Buddhism and the Dharma Moon Association.<span> <br></span></p><p>The clas
 s will combine mindfulness mediation and labyrinth walking each session. </
 p><p>Samuel Ralosky recently earned his teacher certificate in Mindfulness 
 Meditation\, accredited by Dharma Moon and the Tibet House Foundation.The c
 ourse that Sam undertook was led by David Nichtern who is a Senior Teacher 
 in the Kagyu lineage of Tibetan Buddhism and was a student of Chogyam Trung
 pa Rinpoche. Samuel Ralosky has had a disciplined practice of both meditati
 on and the martial art Kendo for thirteen years and integrates these practi
 ces into his everyday life as a Paraprofessional working with special needs
  children and practice as an artist.<span> <br></span></p><p>This class is 
 for first time meditators\, as well as experienced practitioners - ALL ARE 
 WELCOME!</p></td>       </tr>      </tbody></table>      </td>     </tr>   
  </tbody></table></td>   </tr>  </tbody></table>  </td> </tr></tbody></tabl
 e>
