UID:1qva0rkc06h3jpqpii5ag69ska@google.com
CREATED:20171207T204434Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><span lang="en-US">An interfaith Hanukkah gathering in solid
 arity with the&nbsp\; undocumented community.<span>&nbsp\; </span><span></s
 pan></span></p><p><span lang="en-US">Thursday\, December 14<span>&nbsp\; </
 span>7:30pm <b>at Bnai Keshet synagogue - 99 S. Fullerton Avenue\, Montclai
 r.</b> <span></span></span></p><p><span lang="en-US">Announcing our commitm
 ent to offering physical sanctuary for individuals facing deportation.<span
 ></span></span></p><span lang="en-US">The celebration of Hanukkah is a time
  of rededication.<span>&nbsp\; </span>Join us as we help Bnai Keshet dedica
 te their sanctuary for the housing of undocumented immigrants in need.<span
 >&nbsp\; </span>We will share in a brief ceremony of songs\, prayers and wo
 rds of welcome as we join our congregations together in solidarity.<span>&n
 bsp\; </span>FCC\, Bnai Keshet and the Unitarian Universalist Congregation 
 at Montclair have joined to create</span><span lang="en-US"> "The Montclair
  Sanctuary Alliance."</span><span lang="en-US"> <span></span></span><p><spa
 n lang="en-US">In the weeks ahead we will be working with our neighbors at 
 Bnai Keshet to ready their apartment\, create care networks and rapid respo
 nse teams to support our undocumented neighbors.<span>&nbsp\; </span>If you
  are interested in being a part of this team\, please contact Jack Cuffari 
 at </span><a href="mailto:jack@cuffari.com"><span lang="en-US">jack@cuffari
 .com</span></a><span lang="en-US">.<span></span></span></p><p><span lang="e
 n-US">&nbsp\;<span></span></span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20171207T204434Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Rededicating the Sanctuary to  “Sanctuary” - at Bnai Keshet 
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
