DESCRIPTION:The first read of the new FCC Book Club is a searing and profou
 nd Southern odyssey by Jesmyn Ward.\n\nIn her first novel since her Nationa
 l Book Award winning Salvage the Bones\, this singular American writer brin
 gs the archetypal road novel into rural twenty-first-century America. Drawi
 ng on Morrison and Faulkner\, The Odyssey and the Old Testament\, Ward give
 s us an epochal story\, a journey through Mississippi's past and present th
 at is both an intimate portrait of a family and an epic tale of hope and st
 ruggle. Ward is a major American writer\, multiply awarded and universally 
 lauded\, and in Sing\, Unburied\, Sing she is at the height of her powers.\
 n\nSing\, Unburied\, Sing grapples with the ugly truths at the heart of the
  American story and the power\, and limitations\, of the bonds of family. R
 ich with Ward's distinctive\, musical language\, Sing\, Unburied\, Sing is 
 a majestic new work and an essential contribution to American literature. (
 Reviewed by Goodreads)\n\nFCC Member\, Mike Magdalenski\, is facilitating t
 his group.  We'd like to make it both a literary and social evening\, so we
  invite contributions of light refreshments and beverages as well.  We'll b
 egin at 7:30 with some social time and begin book discussion at 8pm.   \nTo
  RSVP please contact Mike at michael.magdalenski@gmail.com .
LAST-MODIFIED:20171010T162811Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:FCC Book Club Discussion\, 7:30 in the Guild Room
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
