CREATED:20170605T171016Z
DESCRIPTION:Sanctuary isn't just a place\, it's a movement!\n\nNorthern NJ 
 training and info session on FCC becoming a "Sanctuary Congregation"\nJune 
 8\, 7-9pm in the Guild Room\n\nThe deportation of undocumented immigrants i
 n our area has increased dramatically in the last four months.  The vast ma
 jority of those at risk have lived in our communities for over a decade wor
 king\, raising families\, paying taxes and contributing to the life of our 
 communities.  Many would be deported back to situations that endanger their
  lives.  First Congregational Church\, synagogue Bnai Keshet and St. Luke's
  Episcopal Church are seeking to join together to create a "sanctuary suppo
 rt" team to assist our neighbors in need.\n\nFaith in New Jersey is hosting
  a Sanctuary Congregation information and training session this month to ed
 ucate\, activate and equip clergy and congregations to move into action to 
 resist policies that would target undocumented immigrants or other marginal
 ized groups in our state.  \n\nRichard Morales\, Esq\, from the PICO Nation
 al Network is our special guest and he will able to answer all your sanctua
 ry questions from a faith\, legal\, and practical perspective. We will we b
 e talking about rapid response teams and how clergy can help advance powerf
 ul sanctuary city resolutions/ordinances/police directives. It is important
  we all stay united during these difficult times and learn how to continue 
 taking collective actions against injustice. Feel free to invite anyone you
  think might also be interested in this session.\nThis event will be open t
 o the public\, so registration is encouraged.  \n\nTo register go to: www.t
 inyurl.com/sanctuaryjune8 . \nQuestions?  Please see Rev. Ann or Jack Cuffa
 ri (jack@cuffari.com)\n\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20170607T161716Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:"Sanctuary Congregation" info session - 7 to 9:30pm in Guild Room
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
