DESCRIPTION:<span>The word"tenebrae" comes from the Latin word meaning "sha
 dows." On this night we confront the shadow side of our faith.  Through con
 templative sacred music\, scripture story\, reflection and  hymns we will s
 hare the story of Jesus' trial\, crucifixion and death. As the light grows 
 dimmer we are invited to stand at the foot of the cross and share this powe
 rful experience.  This service is one of the most meaningful of our church 
 year. <br><br><b><i><span>You are asked to wear black clothing to this serv
 ice. </span></i></b><br><br> Please join us as we walk this final mile toge
 ther.</span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230328T150221Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Good Friday Service of Tenebrae\, 7:30pm
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
