UID:7ojdoheocsffpc6ia92av52kbu@google.com
CREATED:20221228T170231Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><span><b><span>Join FCC in a special conversation on January
  11 @ 7:30pm on Zoom.</span>&nbsp\; </b></span><br><span>&nbsp\;COVID-19 ha
 s pushed us indoors\, away from each other\, and online more than ever. It 
 has also highlighted our increasing reliance on technology\, which is often
  at odds with the public good. Bringing humanity back to tech requires one 
 human at a time talking about how to change that. We stay connected through
  social media but at what cost?&nbsp\; Join us for a discussion exploring t
 he effects of social media use on our mental health\, democracy\, and discr
 imination\, and the way forward--together.</span> <br></p><p><span><b>WATCH
  THE MOVIE "</b></span><a href="https://www.thesocialdilemma.com/"><u><span
 ><b>THE SOCIAL DILEMMA</b></span></u></a><span><b>" ON NETFLIX</b></span></
 p><p><span>The centerpiece of our discussion will be the Netflix film "The 
 Social Dilemma"\, a powerful documentary-drama hybrid which&nbsp\;explores 
 the dangerous human impact of social networking\, with tech experts soundin
 g the alarm on their own creations.&nbsp\; <u>We will watch the documentary
  independently prior to our January 11 conversation.</u><br><b>Then\, on Ja
 nuary 11 we will gather on Zoom to discuss the film together.&nbsp\;</b></s
 pan></p><p><a href="https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86253272997?pwd=UHJqczdCeU1xW
 GxHZzlhTUZadE85UT09#success"><b><span>CLICK HERE FOR <u>ZOOM LINK</u>.</spa
 n></b></a></p><p><span>Dr. Jill Del Pozzo\, a new member of First Congregat
 ional Church\, will&nbsp\;be guiding us through this discussion.</span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20221228T170307Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:What's Your Relationship with Social Media? Conversation on "The So
 cial Dilemma"
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
