DESCRIPTION:An Evolution in Christianity: A Three Part Study <br>&nbsp\;<br
 >We are experiencing a new spiritual awakening\, Dr. Diana Butler Bass argu
 es in Christianity After Religion. Having spent her career as a professor o
 f history\, culture\, and the politics of religion\, Dr. Bass explores the 
 data that shows religious affiliation plummeting and interest in spirituali
 ty on the rise. She concludes there is great possibility in the midst of th
 is instability.&nbsp\; A fresh\, vital faith is emerging. <br>&nbsp\; <br>W
 hether you are trying to get the pulse of our religious moment\, interested
  in how we got here\, or wondering where we're going next\, join us.<br><br
 >This exploration will be led by Associate Pastor\, Rev. John Rogers. Readi
 ng Diana Butler Bass's <u>Christianity After Religion</u> is recommended bu
 t not required. <b>We will meet in the FCC Guild Room. </b><br>&nbsp\; <br>
 Wednesday\, October 9th - 7:30 pm - 9:00 pm<br>Wednesday\, October 23rd - 7
 :30 pm - 9:00 pm<br>Wednesday\, October 30th - 7:30 pm - 9:00 pm <br>&nbsp\
 ; <br>RSVPs are helpful for planning!&nbsp\; Contact Rev. John at <a href="
 mailto:john.rogers28@gmail.com">john.rogers28@gmail.com</a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20191018T165839Z
SEQUENCE:2
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:"An Evolution in Christianity" - A Three Part Study\, Oct 9\,16\,23
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
