UID:15lmhrjeoc4u9a5kuo3h7hcgko@google.com
CREATED:20170306T233212Z
DESCRIPTION:Kindred Spirits for Racial Justice:\n\nKSRJ is a special initia
 tive of First Congregational Church whose mission is to promote dialogue\, 
 learning and deepen relationships between our diverse community.  Throughou
 t the year we will be offering various experiences and programs to help us 
 challenge systems of racial injustice\, oppression and prejudice in society
  and in the church.\n\nIn addition to special events\, we will be engaging 
 in regular monthly conversations on race on the following dates: February 2
 5\, March 25\, April (to be confirmed)\, May 20 and June 24.\n\nSATURDAY SE
 SSIONS:\n\nFor several months we have been preparing for an important serie
 s of conversations as a church family about the realities of racial injusti
 ce and white privilege in our culture and our lives. Now we are ready to ju
 mp in!\n\nHow will we start?\n\nWhile our goal is to engage in deep convers
 ations across racial lines\, our first two sessions will reflect the distin
 ctly different work that white people and people of color must do to prepar
 e ourselves. For the first two sessions only\, February 25 and March 25\, w
 e will be working  in two distinct groups:\n \nA) a group for people who wi
 sh to understand their white privilege\nand\nB) a group for people who expe
 rience systems as a person of color.\n \nBoth of these groups will be led b
 y our Moderator\, Emily Jones McGowan\, but each group will have separate w
 ork to do as we engage in questions of privilege and injustice from our own
  racial perspectives.  Depending on how you identity yourself\, you are fre
 e to choose what group you would like to  join.  Group A will meet at 9am a
 nd Group B will meet at 10:30. Each group will meet for 90 minutes.\n\nSay 
 again?\n\nFor the first two meetings only (Feb 25 & March 25):\n9am -- Whit
 e Privilege group will meet in the Guild Room\n10:30am -- People of Color g
 roup will meet in the Guild Room\n\nAfter that\, the two groups will come t
 ogether for the meetings in April\, May and June.\n\nFor more information\,
  please see Rev. Ann or John Rogers\, or email Emily Jones McGowan at ejone
 smcgowan@gmail.com 
LAST-MODIFIED:20170306T233212Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Kindred Spirits for Racial Justice "Saturday Sessions"
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
