UID:moa6ap5t32im6do3l9akqdmurg@google.com
CREATED:20160627T150848Z
DESCRIPTION:Intergenerational Conversations:  Race\, Culture \nand Beyond—T
 hursday June 30\, 6:30-9pm at FCC (Guild Room)\n\nThe Montclair Branch of t
 he NAACP and First Congregational Church of Montclair have joined together 
 to present the first of a  series of intergenerational community conversati
 ons on race\, culture\, and class.  The event will feature individuals repr
 esenting different perspectives presenting their views in a facilitated for
 um before an audience of Montclair residents\, who will get a chance to wei
 gh in during a Question and Answer session.\n\n“Our objective is to provide
  an instructive opportunity for people of different ages\, generations\, ra
 ces\, and classes to share their views\, opinions\, and experiences – and t
 o hear the views and opinions of others\,” said James Harris\, First VP and
  Chair of the Education  Committee of the Montclair Branch of the NAACP\, a
 nd the person who brought the concept for the event to the attention of Rev
 erend Ann Ralosky\, Senior Minister of FCC.\n\n“We are excited to partner w
 ith the NAACP\, and serve as host for this first conversation\,” Rev. Ralos
 ky said. “Montclair is such a  wonderfully diverse community\, and there is
  so much we can learn from one another. Hopefully all that’s needed is a sa
 fe and structured environment for people to speak up and be heard. We see t
 his as a chance to engage in positive community building!”  — The public is
  absolutely invited!\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20160627T150918Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Intergenerational Conversations:  Race\, Culture  and Beyond
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
