DESCRIPTION:Ash Wednesday Service\, March 1 at 8pm\n\nThe season of Lent is
  a time for going deeper into our faith journey and coming to terms with ou
 r struggles and our yearning for God. It is a time of reflection that prepa
 res us for the passion of Holy Week and the glory of Easter Sunday. \n\nWe 
 begin with a special Ash Wednesday service. Through song and prayers and ti
 mes of silence we will share the ritual of the imposition of ashes\, a symb
 ol of our mortality and sinfulness\, as well as experience the hope and uni
 ty of Holy Communion. \n\nOur regular Wednesday Labyrinth walk will end at 
 8pm and we will begin our worship service then. \n\nThis is a deeply meanin
 gful way to begin the season.  If you are new to our tradition and have nev
 er been to an Ash Wednesday service\, we encourage you to share it with us.
 \n
LAST-MODIFIED:20170213T183209Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Ash Wednesday Service\, 8pm in the FCC Sanctuary
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
