CREATED:20180608T165044Z
DESCRIPTION:June's book club selection is <b><i>“News of the World”</i> by 
 Paulette Jiles.</b>&nbsp\; An old\, itinerant <br>veteran travels through n
 orth Texas in the 1870's reading the "news of the world" to eager audiences
 .&nbsp\; He begrudgingly takes on the job of bringing a young orphan girl\,
  whose <br>frontier parents were killed by Kiowa raiders\, to her relatives
  in southern Texas.&nbsp\; The <br>journey is fraught with difficulties\, f
 rom threatening outlaws\, to the challenges of trying to communicate with J
 ohanna\, who has lost the English language and is resistant to returning to
  her relatives.&nbsp\; But these two souls\, both who've been "othered" in 
 very different ways\, form a poignant bond that is tested by a final terrib
 le dilemma.&nbsp\; As the novel's description says: "unfolding in gorgeous 
 prose\, 'News of the World' is a vivid portrait that captures a beautiful a
 nd hostile land\, and a masterful exploration of the boundaries of family\,
  <br>responsibility\, honor\, and trust." &nbsp\; <br><br><b>FCC Member Mik
 e Magdalenski is facilitating this group\, and <u>Tracey Stephens will be h
 osting at her home.</u></b>&nbsp\; We'd like to make it both a literary and
  social evening\, so we <br>invite contributions of light refreshments and 
 beverages as well.&nbsp\; We'll gather at&nbsp\;7:00&nbsp\;with some social
  time and begin&nbsp\;book&nbsp\;discussion at 7:30pm. <br><br><b>Please co
 ntact Mike to RSVP&nbsp\;by Sunday\, June 17th: <a href="mailto:michael.mag
 dalenski@gmail.com">michael.magdalenski@gmail.com</a></b>
LAST-MODIFIED:20180608T165044Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:FCC Book Club conversation and refreshments\, June 20th\, 7pm 
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
