UID:07ao1gdpi7lt100ftdhe7ufnps_R20210904T150000@google.com
CREATED:20210714T163116Z
DESCRIPTION:<span><span><u>FIRST Saturday </u>of each month: 11am-1pm</span
 ></span>&nbsp\;<br>AND<span>&nbsp\;</span><br><span>Weekly: Wednesdays 11am
 -1pm in the Sanctuary</span><p><span></span><i> </i></p><p><u><b><span>(The
 re will be no labyrinth walk during the&nbsp\; month of August)</span></b><
 /u><br></p>    <br><p><span>Take your soul for a walk on the labyrinth.&nbs
 p\; We are pleased to offer labyrinth walks each Wednesday in the mid-day a
 s a chance to connect with your soul in our beautiful sanctuary.&nbsp\;<br>
 <br><b>Social distancing will be observed with one walker at a time on the 
 labyrinth and specially designated pews for prayer and meditation. We look 
 forward to welcoming you back.</b></span> <br></p><p><span>The labyrinth is
  an ancient spiritual tool \, a mode of “walking prayer” that invites us to
  go deeper in our walk with God.&nbsp\; Our labyrinth\, modeled on one in C
 hartes Cathedral in France\, sits as the center of our Sanctuary\, a consta
 nt metaphor for our spiritual lives.&nbsp\; Just like the labyrinth\, our l
 ives are not linear\, but filled with twists and turns.&nbsp\; Sometimes we
  make great progress\, and other times we feel we are going backwards.&nbsp
 \; But if we trust in the path we will find ourselves in the center -- the 
 heart of God.</span> <br></p><p><span>All are welcome to take their souls o
 ut for a healing walk... no experience necessary!&nbsp\;</span> <a href="ht
 tps://baristanet.com/2014/03/labyrinth-walk-meditation-satisfies-soul/"><sp
 an>Check out this lovely write up on Baristanet</span></a> <span>from the S
 pring 2014.</span> <br></p><p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_c
 ontinue=2&v=D453ajtWb74&feature=emb_logo"><span>Watch this video</span></a>
  <span>to find out more about walking the labyrinth. If you’ve never done s
 o come out one Wednesday evening and give it a try. It is a wonderful way t
 o nourish your soul and spend some quiet time in prayer or meditation.</spa
 n></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20210905T020810Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Labyrinth Walks\, FIRST Saturday of each month AND Wednesdays 11am-
 1pm  (same time)
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
