DTEND:20180414T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260401T043557Z
UID:45rc7k2i9qatqk6tvq6f9t0ama@google.com
CREATED:20180410T191446Z
DESCRIPTION:<br><b><br>Bowling for Columbine</b><h3></h3><span>Political do
 cumentary filmmaker MichaelMoore explores the circumstances that lead to th
 e April 20\, 1999 <b><span>Columbine High School massacre</span></b>in Jeff
 erson County\, Colorado and\, more broadly\, the proliferation of guns andt
 he high homicide rate in America.In light of current events such as thetrag
 edies at the <b><span>PulseNight Club</span></b> in Orlando\, Florida\, <b>
 <span>Marjory Stoneman</span></b> <b><span>Douglas High School</span></b> i
 nParkland\, Florida\, and gun related incidents that occur on an everyday b
 asisthroughout the United States\, make this movie as relevant today as it 
 was whenoriginally released back in 2002.&nbsp\;<br><br>One of the movie’s 
 more thought provoking theories is that the fear thatresides within the Ame
 rican public\, the fear that causes much of its gunviolence is\, for lack o
 f a better word\, the <b><span>fear of the “other" -- essentially\, anyone 
 who isnot white --&nbsp\;&nbsp\;connecting racism and fear.</span></b>We&nb
 sp\;see&nbsp\;this through the purposeful creation of fear of blackAmerican
 s in&nbsp\;US media coverage.&nbsp\; Noting that we treasure urbanlegends d
 esigned to make us fearful of strangers\, Moore notices how TV newsfocuses 
 on local violence ("If it bleeds\, it leads") and says thatwhile the murder
  rate is down 20 percent in America\, TV coverage of violentcrime is up 600
  percent.<br><br>After watching this thought provoking\, often both hilario
 us and sorrowful film\,you will leave with more questions than answers.&nbs
 p\;<br><br></span><b><span>Join us for an evening ofgreat cinema&nbsp\;and 
 great discussion!</span></b>
LAST-MODIFIED:20180410T191446Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Kindred Spirits for Racial Justice Movie Night: Bowling For Columbi
 ne 7pm in the Guild Room
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
