  of NJ - \nSunday Nov 20 from 9-2pm in the FCC Parking Lot!\n\nHelp a local
  family have a happy Thanksgiving by contributing to our food drive for the
  Community Food Bank of New Jersey.  CFB provides food for area soup kitche
 ns\, shelters and food pantries throughout northern NJ.  \n\nHere’s what th
 ey need:  Non-perishable nutritious food (be sure to check the expiration d
 ate!)  Canned vegetables and fruits\, Thanksgiving-appropriate canned goods
 \, Stuffing\, Boxed mashed potatoes\, Pasta\, Cereals\, Peanut butter\, Tun
 a fish.  They also need FROZEN turkeys!  \n\nFood can be brought to FCC any
 time up to November 20 (before 2pm) and collected in the Narthex.. ..HOWEVE
 R FROZEN TURKEYS CAN ONLY BE BROUGHT ON NOVEMBER 20 and will be collected i
 n the back parking lot!\n
