DESCRIPTION:<b>Next FCC&nbsp\;Book&nbsp\;Club&nbsp\;conversation and refres
 hments—April 4\, 7:00pm&nbsp\;</b><br><br>Our next selection is the literar
 y thriller&nbsp\;<i><b>Station Eleven</b></i>&nbsp\;by Emily St. John Mande
 l.&nbsp\;&nbsp\;<br><br>An audacious\, darkly glittering novel set in the e
 erie days of civilization's collapse\,&nbsp\;Station Eleven&nbsp\;tells the
  spellbinding story of a   Hollywood star\, his would-be savior\, and a nom
 adic group of    actors roaming the scattered outposts of the Great Lakes r
 egion\, risking everything for art and humanity.<br><br>Sometimes terrifyin
 g\, sometimes tender\,&nbsp\;Station Eleven&nbsp\;tells a story about the r
 elationships that sustain us\, the ephemeral nature of fame\, and the beaut
 y of the world as we know it. <br><br><b>FCC Member Mike Magdalenski is fac
 ilitating this group at his home.</b>&nbsp\; We like to make it both a lite
 rary and social evening\, so we invite pot luck contributions or light refr
 eshments and beverages as well.&nbsp\; We'll gather at&nbsp\;7:00&nbsp\;wit
 h some social time and begin&nbsp\;book&nbsp\;discussion at 7:30pm.&nbsp\;<
 br><br><b>Please contact Mike to RSVP&nbsp\;by Monday\, April 1st</b>:&nbsp
 \;<a href="mailto:michael.magdalenski@gmail.com" id="ow1033" __is_owner="tr
 ue">michael.magdalenski@gmail.com</a>&nbsp\;
LAST-MODIFIED:20190326T175130Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Next FCC Book Club conversation and  refreshments  (Please RSVP for
  location)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
