DESCRIPTION:Talking\, Listening and Connecting \n\nThe Montclair Branch of 
 the NAACP and First Congregational Church of Montclair have joined together
  to present the second of a series of intergenerational community conversat
 ions on race\, culture\, and class. \n\nIn the midst of changing demographi
 cs and expectations\, our community of Montclair has much to say about how 
 the shifts and trends impact our every day lives across racial\, generation
 al and economic boundaries.\n\nThe event will feature individuals represent
 ing different perspectives presenting their views in a facilitated forum be
 fore an audience of Montclair residents\, who will get a chance to weigh in
  during a Question and Answer session.\n\nAll are welcome.  Come join the c
 onversation!\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20161201T201025Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:NAACP/FCC Intergenerational Conversation on "Race and Culture in Mo
 ntclair" Dec 1\, 7:30pm in the Guild Room
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
