CREATED:20230117T155109Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><i><span>Weaving together her own story and the stories of t
 hose she encountered in her life of faith\, Rev. Molly Baskette mines joy f
 rom all the hardest parts of being human. In doing so she reminds us that w
 hatever you are going through\, someone has been there before you\, and fou
 nd meaning in the madness. </span></i><span><br><br>Her new book<u>\, <i><s
 pan>How To Begin When Your World is Ending</span></i></u>\, is a spiritual 
 guide to post-traumatic growth and joy. It can be ordered online.</span></p
 ><p><span>Rev. Molly Phinney Baskette is\, in no particular order\, a mothe
 r\, spouse\, recovering workaholic\, cancer survivor\, adventurous home coo
 k\,and senior minister of First Church Berkeley UCC in Ber(zer)kley\, CA\, 
 nick named the Motley Pew for its tendency to make seatmates of purple-hair
 ed trans activists and Nobel laureates.</span></p><p><span>  <span><strong>
 <a href="https://us02web.zoom.us/j/81632536538?pwd=U2owS2plRXVQMUVQVHl6RVdt
 cVRZZz09">Click here to join us on Zoom!</a></strong></span><br><em><strong
 >You do not need to read the book to participate.</strong></em><b><i><span>
 </span></i></b></span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230120T181229Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Book Discussion on How to Begin When Your World Is Ending - Februar
 y 1st\, 7 pm on Zoom
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
