CREATED:20230512T174108Z
DESCRIPTION:<span>PLEASE NOTE THAT THERE WILL BE NO LABYRINTH WALK TODAY 12
 /27\, DUE TO THE HOLIDAYS.</span><br><span> </span><br><span>WE LOOK FORWAR
 D TO SEEING YOU AGAIN BEGINNING NEXT WEDNESDAY. <br></span><br><span> </spa
 n><br><span>Weekly: Wednesdays 11am-1pm in the Sanctuary</span><span> </spa
 n><span></span><i> </i><p></p><p><span>Take your soul for a walk on the lab
 yrinth.  We are pleased to offer labyrinth walks each Wednesday in the mid-
 day as a chance to connect with your soul in our beautiful sanctuary. <br><
 br>The labyrinth is an ancient spiritual tool \, a mode of “walking prayer”
  that invites us to go deeper in our walk with God.  Our labyrinth\, modele
 d on one in Chartes Cathedral in France\, sits as the center of our Sanctua
 ry\, a constant metaphor for our spiritual lives.  Just like the labyrinth\
 , our lives are not linear\, but filled with twists and turns.  Sometimes w
 e make great progress\, and other times we feel we are going backwards.  Bu
 t if we trust in the path we will find ourselves in the center -- the heart
  of God.</span> <br></p><p><span>All are welcome to take their souls out fo
 r a healing walk... no experience necessary! </span> <a href="https://baris
 tanet.com/2014/03/labyrinth-walk-meditation-satisfies-soul/"><span>Check ou
 t this lovely write up on Baristanet</span></a> <span>from the Spring 2014.
 </span> <br></p><p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=2&v
 =D453ajtWb74&feature=emb_logo"><span>Watch this video</span></a> <span>to f
 ind out more about walking the labyrinth. If you’ve never done so come out 
 one Wednesday evening and give it a try. It is a wonderful way to nourish y
 our soul and spend some quiet time in prayer or meditation.</span></p><u></
 u>
LAST-MODIFIED:20231120T214405Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:No Labyrinth Walk Today - due to the holidays!
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
