CREATED:20180328T144653Z
DESCRIPTION:<span lang="en-US"></span><p align="center"><b><i><span>Moments
  of Grace</span></i></b><span><span></span></span></p><p align="center"><i>
 <span>&nbsp\;What can we do to ease the pain of a hurting world?&nbsp\; Wha
 t if we could become aware of how we can be an instrument of grace in every
  moment?&nbsp\; What if we could find a way to turn mundane tasks into pray
 ers\, lay down our burdens and open ourselves to be of service to others?&n
 bsp\; Journey with us&nbsp\;<span>this Saturday</span>&nbsp\;evening as we 
 delve into the gospel of Mark.&nbsp\; Jesus reminds us that we don't have t
 o "gain the whole world."&nbsp\; And that we should not forfeit our souls.&
 nbsp\;Because authentic souls joined together to intentionally live into mo
 ments of grace can create a powerful energy of healing and wholeness.&nbsp\
 ; </span></i><span><span></span></span></p><p align="center"><i><span>Under
 ground church travels back to our earliest Christian roots.&nbsp\; We seek 
 to recapture the excitement and community of Jesus's early followers throug
 h worship that is simple yet profound\, communal yet personal\, comforting 
 yet inspiring.&nbsp\; We live the questions much as Jesus's friends did as 
 they sought ways to transform the world through the simple acts of a shared
  and loving community.&nbsp\; We invite you to gather with us from 5PM to6:
 30PM go deeper into the beauty of community.&nbsp\; Worship will be informa
 l. We will engage through the reading of sacred texts\, share a simple and 
 blessed communion meal of soup and bread\, and end our evening with "Spirit
 ual Take-Out" .&nbsp\; Please<a href="mailto:juliemarie.matz@gmail.com" tar
 get="_blank"><span></span></a>&nbsp\; join us in the&nbsp\;transformative p
 ower of opening hearts to the Holy Spirit and to each other.&nbsp\;&nbsp\;<
 /span></i><span><span></span></span></p><p align="center"><span><span><br><
 /span></span><i><span></span></i><span><span></span></span></p>&nbsp\;<span
  lang="en-US"><i><span></span></i><span></span></span><p><span lang="en-US"
 >&nbsp\;<span></span></span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20180328T145027Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Underground Church 5pm in the basement of FCC (enter from The Cresc
 ent)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
