 /span> <br></p></span><br>"Reading the Bible Again for the First Time" : <i
 >"This welcome book removes many of the barriers that separate thoughtful p
 eople from the wisdom of the Bible."</i> -Rabbi Harold Kushner <br> <br><sp
 an>Many folks at FCC are inspired by the fresh interpretation of scripture 
 they hear during worship but wonder why it sounds so different.  If this is
  you\, please join us for a thought-provoking exploration in to the scriptu
 res through the book\, <b><u><span><a href="https://firstcongmontclair.us6.
 list-manage.com/track/click?u=62bf2ca744bdb8b46fa1a7788&id=3c5141d050&e=d2d
 6ac503b"><span>Reading the Bible Again for the First Time</span></a> </span
 ></u></b><b><span>by Biblical scholar\, Marcus Borg.  </span></b>Borg offer
 s an accessible and deeply insightful understanding of how to read the Bibl
 e through the lenses of history and metaphor that lets the scripture come a
 live. To order the book\, <a href="https://firstcongmontclair.us6.list-mana
 ge.com/track/click?u=62bf2ca744bdb8b46fa1a7788&id=511bf04c1b&e=d2d6ac503b">
 <span>CLICK HERE.</span></a><span>  </span></span><br><span><span> </span><
 /span><br><b><span>We will cover each chapter over a series of 10 weeks\, <
 u>approximately every other Thursday</u> on Zoom at 7:00pm from </span></b>
 <b><span><b><span>September 28 through February 1. </span></b></span></b><b
 r><b><span><b><span><u>F</u></span></b></span></b><span><b><u>ull Class Sch
 edule</u>: </b>Sept 28\, Oct 12\, Oct26\, Nov16\, Nov30\, Dec7\, Jan4\, Jan
 18\, Feb1\, Feb15</span><p><span></span></p><p><span></span></p><p><span>Wh
 ether this is the first time you've cracked open a bible\, or you've been r
 eading for years\, you are welcome to join us!  Questions? Email Rev. Ann <
 a href="mailto:(acralosky@msn.com)"><span>(</span></a><a href="mailto:acral
 osky@msn.com"><span>acralosky@msn.com</span></a><a href="mailto:(acralosky@
