DESCRIPTION:<p><span>Longest Night Service\, Saturday\, December 21\, 7pm</
 span> <br></p><p><span>Christmas is a time of joy and celebration. Yet for 
 many of us the holiday season brings a sense of sadness and grief as well. 
 Separation from loved ones through distance or death\, loss of a relationsh
 ip\, personal illness\, loneliness\, or financial stress can make this “sea
 son of light” a time of darkness.</span></p><p><span>On Saturday evening\, 
 December 21\, we will offer a special service to acknowledge the difficult 
 emotions of the season and offer a place for blessing and comfort.&nbsp\; T
 here will be a contemplative service of readings and beautiful music\, a ti
 me to pray individually with our pastors\, receive an anointing with oil\, 
 and an opportunity to walk the&nbsp\; labyrinth.&nbsp\; All are welcome to 
 find comfort and hope. </span></p><p>&nbsp\;</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20191211T202558Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Longest Night Service\, 8pm
TRANSP:OPAQUE
