CREATED:20180125T143238Z
DESCRIPTION:<p align="center"><b><span><span>Join us on Thursday\, January 
 25 at 7:00pm for our third FCC Book Club conversation and refreshments.</sp
 an></span></b><span><span></span></span></p><p><span>The next selection of 
 the FCC BookClub\, <i><b><u><span>Prodigal Summer</span></u><span> by Barba
 ra&nbsp\; Kingsolver</span>\,</b></i> has been hailed as "a </span><span>ba
 lance of narrative\, drama\, and ideas [that] weaves together three stories
  of human love within a larger tapestry of . . . the forested mountains and
  struggling small farms of southern Appalachia."&nbsp\;</span><span><span><
 /span></span></p><span> <span>From her outpost in an isolated mountain cabi
 n\, a reclusive wildlife biologist watches a den of coyotes that have recen
 tly migrated into the region. She is caught off-guard by a young hunter who
  invades her most private spaces and confounds her self-assured\, solitary 
 life. On a farm several miles down the mountain\, a bookish city girl turne
 d farmer's wife finds herself unexpectedly marooned in a strange place wher
 e she must declare or lose her attachment to the land that has become her o
 wn. And a few more miles down the road\, a pair of elderly feuding neighbor
 s tend their respective farms and wrangle about God\, pesticides\, and the 
 possibilities of a future neither of them expected.</span></span><p><span><
 span></span><span>Over the course of one humid summer\, these characters fi
 nd their connections to one another and to the flora and fauna with whom th
 ey share a place.&nbsp\;</span><span>&nbsp\;</span><span> (Synopsis adapted
  from&nbsp\;<a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https%3A%2F%2Ffirstcongmo
 ntclair.us6.list-manage.com%2Ftrack%2Fclick%3Fu%3D62bf2ca744bdb8b46fa1a7788
 %26id%3D487a60ab8e%26e%3Dd2d6ac503b&amp\;sa=D&amp\;usd=2&amp\;usg=AFQjCNGk9
 rQAMETlU0iXHki8zpM01Zm8-g" target="_blank"><span>goodreads.com</span></a>).
 &nbsp\;</span></span><span> <span></span></span></p><p align="center"><span
 ><b>&nbsp\; FCC Member Mike Magdalenski is facilitating this group and <u>w
 ill be hosting at his home</u>.&nbsp\;</b>We'd like to make it both a liter
 ary and social evening\, so we invite contributions of light refreshments a
 nd beverages as well.&nbsp\; We'll gather at&nbsp\;7:00&nbsp\;with some soc
 ial time and begin&nbsp\;book&nbsp\;discussion at7:30pm.&nbsp\;</span><span
 ><br><br></span><span>To RSVP\, please contact Mike at </span><span><a href
 ="https://www.google.com/url?q=https%3A%2F%2Ffirstcongmontclair.us6.list-ma
 nage.com%2Ftrack%2Fclick%3Fu%3D62bf2ca744bdb8b46fa1a7788%26id%3D366027953a%
 26e%3Dd2d6ac503b&amp\;sa=D&amp\;usd=2&amp\;usg=AFQjCNFxPPSCtjVq7jhR2ULuX2_a
 rbIF6Q" target="_blank"><span>michael.magdalenski@gmail.com</span></a><span
 ></span></span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20180125T143238Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:FCC Book Group\, 7pm (email for location of meeting)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
