UID:07ao1gdpi7lt100ftdhe7ufnps@google.com
CREATED:20210714T163116Z
DESCRIPTION:<br><br><br><br><br><span><span><u>FIRST Saturday </u>of each m
 onth: 11am-1pm</span></span>&nbsp\;<br>AND<span>&nbsp\;</span><br><span>Wee
 kly: Wednesdays 11am-1pm in the Sanctuary</span><p><span></span><em> </em><
 /p><p><u><b><span>(There will be no labyrinth walk during the&nbsp\; month 
 of August)</span></b></u></p>                                            <b
 r>    <br><p><span>Take your soul for a walk on the labyrinth.&nbsp\; We ar
 e pleased to offer labyrinth walks each Wednesday in the mid-day as a chanc
 e to connect with your soul in our beautiful sanctuary.&nbsp\;<br><br><stro
 ng>Social distancing will be observed with one walker at a time on the laby
 rinth and specially designated pews for prayer and meditation. We look forw
 ard to welcoming you back.</strong></span> <br></p><p><span>The labyrinth i
 s an ancient spiritual tool \, a mode of “walking prayer” that invites us t
 o go deeper in our walk with God.&nbsp\; Our labyrinth\, modeled on one in 
 Chartes Cathedral in France\, sits as the center of our Sanctuary\, a const
 ant metaphor for our spiritual lives.&nbsp\; Just like the labyrinth\, our 
 lives are not linear\, but filled with twists and turns.&nbsp\; Sometimes w
 e make great progress\, and other times we feel we are going backwards.&nbs
 p\; But if we trust in the path we will find ourselves in the center -- the
  heart of God.</span> <br></p><p><span>All are welcome to take their souls 
 out for a healing walk... no experience necessary!&nbsp\;</span> <a href="h
 ttps://baristanet.com/2014/03/labyrinth-walk-meditation-satisfies-soul/"><s
 pan>Check out this lovely write up on Baristanet</span></a> <span>from the 
 Spring 2014.</span> <br></p><p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_
 continue=2&amp\;v=D453ajtWb74&amp\;feature=emb_logo"><span>Watch this video
 </span></a> <span>to find out more about walking the labyrinth. If you’ve n
 ever done so come out one Wednesday evening and give it a try. It is a wond
 erful way to nourish your soul and spend some quiet time in prayer or medit
 ation.</span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20210905T020810Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Weekly Labyrinth Walks\, FIRST Saturday of each month AND Wednesday
 s 11am-1pm  (same time)
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
