DESCRIPTION:The Giving Tree Holiday Toy Drive<br>&nbsp\;<br>MSU Holiday Con
 cert and Toy Drive in FCC Sanctuary\, December 7 at 7pm<br>&nbsp\;<br>MONTC
 LAIR STATE UNIVERSITY SYMPHONIC BAND PRESENTS<br>&nbsp\;<br>A HOLIDAY CONCE
 RT<br><br><i><b><br>Admission is an unwrapped toy or monetary donation</b><
 /i><br>(All proceeds will go to the Valerie Fund) Guest appearance by Santa
  Claus!<br>&nbsp\;<br><br>Enjoy some Christmas cheer and make the holiday b
 righter this year for a child in need!<br>&nbsp\;<br>First Congregational C
 hurch is excited to announce the beginning of our annual toy drive on Sunda
 y November 25 and ending on Sunday December 9.&nbsp\; The toys collected wi
 ll be donated to St. Joseph’s Hospital for Children\, and there are two way
 s you can participate.<br>&nbsp\;<br>The first is to bring an unwrapped gif
 t to donate at the Church guild room under the Christmas tree either during
  regular church hours Monday – Friday (9 AM – 5 PM) or after regular Sunday
  service during coffee hour. The second way you can participate is to bring
  an unwrapped toy as admission to the Montclair State Symphonic Band Christ
 mas Concert in the FCC Sanctuary on Friday December 7\, at 7:00 PM. One unw
 rapped toy will serve as a single admission for the concert.&nbsp\; <br>The
  toys you donate will help make this holiday season extra special for child
 ren in need. <br>&nbsp\;<br><b>FCC will be collecting unwrapped toys in the
  Narthex from November 25 - December 9. </b>
LAST-MODIFIED:20181207T202909Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
