CREATED:20190903T175958Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><span>The Acts of the Apostles</span></p><p><span>Starting o
 n&nbsp\; November 4th\, our Slow Motion Adult Bible Study will start diggin
 g into the Acts of the Apostles. Written by the author(s) of the Gospel of 
 Luke\, the Acts of the Apostles is&nbsp\;a dynamic book that pays attention
  to leadership and conflict issues\, the use of wealth and possessions\, th
 e role of women in the church\, the relationship between the church and the
  state and Christians and civil authorities\, and the challenge of persecut
 ion. Join us for a fascinating journey into this wonderful work.</span></p>
 <p><span> Feel free to come and jump right in. Bring your favorite translat
 ion / paraphrase of the Bible\, and join us!</span><br></p><i>Rev. Jack Cuf
 fari is a member of FCC\, as well as our Spiritual Director in Residence. H
 e currently serves as Interim Pastor at the First Congregational United Chu
 rch of Christ in Haworth\, NJ. </i>
LAST-MODIFIED:20200116T214430Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:NO BIBLE STUDY TODAY! (Will resume Monday evenings 7:30pm in the FC
 C library)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
