UID:3bqnhfh6in67p2c1l7sgfaabev@google.com
CREATED:20231106T223039Z
DESCRIPTION:The activity focuses on gratitude as a key to resilience.Using 
 the words of the Native American Iroquois confederacy: “the original instru
 ctions direct that we who walk about on the Earth are to express a great re
 spect\, an affection\, and a gratitude toward all the spirits which create 
 and support Life. We give a greeting and thanksgiving to the many supporter
 s of our own lives – the corn\, beans\, squash\, the winds\, the sun. When 
 people cease to respect and express gratitude for these many things\, then 
 all life will be destroyed\, and human life on this planet will come to an 
 end.” <span><br></span><p>That says at all. The oldest earth wisdom traditi
 ons identify thanksgiving as key to our survival. Whether you are reading <
 i>Active Hope</i> or not\, come and join us as we dive into gratitude.</p><
 p><span> </span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20231117T192104Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:"Active Hope" Book Discussion Continues\, 7pm in Room 5  (please no
 te date change)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:First Congregational Church Montclair
X-SOURCE-URL:https://fccmontclair.org/upcoming-events-at-fcc/
DTSTART:20190612T230000Z
DTEND:20190613T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260401T043557Z
UID:3mommjpcf360nm7pkeagi2k3cs@google.com
CREATED:20190517T152929Z
DESCRIPTION:<br><b>Join us on Wednesday\, June 12th at 7:00pm for our next 
 FCC Book Club conversation and refreshments.<i><br></i></b><br><b><i><br></
 i></b><br><i>June's book club selection\, <u>Commonwealth</u> by Ann Patche
 tt\, "brings humanity\, humor\, and a disarming affection to lovable\, stru
 ggling characters... Irresistible" </i>(Library Journal)<i>.&nbsp\; </i><b>
 <i><br></i></b><br><br>One Sunday afternoon in Southern California\, Bert C
 ousins shows up at Franny Keating’s christening party uninvited. Before eve
 ning falls\, he has kissed Franny’s mother\, Beverly—thus setting in motion
  the dissolution of their marriages and the joining of two families.<br><br
 >Spanning five decades\, Commonwealth explores how this chance encounter re
 verberates through the lives of the four parents and six children involved.
  Spending summers together in Virginia\, the Keating and Cousins children f
 orge a lasting bond that is based on a shared disillusionment with their pa
 rents and the strange and genuine affection that grows up between them.<br>
 <br>When\, in her twenties\, Franny begins an affair with the legendary aut
 hor Leon Posen and tells him about her family\, the story of her siblings i
 s no longer hers to control. Their childhood becomes the basis for his wild
 ly successful book\, ultimately forcing them to come to terms with their lo
 sses\, their guilt\, and the deeply loyal connection they feel for one anot
 her.<br>Told with equal measures of humor and heartbreak\, Commonwealth is 
 a meditation on inspiration\, interpretation\, and the ownership of stories
 . It is a brilliant and tender tale of the far-reaching ties of love and re
 sponsibility that bind us together. (synopsis from goodreads.com)<br><br><b
 >FCC Member Mike Magdalenski is facilitating this group at his home.&nbsp\;
 </b> We like to make it both a literary and social evening\, so we invite p
 ot luck contributions or light refreshments and beverages as well.&nbsp\; W
 e'll gather at 7:00 with some social time and begin book discussion at 7:30
 pm. <br><br><b>Please contact Mike to RSVP by Sunday\, June 9th: </b><a hre
 f="mailto:michael.magdalenski@gmail.com">michael.magdalenski@gmail.com</a><
 br><br><i>... and stay tuned for the second annual "FCC Big Summer Read"! <
 /i>
LAST-MODIFIED:20190517T152929Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:FCC Book Club conversation and refreshments\, 7pm
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
