UID:0g4cu7i7qu1ceptss2e9kq7j23@google.com
CREATED:20241025T201709Z
DESCRIPTION:<span>Author Jeff Korgen Presents New Graphic Novel\, <i><span>
 Dorothy Day: Radical Devotion</span></i>\, at FCC Montclair.</span><p><span
 ></span><i><span>Dorothy Day: Radical Devotion</span></i><span> introduces 
 readers to the amazing life of Dorothy Day\,reviews her impact on the churc
 h and peace and justice movements\, and provides an informative understandi
 ng of the process of canonization.<br> <br>Jeffry Odell Korgen is a spiritu
 al writer and comics creator with a 32-yearcareer in pastoral ministry. Jef
 f has worked as an educator/trainer in the social Gospel and acting on it\,
  a community organizer\, a youth minister\, led a professional association 
 for diocesan social justice directors\, and after a six-year stint as Execu
 tive Director for Diocesan Planning for the Diocese of Metuchen in central 
 New Jersey\, in 2014\, he founded</span><span> <a href="https://firstcongmo
 ntclair.us6.list-manage.com/track/click?u=62bf2ca744bdb8b46fa1a7788&id=66e2
 217574&e=d2d6ac503b" target="_blank"><span>Korgen Associates</span></a></sp
 an><span>\, a Catholic consulting firm focusing on coaching\, planning\, an
 d evaluation. From 2014-2021 he coordinated the local phase of Dorothy Day’
 s Cause for Canonization for Cardinal Dolan.<br> <br>He is the author of se
 veral books\, including <i><span>Solidarity Will Transform the World: Stori
 es of Hope from Catholic Relief Services\, My Lord and My God!: Engaging Ca
 tholics in Social Ministry\, </span></i>and <i><span>Beyond Empowerment: A 
 Pilgrimage with the Catholic Campaign for Human Development</span></i>\,as 
 well as the newly published <i><span>Dorothy Day: Radical Devotion</span></
 i>.</span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20241108T172200Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Radical Devotion: The Dorothy Day Story\, 7pm in the Guild Room
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
