UID:0qm2j5fm5eed7d3pm2jae3vqfj@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20240626T110000
CREATED:20230512T174108Z
DESCRIPTION:<span><span><span><b><u>Please note:</u> This will be the last 
 Labyrinth Walk until September.  </b></span></span></span><span><br></span>
 <br><span> </span><br><span>Weekly: Wednesdays 11am-1pm in the Sanctuary</s
 pan><span> </span><span></span><i> </i><p></p><p><span>Take your soul for a
  walk on the labyrinth.  We are pleased to offer labyrinth walks each Wedne
 sday in the mid-day as a chance to connect with your soul in our beautiful 
 sanctuary. <br><br>The labyrinth is an ancient spiritual tool \, a mode of 
 “walking prayer” that invites us to go deeper in our walk with God.  Our la
 byrinth\, modeled on one in Chartes Cathedral in France\, sits as the cente
 r of our Sanctuary\, a constant metaphor for our spiritual lives.  Just lik
 e the labyrinth\, our lives are not linear\, but filled with twists and tur
 ns.  Sometimes we make great progress\, and other times we feel we are goin
 g backwards.  But if we trust in the path we will find ourselves in the cen
 ter -- the heart of God.</span> <br></p><p><span>All are welcome to take th
 eir souls out for a healing walk... no experience necessary! </span> <a hre
 f="https://baristanet.com/2014/03/labyrinth-walk-meditation-satisfies-soul/
 " target="_blank"><span>Check out this lovely write up on Baristanet</span>
 </a> <span>from the Spring 2014.</span> <br></p><p><a href="https://www.you
 tube.com/watch?time_continue=2&v=D453ajtWb74&feature=emb_logo" target="_bla
 nk"><span>Watch this video</span></a> <span>to find out more about walking 
 the labyrinth. If you’ve never done so come out one Wednesday evening and g
 ive it a try. It is a wonderful way to nourish your soul and spend some qui
 et time in prayer or meditation.</span></p><u></u>
LAST-MODIFIED:20240529T133815Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Weekly Labyrinth Walks\, Wednesdays 11am-1pm
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
