CREATED:20250627T162257Z
DESCRIPTION:THE LABYRINTH WILL BE ON HIATUS UNTIL SEPTEMBER! <br><span> </s
 pan><br><span>Weekly: Wednesdays 11am-1pm in the Sanctuary</span><span> </s
 pan><span></span><i> </i><p></p><p><span>Take your soul for a walk on the l
 abyrinth.  We are pleased to offer labyrinth walks each Wednesday in the mi
 d-day as a chance to connect with your soul in our beautiful sanctuary. <br
 ><br>The labyrinth is an ancient spiritual tool \, a mode of “walking praye
 r” that invites us to go deeper in our walk with God.  Our labyrinth\, mode
 led on one in Chartes Cathedral in France\, sits as the center of our Sanct
 uary\, a constant metaphor for our spiritual lives.  Just like the labyrint
 h\, our lives are not linear\, but filled with twists and turns.  Sometimes
  we make great progress\, and other times we feel we are going backwards.  
 But if we trust in the path we will find ourselves in the center -- the hea
 rt of God.</span> <br></p><p><span>All are welcome to take their souls out 
 for a healing walk... no experience necessary! </span> <a href="https://bar
 istanet.com/2014/03/labyrinth-walk-meditation-satisfies-soul/" target="_bla
 nk"><span>Check out this lovely write up on Baristanet</span></a> <span>fro
 m the Spring 2014.</span> <br></p><p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch
 ?time_continue=2&v=D453ajtWb74&feature=emb_logo" target="_blank"><span>Watc
 h this video</span></a> <span>to find out more about walking the labyrinth.
  If you’ve never done so come out one Wednesday evening and give it a try. 
 It is a wonderful way to nourish your soul and spend some quiet time in pra
 yer or meditation.</span></p><u></u>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250627T162257Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Last Labyrinth Walk for the season + Blessing Ceremony\, 11am-1pm
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
