 an></p><p><span>For many\, the Lord's Prayer is quite familiar\, but new re
 velations emerge when  we explore it through the original language of Arama
 ic. Each week\,we'll excavate the treasure load of spiritual meaning and fe
 eling behind each phrase\, reflect on our intentions when we recite it\, li
 sten to the sound musically\, and share our thoughts together.  <br><br>Rev
 . Karla Wrona\, will facilitate this conversation which will fold in many n
 ative language translations\, thoughts\, and intentions -  all about reachi
 ng towards the mystery of God. As we share our wisdom and light - our souls
  grow stronger and brighter!  </span></p><p><b><span>Rev. Karla Wrona</span
 ></b><span> is a member of FCC community - and FCC choir! She's an </span><
 span>Interfaith Minister ordained through One Spirit Alliance\, with over 2
 0 years of experience in holistic healing and a life of spiritual explorati
 on. </span></p><p><span><a href="https://firstcongmontclair.us6.list-manage
 .com/track/click?u=62bf2ca744bdb8b46fa1a7788&id=898620608c&e=d2d6ac503b" ta
 rget="_blank"><span>CLICK HERE FOR ZOOM LINK</span></a></span></p><span>Mee
 ting ID: 861 5139 5498       Passcode: 559188</span>
