CREATED:20240124T150444Z
DESCRIPTION:<b><span>Grab a vegan bite at coffee hour and then come watch a
 t the labyrinth in the sanctuary.  </span></b><br><b><span> </span></b><br>
 T<span>his 1 hour documentary tells the story of NY Port Authority’s attemp
 t to turn 10\,000 acres of rural New Jersey into an airport\, and the grass
 roots movement (starting at a local high school) that defeated the project.
  In 1960\, the area was designated a National Wildlife Refuge (one of 560 t
 hrough the US Fish &amp\; Wildlife Service). The film includes interviews\,
  historic film footage and beautiful cinematography of the Great Swamp toda
 y.</span>
