DESCRIPTION:<u></u><span>Weekly: Wednesdays 11am-1pm in the Sanctuary</span
 ><span> </span><span></span><i> </i><p></p><p><span>THE LABYRINTH WILL BE C
 LOSED TODAY. We will return next Wednesday. <br></span></p><p><span>Take yo
 ur soul for a walk on the labyrinth.  We are pleased to offer labyrinth wal
 ks each Wednesday in the mid-day as a chance to connect with your soul in o
 ur beautiful sanctuary. <br><br>The labyrinth is an ancient spiritual tool 
 \, a mode of “walking prayer” that invites us to go deeper in our walk with
  God.  Our labyrinth\, modeled on one in Chartes Cathedral in France\, sits
  as the center of our Sanctuary\, a constant metaphor for our spiritual liv
 es.  Just like the labyrinth\, our lives are not linear\, but filled with t
 wists and turns.  Sometimes we make great progress\, and other times we fee
 l we are going backwards.  But if we trust in the path we will find ourselv
 es in the center -- the heart of God.</span> <br></p><p><span>All are welco
 me to take their souls out for a healing walk... no experience necessary! <
 /span> <a href="https://baristanet.com/2014/03/labyrinth-walk-meditation-sa
 tisfies-soul/" target="_blank"><span>Check out this lovely write up on Bari
 stanet</span></a> <span>from the Spring 2014.</span> <br></p><p><a href="ht
 tps://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=2&v=D453ajtWb74&feature=emb_logo"
  target="_blank"><span>Watch this video</span></a> <span>to find out more a
 bout walking the labyrinth. If you’ve never done so come out one Wednesday 
 evening and give it a try. It is a wonderful way to nourish your soul and s
 pend some quiet time in prayer or meditation.</span></p><u></u>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250618T102058Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:CLOSED TODAY: Weekly Labyrinth Walks\, Wednesdays 11am-1pm
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
