DESCRIPTION:<span>The Great Swamp National Wildlife Refuge is truly a victo
 ry for wild lands preservation for the State of New Jersey offering opportu
 nities for hiking\, walking &amp\; wildlife observation. It has a well main
 tained system of boardwalk trails that guides the walker through wetlands &
 amp\;forests home to whitetail deer\, red fox\, otters\, bobcats\, bear\, a
 nd a multitude of bird species! It is a beloved place &amp\; well worth the
  visit!  </span><span>Our outing will be an easy 1 hour-ish stroll right ov
 er the swamp on a flat 1.2 mile loop boardwalk path while we get a close-up
  view of an exciting array of plants and wildlife including frogs\, turtles
 \, mammals\, and birds</span><span>.<br></span><u><span>Please note:</span>
 </u><span><span> </span></span><span>Park rules do not allow dogs\, even on
  leashes\,because they disturb the wildlife.</span><span></span><br><span><
 br><b><span>Carpool from FCC parking lot 9am or</span></b> <b><span>meet us
  there </span></b></span><b><span>at the Helen C. Fenske Visitor Center</sp
 an></b> <span>3</span><span>2 Pleasant Plains Rd\, Basking Ridge\, Morris C
 ounty. We’ll meet at the visitor center.</span><span><br><i><span>Bring a s
 nack and water. Bring lunch if you’d like to eat together on picnic benches
  </span></i><i><span>under an open-air pavilion roof.  </span></i><b><span>
  </span></b></span><br><span><b><span> </span></b></span><br><span><b><span
 >Please RSVP</span></b> to <a href="mailto:greenteam@fccmtc.com" target="_b
 lank"><span>greenteam@fccmtc.com</span></a><br>The event is free but please
  register so we know to expect you. <br><br></span>
