DESCRIPTION:<p><span>FCC’s Green Team Ministry\, which is part of Interfait
 h Climate Action NJ\, is helping to create local events for “SUN DAY”\, a n
 ational weekend of advocacy\, education and social events for Clean Energy 
 and support for a healthy earth. Greenfaith\, United Church of Christ and T
 hird Act are among the broad organizations working to make this national we
 ekend happen.</span></p><p><span></span></p><p><span>There are several loca
 l opportunities on Saturday </span><span><span>9/20 and Sunday\, 9/21</span
 ></span><span> including:solar home tours\, a clean energy fair\, a “turn t
 he lights on” event\, climate justice reading and conversation book group\,
  and even a "renew your energy" dance party!  </span><span><span>Go to to <
 /span><span> <a href="https://firstcongmontclair.us6.list-manage.com/track/
 click?u=62bf2ca744bdb8b46fa1a7788&id=edde2d2041&e=d2d6ac503b" target="_blan
 k"><span>http://tinyurl.com/SUNDAY-2025</span></a> </span><span>to <b><span
 >look for events in the Montclair area.</span></b></span><span><br></span><
 /span></p><p><span><b>Registration is free but required for all activities.
 </b> (It would be a good idea to register early as there are capacity limit
 s at the venues.) Feel free to email <a href="mailto:greenteam@fccmtc.com" 
 target="_blank">greenteam@fccmtc.com</a>for more information. Hope to see y
 ou there! </span><span><br></span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250912T211315Z
