DESCRIPTION:<span>"From dust you came and to dust you shall return..."<i><b
 r></i><br>The season of Lent is a time for going deeper into our faith jour
 ney and coming to terms with our struggles and our yearning for God. It is 
 a time of reflection that prepares us for the passion of Holy Week and the 
 glory of Easter Sunday.<br> <br>We begin with a special Ash Wednesday servi
 ce. Through song and prayers and times of silence we will share the ritual 
 of the imposition of ashes\, a symbol of our mortality and brokenness\, as 
 well as experience the hope and unity of Holy Communion.<br> <br>This is a 
 deeply meaningful way to begin the season.  If you are new to our tradition
  and have never been to and Ash Wednesday service\, we encourage you to sha
 re it with us.<br><br>We will be<a href="https://firstcongmontclair.us6.lis
 t-manage.com/track/click?u=62bf2ca744bdb8b46fa1a7788&id=c98d769ddc&e=d2d6ac
 503b" target="_blank"><span> live-streaming</span></a> the service over Fac
 ebook.</span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250225T152126Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:The Journey of Lent Begins With Ash Wednesday\, 7:30pm in the Sanct
 uary
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
