DESCRIPTION:Support the work of the Community Food Bank of NJ as they colle
 ct frozen turkeys and other Thanksgiving dinner foods for families in need.
   Food items will be collected on the front walk of the church\, Sunday Nov
  24th from 9am—1pm. However\, if you're not able to\, then you can drop NON
 -PERISHABLE ONLY items off on Sunday 11/10 and Sunday 11/17. <i>Please mark
  the bags “Thanksgiving Food Drive” and leave them next to the shopping car
 t in the Narthex. </i><br><i> </i><br><u>MOST NEEDED ITEMS:</u><br>Turkey (
 MUST BE FROZEN and<u> brought directly to the collections truck</u> on the 
 day of the Drive!)\, Canned Yams\, Gravy (packs and cans)\, Cranberry Sauce
 \, Canned Vegetables\, Stuffing Mixes\, Instant Mashed Potatoes\, Applesauc
 e\, Canned Fruits\, Juice/Instant Coffee/Tea\, and Boxed Desserts (be sure 
 to check the expiration date).<br><br>Monetary donations for the Turkey Dri
 ve are also welcome - you can go directly to <a href="http://cfbnj.org/turk
 ey" target="_blank">cfbnj.org/turkey</a> <i>or checks can be made out to "C
 ommunity Food Bank of NJ" and dropped off at the truck.</i><br><br><u>VOLUN
 TEERS NEEDED</u><br>We still need a few volunteers. If you can help please 
 <a href="https://www.signupgenius.com/go/10C0B44AAAC28A2FB6-52969858-volunt
 eers#/" target="_blank">click this link</a> and sign up now.
