DESCRIPTION:<p><span>You are invited to a free film showing of <i>Cooked: S
 urvival by Zip Code</i>.<span> <br></span></span></p><p><span>In 1995\, a d
 isastrous heatwave (heat index was more than 126°) killed 739 Chicagoans in
  1 week\, most of them poor\, elderly and African American. This PBS docume
 ntary investigates the intersection of poverty\, politics\, economics and e
 nvironmental racism that underlies this tragedy.<span> <br></span></span></
 p><p><span>Presented by our local Interfaith Climate Action group. </span><
 /p><p><span>Hosted by Union Congregational Church at Bnai Keshet.<span> <br
 ></span></span></p><p><span>Thursday August 22\, 2024</span></p><p><span><b
 >Bnai Keshet 99 S. Fullerton Ave\, Montclair</b></span></p><p><span>6:30pm 
 — come early with your own dinner</span></p><p><span>7:00pm — film and disc
 ussion<span> <br></span></span></p><p><span>Extreme heat will continue and 
 worsen if we don’t stop burning fossil fuels. As a faith community\, what a
 ctions can we take?</span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20240809T172319Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Film “Cooked: Survival by Zip Code”\, Aug 22 at Bnai Keshet
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
