DESCRIPTION:<p><em><span><strong>If you're needing comfort this holiday sea
 son join us!</strong></span></em><br></p><p><span>Christmas is a time of jo
 y and celebration. Yet for many of us the holiday season brings more compli
 cated emotions. Separation from loved ones through distance or death\, pers
 onal illness\, difficult memories\, loneliness\, or financial stress can ma
 ke this "season of light" a time of darkness.</span></p><p><span>On Saturda
 y\, December 21\, the longest night of the year\, we will offer a special w
 orship to acknowledge  and hold the difficult emotions of the season and of
 fer a place for blessing and comfort.  At 7:30 we will begin our contemplat
 ive service of readings and music\, a time to pray individually with our pa
 stors\, receive an anointing with oil\, and an opportunity to walk the laby
 rinth.</span></p><p><span><em>You are not alone. Join us for moment of comf
 ort and hope. All are welcome.</em></span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20241211T145848Z
