DESCRIPTION:INTERFAITH CLIMATE ACTION INVITES YOU:<br>BYO LUNCH + CLIMATE R
 IBBONS PROJECT + PROTEST SATURDAY MAY 31\, 12:30 - 2:30<br><br>Weather perm
 itting\, we will gather on FCC’s front lawn for lunch and ribbon making. If
  raining\, we’ll meet in the Guild Room to make ribbons and assess our next
  move.<br><br>When our ribbons are completed\, we will attach them to strin
 gs\, and walk down the block to Church Street for some chanting and singing
 .<br><br>Then we will walk across the street to the Chase Bank at 19 North 
 Fullerton Ave to protest Chase’s funding of fossil fuel companies and profi
 ting at our expense. We’ll hang or tie ribbons around the neighborhood\, or
  take them with you to place as you wish.<br><br><b><u>You bring</u>: </b>y
 our own lunch\, water bottle\, a sharpie\, your passion for climate justice
 \, ideas for messages like a prayer\, motivational action\, inspiring thoug
 ht\, hope for the future\, or a demand for action.<br><p><span><strong><u><
 span>We supply:  </span></u></strong></span><span>Long strips of     fabric
 \, sample prompts for ribbon messages + f</span><span>lyers with     inform
 ation on banks that do not fund fossil fuels to hand out to people     pass
 ing by.</span> <br></p><span>Please register here so we have enough supplie
 s:  <a href="mailto:InterfaithClimateActionNJ@gmail.com" target="_blank">In
 terfaithClimateActionNJ@gmail.com</a></span>
