UID:6epldvedspr9k4klitu5flp354@google.com
CREATED:20250113T182308Z
DESCRIPTION:Come to our Enneagram workshop on February 1st\, led by FCC mem
 ber\, Cullen McVoy\, and discover your personality type. Then you will know
  something that can change your life—your personality is not who you really
  are. In fact you are much more! The Enneagram will enter your life as a fu
 n parlor game but then quickly become a powerful tool for personal growth.<
 br><br>The Enneagram is a colorful and enigmatic system of personality type
 s that facilitates spiritual growth and personal awareness. It teaches that
  while our personalities come in infinite varieties\, when reduced to essen
 tials they follow nine distinct patterns. Early in life\, not knowing who w
 e are\, we look for a ready-made pattern of behavior and values we can quic
 kly adopt as our own—hence we choose one of the nine personality types. Thi
 s gives us an identity and over time we come to believe our personality is 
 all that we are\, when in truth we are much more than our personality.<br><
 br>Understanding our Enneagram Type helps free us from its limitations\, op
 ening up our awareness of a vast world of human experience and a deeper com
 munion with God. Many have an “Aha moment” when they recognize their person
 ality type and its self-imposed limitations\, and realize they are free to 
 expand their horizons.<br><br> <br>FCC member\, Cullen McVoy is a retired a
 ttorney with a lifelong interest in the Enneagram. He is a graduate of the 
 New York Enneagram Institute and a certified Enneagram instructor. Cullen i
 s also a minster ordained by the Church of Wisdom\, an interfaith church de
 dicated to development of the inner senses\, and over the years has been ac
 tively engaged in energy healing\, and spiritual counselling.<br><br>Readin
 g: The Enneagram Made Easy: Discover the 9 Types of People\, by Elizabeth W
 agele and Renee Baron\; Personality Types by Don Riso and Russ Hudson.<br>I
 nternet Link: <a href="https://www.enneagraminstitute.com/">https://www.enn
 eagraminstitute.com/</a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250113T182308Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Discover Your Personality Type with the Enneagram—12:30pm in the Gu
 ild Room
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
