CREATED:20231211T211312Z
DESCRIPTION:<span><b><i><u>Active Hope</u></i>\, chapter 4 “Honoring Our Pa
 in for the World.“ 7pm in Room 5.</b></span><p>Can "Active Hope" inspire us
  in 2024 to be more proactive and determined in addressing our world's form
 idable problems---particularly the climate emergency?<span> <br></span></p>
 <p>Join us on January 10th as we dive into conversation and activities that
  explore Chapter 4 of this book\, "Honoring our Pain for the World."  We wi
 ll seek to move past our avoidance of emotional distress and easy fall-back
  to "business as usual"---and to explore an approach of creative engagement
  and renewed commitment\, which our authors call "Work that Reconnects." <s
 pan><span>This event is led by friends of the<span> </span>congregation\, C
 ynthia and John E. Rogers. </span></span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20231229T153236Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:"Active Hope" Continued Book Discussion\, chapter 4\, 7pm
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
