UID:2hbir5hvjoeednctt58mcoo9q7@google.com
CREATED:20251126T224813Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Sometimes the Christmas season is not so merry.<span> </span
 ><span><span>A contemplative service of comfort and blessing on the winter 
 solstice. </span></span></p><p><b>If you are needing comfort this season jo
 in us for The Longest Night Service.</b><br> <br>Christmas is a time of joy
  and celebration. Yet for many of us the holiday season brings more complic
 ated emotions. Separation from loved ones through distance or death\, perso
 nal illness\, difficult memories\, loneliness\, or financial stress can mak
 e this "season of light" a time of darkness. <br>On Sunday\, December 21\, 
 the longest night of the year\, we will offer a special worship to acknowle
 dge  and hold the difficult emotions of the season and offer a place for bl
 essing and comfort.  At 7:30 we will begin our contemplative service of rea
 dings and music\, a time to pray individually with our pastors\, receive an
  anointing with oil\, and an opportunity to walk the labyrinth.<br><br>You 
 are not alone. Join us for moment of comfort and hope. <b>All are welcome.<
 /b></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20251126T224813Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Longest Night service\, 7:30pm in the Sanctuary
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
