DESCRIPTION:<span>We take our time\, looking into historical context\, lang
 uage\, and any other disciplines that provide insight into our sacred texts
 . We will be starting with the Foundations of the Bible\, a primer that pro
 vides an overview of the structure and background of our Jewish and Christi
 an scriptures. That will be the first one or two weeks\,and then we will be
 gin looking at specific books. Participants are encouraged to bring their f
 avorite translation of the Bible<b>. </b></span><strong> </strong><br><stro
 ng>Here is the link we will use <u>each week </u>for the class: </strong><b
 r><span><span><a href="https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87533241357?pwd=suSsWRbraJ
 dH9z1MGSF0KeTsF8n36k.1" target="_blank">https://us02web.zoom.us/j/875332413
 57?pwd=suSsWRbraJdH9z1MGSF0KeTsF8n36k.1</a> <br>Meeting ID: 875 3324 1357<s
 pan> </span><br>Passcode: 481855 </span></span><br><br>If you have any ques
 tions\, please email Rev. Jack at <a href="mailto:jack@cuffari.com" target=
 "_blank">jack@cuffari.com</a>.
