BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:First Congregational Church Montclair
X-SOURCE-URL:https://fccmontclair.org/upcoming-events-at-fcc/
DTSTART:20250220T003000Z
DTEND:20250220T014500Z
DTSTAMP:20260401T043557Z
UID:19uv8agp8c091mbjtkvkt8usi5@google.com
CREATED:20250207T182509Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><i><span>We are so pleased to share a very special documenta
 ry with you:</span></i><span><br><br></span><b><i><span>MAYA ANGELOU: REFLE
 CTIONS OF A BLESSED SOUL</span></i></b><span> </span></p><p><span><span><a 
 href="https://us02web.zoom.us/j/6242947554#success">Click here for the zoom
  link.</a></span></span></p><p><span>A documentary film based on an exclusi
 ve interview with Maya Angelou in her home in Winston Salem\, North Carolin
 a by the multi-award winning filmmakers Hafiz Farid\, Shelley Grodner Seide
 nstein\, and Richard Woods.<br><br>The film offers an intimate portrait of 
 one of the greatest Artists/ Poets/Activists/ Teachers/ Philosophers and Hu
 manitarians of our time. With a razor sharp memory of events that occurred 
 many decades ago\, Dr. Angelou reflects on her unforgettable experiences\, 
 and her deep insight into the most controversial and pressing issues of the
  day.</span><span><br><br></span><b><span>Hafiz Farid is a friend of First 
 Congregational Church and will be hosting the evening and discussion. </spa
 n></b></p><br><b><span>Hafiz Farid</span></b><span> is the Founder and Exec
 utive Director of the non-profit organization NoCane Inc\, which has been p
 roviding art-based seminars\, workshops\, projects and documentary films fo
 r over 25 years to promote the well-being of the community. Hafiz went on t
 o produce/write/direct multiple award-winning documentary films\, including
 : <i><b><span>A Pillar of Salt: The Angry Woman Syndrome</span></b></i><b><
 span>\, </span></b>which examines the root causes of anger and bitterness a
 nd the physical\, emotional and spiritual effects of these greatly misunder
 stood emotions\;  <i><span>and<b> Darfur Too Dark Too Far</b></span></i>\, 
 the powerful documentary written and directed by Hafiz\, exposes the root c
 auses of genocide as being slavery\, racism and oppression in the name of r
 eligion. </span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250218T212853Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:An evening with Maya Angelou (documentary)\, 7:30 on Zoom
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
