DESCRIPTION:<span>The interfaith climate community has been working hard to
  pass the NJ Climate Superfund bill(A4696/S3545) in NJ\, aka Make Polluters
  Pay. Last week's White House executive order targets state climate legisla
 tion and any attempts to hold fossil fuel companies accountable.<br><br>NJ 
 Senator John McKeon says Hands Off our climate legislation:<br>“We will not
  let the Trump Administration bully us into submission. New Jersey will con
 tinue working to achieve environmental justice and create a more sustainabl
 e and affordable future for all through clean energy initiatives.”<br><br>J
 oin Senator McKeon (the bill's sponsor)\, climate activists\, local elected
  officials\, local residents and the interfaith community to discuss the wa
 ys NJ is already experiencing the impacts of the climate crisis\, fight bac
 k against federal attempts to target state climate legislation\, and mobili
 ze support for the Climate Superfund bill.</span>  <span><a href="https://f
 irstcongmontclair.us6.list-manage.com/track/click?u=62bf2ca744bdb8b46fa1a77
 88&id=4f86e2a08e&e=d2d6ac503b" target="_blank"><b><span>Please register her
 e!</span></b></a></span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250425T192357Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Hands Off Our Planet: Montclair Town Hall @ FCC\, Sunday\, April 27
 \, 2:30-4pm
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
