UID:0pt4lba36ptvf4sgi1j0buj48j@google.com
CREATED:20241025T200349Z
DESCRIPTION:<span><span>When confronted with climate change many of us feel
  angry and despairing. Can we change this mood to a cautious optimism? </sp
 an></span><span>The Green Team Ministry invites you to come together to lis
 ten to this response to our climate crisis in an inspiring podcast featurin
 g </span><span><span><span>Dr. Ayana Elizabeth Johnson</span></span></span>
 <span> after worship at 12:15pm\,<i><span> </span></i><span>as she discusse
 s how to transform climate despair into climate action!</span></span><span>
  <br><br></span><span>Ayana Elizabeth Johnson\, a marine biologist\,climate
  expert\, and author of <i><span>What if We Get it Right: Visions of Climat
 e Futures</span></i>\, believes this can happen. If we recognize the opport
 unities inherent in the problems\, we can then harness the energy of millio
 ns of people who want to be part of the solutions\,but don't know where to 
 start. There are actions we can start now that will transform and replenish
  our world. <br><br><b><i><span>Get your coffee and snack and make your way
  to the FCC library.</span></i></b>  After the podcast\, let's share ideas 
 about ways we can start being part of the solution.  Hope to see you there!
 </span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20241028T173033Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Change Climate Despair into Climate Action\, 12:15pm in the FCC Lib
 rary
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
