DESCRIPTION:<h4><span><i>Enter from the back parking lot. </i></span></h4><
 h4><span>Experience this special Ramadan tradition through an evening of ed
 ucation\, friendship and food!</span></h4><p><span></span><span>The holy mo
 nth of Ramadan is a sacred time for Muslims. Similar to our season of Lent\
 , it is an time of intentional prayer\,actions and fasting to bring our sou
 ls closer to God. One of the daily practices is to fast from sun up to sun 
 down each day and then break the fast with an Iftar dinner -- a celebratory
  time to gather with friends and family ingratitude for God's blessings.<br
 ><br>On March 5\, our friends from Peace Islands Institute\, have offered t
 o provide a special experience to share this tradition with us. They will o
 ffer a presentation on the spiritual and cultural practices of Ramadan and 
 provide a delicious traditional Turkish Iftar dinner for us.  As always\, w
 e will enjoy deepening our friendships with this wonderful community!</span
 ><span>  </span></p><b><span>IF YOU'LL BE ATTENDING <u>PLEASE RSVP</u> ON T
 HE LINK BELOW</span></b><b><span> <b><u><span>AS SOON AS POSSIBLE</span></u
 ></b></span></b><span><span><b>.</b></span></span><span> <span><i>Peace Isl
 ands need to know how many to cook for.</i></span></span><span><br><br></sp
 an><b><span>IF YOU'D LIKE TO BRING A DESSERT:</span></b><b><span> </span></
 b><span><span>What we need are</span></span><b><span><b><span> <u>bite-size
 d finger desserts</u> <i>(no gelatin or alcoholic ingredients.)</i></span><
 /b></span></b><span>  </span><span><a href="https://firstcongmontclair.us6.
 list-manage.com/track/click?u=62bf2ca744bdb8b46fa1a7788&id=a862b2a56a&e=d2d
 6ac503b" target="_blank"><b><span>SIGNUP HERE</span></b></a></span><span><b
 r><br></span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260224T174111Z
LOCATION:40 S Fullerton Ave\, Montclair\, NJ 07042\, USA
